  19                   julia_code, lambdify, nsimplify, octave_code, pi, powsimp,
  20                   symbols, zeros)

  23from sympy.simplify.cse_main import numbered_symbols

  35class _AbstractCodeGeneration():
  36    def __init__(self) -> None:
  37        # variables for Code Generation:
  38        self.fkin = None  # forward_kinematics
  39        self.J = None  # system_jacobian_matrix
  40        self.Jb = None  # body_jacobian_matrix
  41        self.Jh = None  # hybrid_jacobian_matrix
  42        self.Jdot = None  # system_jacobian_dot
  43        self.Vb_ee = None  # body_twist_ee
  44        self.Vh_ee = None  # hybrid_twist_ee
  45        self.Jb_ee = None  # body_jacobian_matrix_ee
  46        self.Jh_ee = None  # hybrid_jacobian_matrix_ee
  47        self.M = None  # generalized_mass_inertia_matrix
  48        self.C = None  # coriolis_centrifugal_matrix
  49        self.Qgrav = None  # gravity_vector
  50        self.Q = None  # inverse_dynamics
  51        self.Md = None # generalized_mass_inertia_matrix_dot 
  52        self.Cd = None # coriolis_centrifugal_matrix_dot
  53        self.Qdgrav = None # gravity_vector_dot
  54        self.Qd = None # inverse_dynamics_dot
  55        self.M2d = None # generalized_mass_inertia_matrix_ddot
  56        self.C2d = None # coriolis_centrifugal_matrix_ddot
  57        self.Q2dgrav = None # gravity_vector_ddot
  58        self.Q2d = None # inverse_dynamics_ddot
  59        self.Vh_BFn = None # hybrid_twist
  60        self.Vb_BFn = None # body_twist
  61        self.Vhd_BFn = None  # hybrid_acceleration
  62        self.Vbd_BFn = None  # body_acceleration
  63        self.Vhd_ee = None  # hybrid_acceleration_ee
  64        self.Vbd_ee = None  # body_acceleration_ee
  65        self.Jh_dot = None  # hybrid_jacobian_matrix_dot
  66        self.Jb_dot = None  # body_jacobian_matrix_dot
  67        self.Jh_ee_dot = None  # hybrid_jacobian_matrix_ee_dot
  68        self.Jb_ee_dot = None  # body_jacobian_matrix_ee_dot
  69        self.Yr = None # regressor_matrix
  70        self.Xr = None # parameter_vector
  71
  72        # set of variable symbols to use in generated functions as arguments
  73        self.var_syms = set()
  74        self.optional_var_syms = set() # for wrenches
  75        
  76        # Value assignment
  77        # dict with assigned variables for code generation
  78        self.assignment_dict = {}  
  79        # dict for subexpressions fro common subexpression elimination
  80        self.subex_dict = {}  
  81
  82        self.all_symbols = set()  # set with all used symbols
  83
  84
  85    def get_expressions_dict(self, filterNone: bool=True) -> dict[str,sympy.Expr | None]:
  86        """Get dictionary with expression names (key) and generated 
  87        expressions (value).
  88
  89        Args:
  90            filterNone (bool, optional): 
  91                Exclude expressions which haven't been generate yet. 
  92                Defaults to True.
  93
  94        Returns:
  95            dict: dictionary with expression names (key) and generated 
  96                expressions (value).
  97        """
  98        # all expressions in this dictionary can be code generated 
  99        # using the generate_code function.
 100        expressions = {"forward_kinematics": self.fkin,
 101                       "system_jacobian_matrix": self.J,
 102                       "body_jacobian_matrix": self.Jb,
 103                       "hybrid_jacobian_matrix": self.Jh,
 104                       "system_jacobian_dot": self.Jdot,
 105                       "body_twist_ee": self.Vb_ee,
 106                       "hybrid_twist_ee": self.Vh_ee,
 107                       "body_twist": self.Vb_BFn,
 108                       "hybrid_twist": self.Vh_BFn,
 109                       "body_jacobian_matrix_ee": self.Jb_ee,
 110                       "hybrid_jacobian_matrix_ee": self.Jh_ee,
 111                       "generalized_mass_inertia_matrix": self.M,
 112                       "coriolis_centrifugal_matrix": self.C,
 113                       "gravity_vector": self.Qgrav,
 114                       "inverse_dynamics": self.Q,
 115                       "hybrid_acceleration": self.Vhd_BFn,
 116                       "body_acceleration": self.Vbd_BFn,
 117                       "hybrid_acceleration_ee": self.Vhd_ee,
 118                       "body_acceleration_ee": self.Vbd_ee,
 119                       "hybrid_jacobian_matrix_dot": self.Jh_dot,
 120                       "body_jacobian_matrix_dot": self.Jb_dot,
 121                       "hybrid_jacobian_matrix_ee_dot": self.Jh_ee_dot,
 122                       "body_jacobian_matrix_ee_dot": self.Jb_ee_dot,
 123                       "generalized_mass_inertia_matrix_dot": self.Md, 
 124                       "coriolis_centrifugal_matrix_dot": self.Cd,
 125                       "gravity_vector_dot": self.Qdgrav,
 126                       "inverse_dynamics_dot": self.Qd,
 127                       "generalized_mass_inertia_matrix_ddot": self.M2d,
 128                       "coriolis_centrifugal_matrix_ddot": self.C2d,
 129                       "gravity_vector_ddot": self.Q2dgrav,
 130                       "inverse_dynamics_ddot": self.Q2d,
 131                       "regressor_matrix": self.Yr,
 132                       "parameter_vector": self.Xr,
 133                       }  
 134        
 135        # deal with multiple ee
 136        all_expressions = {}
 137        for k, v in expressions.items():
 138            if type(v) is list:
 139                if len(v) > 1:
 140                    for i in range(len(v)):
 141                        all_expressions[f"{k}_{i+1}"] = v[i]
 142                else:
 143                    all_expressions[k] = v[0]
 144            else:
 145                all_expressions[k] = v
 146        
 147        # exclude expressions which are None
 148        if filterNone:
 149            filtered = {k: v for k, v in all_expressions.items()
 150                        if v is not None}
 151            return filtered
 152        return all_expressions
 153
 154    def generate_code(self, python: bool=False, C: bool=False, Matlab: bool=False, 
 155                      cython: bool=False, julia: bool=False, latex: bool=False, 
 156                      cache: bool=False, landscape: bool=False,
 157                      folder: str="./generated_code", use_global_vars: bool=True, 
 158                      name: str="plant", project: str="Project") -> None:
 159        """Generate code from generated expressions. 
 160        Generates Python, C (C99), Matlab/Octave, Cython and/or LaTeX code.  
 161        Needs 'closed_form_inv_dyn_body_fixed' and/or 
 162        'closed_form_kinematics_body_fixed' to run first.
 163
 164
 165        Args:
 166            python (bool, optional): 
 167                Generate Python code. Defaults to False.
 168            C (bool, optional): 
 169                Generate C99 code. Defaults to False.
 170            Matlab (bool, optional): 
 171                Generate Matlab/Octave code. Defaults to False.
 172            cython (bool, optional):
 173                Generate cython code. Defaults to False.
 174            julia (bool, optional):
 175                Generate julia code. Defaults to False.
 176            latex (bool, optional):
 177                Generate latex code with all equations and generate pdf from it. 
 178                Defaults to False.
 179            cache (bool, optional):
 180                Cache results sin and cos function in generated python 
 181                and cython code. Defaults to False.
 182            landscape (bool, optional):
 183                Generate LaTeX document in landscape mode to fit longer equations.
 184                Defaults to False.
 185            folder (str, optional): 
 186                Folder where to save code. 
 187                Defaults to "./generated_code".
 188            use_global_vars (bool, optional): 
 189                Constant vars like mass etc are no arguments of the 
 190                generated expressions. Defaults to True.
 191            name (str, optional): 
 192                Name of class and file. 
 193                Defaults to "plant".
 194            project (str, optional): 
 195                Project name in C header. Defaults to "Project".
 196
 197        """
 198        # create Folder
 199        if not os.path.exists(folder):
 200            os.mkdir(folder)
 201
 202        # dict of expression names and expressions
 203        all_expressions = self.get_expressions_dict()
 204
 205        # get individual tuples for expression names and expressions
 206        (names, expressions) = zip(*all_expressions.items())
 207
 208        # generate set with all used symbols
 209        all_syms = set()
 210        for e in expressions:
 211            all_syms.update(e.free_symbols)
 212
 213        if use_global_vars:
 214            # generate list of constant symbols
 215            constant_syms = self._sort_variables(
 216                all_syms
 217                .difference(self.var_syms)
 218                .difference(self.optional_var_syms)
 219                .union(self.subex_dict))
 220            # generate list with preassigned symbols like subexpressions
 221            # from common subexpression elimination
 222            not_assigned_syms = self._sort_variables(
 223                all_syms
 224                .difference(self.var_syms)
 225                .difference(self.optional_var_syms)
 226                .difference(self.assignment_dict)
 227                .difference(self.subex_dict)
 228                )
 229        else:
 230            constant_syms = []
 231            not_assigned_syms = []
 232
 233        if python:
 234            print("Generate Python code")
 235            # create folder
 236            if not os.path.exists(os.path.join(folder, "python")):
 237                os.mkdir(os.path.join(folder, "python"))
 238
 239            p = NumPyPrinter()
 240
 241            # start python file with import
 242            s = ["import numpy"]
 243            if cache:
 244                s.append("from functools import lru_cache")
 245            s.append("\n")
 246            # class name
 247            s.append("class "+regex.sub("^\w",lambda x: x.group().upper(),name)+"():")
 248            # define __init__ function
 249            s.append("    def __init__(self, %s) -> None:" % (
 250                ", ".join(
 251                    [str(not_assigned_syms[i])+": float" 
 252                     for i in range(len(not_assigned_syms))] 
 253                    + [str(i)+": float=" + str(self.assignment_dict[i]) 
 254                       for i in self.assignment_dict])))
 255            if len(not_assigned_syms) > 0:
 256                s.append("        "
 257                         + ", ".join(["self."+str(not_assigned_syms[i]) 
 258                                      for i in range(len(not_assigned_syms))])
 259                         + " = " 
 260                         + ", ".join([str(not_assigned_syms[i]) 
 261                                      for i in range(len(not_assigned_syms))])
 262                         )
 263
 264            # append preassigned values to __init__ function
 265            if len(self.assignment_dict) > 0:
 266                s.append("        "
 267                         + ", ".join(sorted(["self."+str(i) 
 268                                             for i in self.assignment_dict]))
 269                         + " = " 
 270                         + ", ".join(sorted([str(i) 
 271                                             for i in self.assignment_dict]))
 272                         )
 273
 274            # append cse expressions to __init__ function
 275            if len(self.subex_dict) > 0:
 276                for i in sorted([str(j) for j in self.subex_dict], key=lambda x: int(regex.findall("(?<=sub)\d*",x)[0])):
 277                    modstring = p.doprint(self.subex_dict[symbols(i)])
 278                    for j in sorted([str(h) 
 279                                     for h in self.subex_dict[symbols(i)].free_symbols],
 280                                    reverse=1):
 281                        modstring = regex.sub(
 282                            str(j), "self."+str(j), modstring)
 283                        # remove double self
 284                        modstring = regex.sub("self.self.", "self.", modstring)
 285                    s.append("        self."+str(i)+" = " + modstring)
 286
 287            # avoid empty init function
 288            if (not len(self.subex_dict) > 0 
 289                and not len(self.assignment_dict) > 0
 290                and not len(not_assigned_syms) > 0
 291                ):
 292                s.append("        pass")
 293            
 294            # define functions
 295            for i in range(len(expressions)):
 296                var_syms = self._sort_variables(self.var_syms.intersection(
 297                    expressions[i].free_symbols))
 298                optional_var_syms = self._sort_variables(self.optional_var_syms.intersection(
 299                    expressions[i].free_symbols))
 300                const_syms = self._sort_variables(
 301                    set(constant_syms).intersection(
 302                        expressions[i].free_symbols))
 303                if len(var_syms) > 0 or len(optional_var_syms) > 0:
 304                    s.append("\n    def "+names[i]+"(self, %s) -> numpy.ndarray:" % (
 305                        ", ".join([str(var_syms[i])+": float" 
 306                                   for i in range(len(var_syms))]
 307                                  + [str(optional_var_syms[i])+": float=0" 
 308                                   for i in range(len(optional_var_syms))])))
 309
 310                else:
 311                    s.append("\n    def "+names[i]+"(self) -> numpy.ndarray:")
 312                
 313                if const_syms: # insert self. in front of const_syms
 314                    s.append("        "
 315                            + names[i] 
 316                            + " = " 
 317                            + regex.sub(f"(?<=\W|^)(?={'|'.join([str(i) for i in const_syms])}(\W|\Z))",
 318                                        "self.",
 319                                        p.doprint(expressions[i])))
 320                else: 
 321                    s.append("        "
 322                            + names[i] 
 323                            + " = " 
 324                            + p.doprint(expressions[i]))
 325                s.append("        return " + names[i])
 326
 327            if cache:
 328                s = list(map(lambda x: x.replace("numpy.sin", "cached_sin"), s))
 329                s = list(map(lambda x: x.replace("numpy.cos", "cached_cos"), s))
 330                
 331                s.append("")
 332                s.append("@lru_cache(maxsize=128)")
 333                s.append("def cached_sin(x: float) -> float:")
 334                s.append("    return numpy.sin(x)")
 335                s.append("")
 336                s.append("@lru_cache(maxsize=128)")
 337                s.append("def cached_cos(x: float) -> float:")
 338                s.append("    return numpy.cos(x)")
 339                
 340            # replace numpy with np for better readability
 341            s = list(map(lambda x: x.replace("numpy.", "np."), s))
 342            s[0] = "import numpy as np\n\n"
 343
 344            # join list to string
 345            s = "\n".join(s)
 346
 347            # write python file
 348            with open(os.path.join(folder, "python", name + ".py"), "w+") as f:
 349                f.write(s)
 350            print("Done")
 351
 352        if cython:
 353            print("Generate Cython code")
 354            # create folder
 355            if not os.path.exists(os.path.join(folder, "cython")):
 356                os.mkdir(os.path.join(folder, "cython"))
 357
 358            p = NumPyPrinter()
 359
 360            # start python file with import
 361            s = ["import numpy"]
 362            s.append("cimport numpy\n")
 363            s.append("cimport cython\n")
 364            if cache:
 365                s.append("from functools import lru_cache\n")
 366            s.append("")
 367            s.append("numpy.import_array()")
 368            # s.append("DTYPE = numpy.float64")
 369            # s.append("ctypedef numpy.float64_t DTYPE_t")
 370            
 371            s.append("\n")
 372            # class name
 373            s.append("@cython.boundscheck(False)")
 374            s.append("@cython.wraparound(False)")
 375            s.append("cdef class "+regex.sub("^\w",lambda x: x.group().upper(),name)+"():")
 376            s.append("    cdef public double %s\n"%(
 377                ", ".join(
 378                    [str(not_assigned_syms[i]) 
 379                        for i in range(len(not_assigned_syms))] 
 380                    + [str(i) 
 381                      for i in self.assignment_dict])))
 382            if self.subex_dict:
 383                s.append("    cdef double %s\n"%(
 384                    ", ".join(
 385                        [str(i) 
 386                        for i in self.subex_dict])))
 387                    
 388            
 389            # define __cinit__ function
 390            s.append("    def __cinit__(self, %s):" % (
 391                ", ".join(
 392                    ["double "+str(not_assigned_syms[i]) 
 393                     for i in range(len(not_assigned_syms))] 
 394                    + ["double "+str(i)+" = " + str(self.assignment_dict[i]) 
 395                       for i in self.assignment_dict])))
 396            if len(not_assigned_syms) > 0:
 397                s.append("        "
 398                         + ", ".join(["self."+str(not_assigned_syms[i]) 
 399                                      for i in range(len(not_assigned_syms))])
 400                         + " = " 
 401                         + ", ".join([str(not_assigned_syms[i]) 
 402                                      for i in range(len(not_assigned_syms))])
 403                         )
 404
 405            # append preassigned values to __cinit__ function
 406            if len(self.assignment_dict) > 0:
 407                s.append("        "
 408                         + ", ".join(sorted(["self."+str(i) 
 409                                             for i in self.assignment_dict]))
 410                         + " = " 
 411                         + ", ".join(sorted([str(i) 
 412                                             for i in self.assignment_dict]))
 413                         )
 414
 415            # append cse expressions to __cinit__ function
 416            if len(self.subex_dict) > 0:
 417                for i in sorted([str(j) for j in self.subex_dict], key=lambda x: int(regex.findall("(?<=sub)\d*",x)[0])):
 418                    modstring = p.doprint(self.subex_dict[symbols(i)])
 419                    for j in sorted([str(h) 
 420                                     for h in self.subex_dict[symbols(i)].free_symbols],
 421                                    reverse=1):
 422                        modstring = regex.sub(
 423                            str(j), "self."+str(j), modstring)
 424                        modstring = regex.sub("(?<=(\W|^)(?<!\.)\d+)(?!\.)(?=\W|\Z)",".0", modstring) # replace integer with floats
 425                        # remove double self
 426                        modstring = regex.sub("self.self.", "self.", modstring)
 427                    s.append("        self."+str(i)+" = " + modstring)
 428
 429            # avoid empty init function
 430            if (not len(self.subex_dict) > 0 
 431                and not len(self.assignment_dict) > 0
 432                and not len(not_assigned_syms) > 0
 433                ):
 434                s.append("        pass")
 435            
 436            # define functions
 437            for i in range(len(expressions)):
 438                var_syms = self._sort_variables(self.var_syms.intersection(
 439                    expressions[i].free_symbols))
 440                optional_var_syms = self._sort_variables(self.optional_var_syms.intersection(
 441                    expressions[i].free_symbols))
 442                const_syms = self._sort_variables(
 443                    set(constant_syms).intersection(
 444                        expressions[i].free_symbols))
 445                s.append("") # empty line
 446                s.append("    @cython.boundscheck(False)")
 447                s.append("    @cython.wraparound(False)")
 448                if len(var_syms) > 0 or len(optional_var_syms) > 0:
 449                    # s.append(f"    cpdef double[:,::1] "+names[i]+"(self, %s):" % (
 450                    s.append(f"    cpdef numpy.ndarray[double, ndim={len(expressions[i].shape)}] "+names[i]+"(self, %s):" % (
 451                    # s.append(f"\n    cpdef np.ndarray[DTYPE_t,ndim={len(expressions[i].shape)}] "+names[i]+"(self, %s):" % (
 452                        ", ".join(["double "+str(var_syms[i]) 
 453                                   for i in range(len(var_syms))]
 454                                  + ["double "+str(optional_var_syms[i])+"=0.0" 
 455                                     for i in range(len(optional_var_syms))])))
 456
 457                else:
 458                    s.append(f"    cpdef numpy.ndarray[double, ndim={len(expressions[i].shape)}] "+names[i]+"(self):")
 459                
 460                # s.append(f"        cdef double[:,::1] {names[i]} = numpy.empty({expressions[i].shape}, dtype=double)")
 461                s.append(f"        cdef numpy.ndarray[double, ndim={len(expressions[i].shape)}] {names[i]} = numpy.empty({expressions[i].shape}, dtype=np.double)")
 462                for j in range(expressions[i].shape[0]):
 463                    for k in range(expressions[i].shape[1]):
 464                        if const_syms:
 465                            # add self before const_syms
 466                            ex_string = regex.sub(f"(?<=\W|^)(?={'|'.join([str(i) for i in const_syms])}(\W|\Z))","self.",p.doprint(expressions[i][j,k]))
 467                            # replace integer with floats
 468                            ex_string = regex.sub("(?<=(\W|^)(?<!\.)\d+)(?!\.)(?=\W|\Z)",".0", ex_string) 
 469                            s.append("        "
 470                                    + names[i]
 471                                    + f"[{j}, {k}]" 
 472                                    + " = " 
 473                                    + ex_string)
 474                                    #  + regex.sub("(?<=((?<=[^\.])\W)\d+)(?=\W)(?!\.)",".0",regex.sub(f"(?<=\W|^)(?={'|'.join([str(i) for i in const_syms])}(\W|\Z))","self.",p.doprint(expressions[i]))))
 475                        else:
 476                            ex_string = p.doprint(expressions[i])
 477                            # replace integer with floats
 478                            ex_string = regex.sub("(?<=(\W|^)(?<!\.)\d+)(?!\.)(?=\W|\Z)",".0", ex_string) 
 479                            s.append("        "
 480                                    + names[i] 
 481                                    + f"[{j}, {k}]" 
 482                                    + " = " 
 483                                    + ex_string)
 484                            
 485                s.append("        return " + names[i])
 486
 487            if cache:
 488                s = list(map(lambda x: x.replace("numpy.sin", "cached_sin"), s))
 489                s = list(map(lambda x: x.replace("numpy.cos", "cached_cos"), s))
 490                
 491                s.append("")
 492                s.append("@lru_cache(maxsize=128)")
 493                s.append("def cached_sin(double x):")
 494                s.append("    return numpy.sin(x)")
 495                s.append("")
 496                s.append("@lru_cache(maxsize=128)")
 497                s.append("def cached_cos(double x):")
 498                s.append("    return numpy.cos(x)")
 499            
 500            # replace numpy with np for better readability
 501            s = list(map(lambda x: x.replace("numpy.", "np."), s))
 502            s[0] = "import numpy as np"
 503            s[1] = "cimport numpy as np\n"
 504
 505            # join list to string
 506            s = "\n".join(s)
 507
 508            # create setup file to compile cython code
 509            su = ("import os.path\n"
 510                  + "from setuptools import setup\n"
 511                  + "from Cython.Build import cythonize\n"
 512                  + "\n"
 513                  + "setup(\n"
 514                  + f"    name='{name}',\n"
 515                  + f"    ext_modules=cythonize(os.path.join(os.path.dirname(__file__), '{name + '.pyx'}'), \n"
 516                  +  "                          compiler_directives={'language_level' : '3'}),\n"
 517                  + "    zip_safe=False,\n"
 518                  + ")\n"
 519            )
 520
 521
 522            # write cython file
 523            with open(os.path.join(folder, "cython", name + ".pyx"), "w+") as f:
 524                f.write(s)
 525            
 526            # write setup file
 527            with open(os.path.join(folder, "cython", "setup_" + name + ".py"), "w+") as f:
 528                f.write(su)
 529            
 530            print("Done")
 531
 532        if C:
 533            print("Generate C code")
 534            if not os.path.exists(os.path.join(folder, "C")):
 535                os.mkdir(os.path.join(folder, "C"))
 536
 537            # generate c files
 538            if use_global_vars:
 539                [(c_name, c_code), (h_name, c_header)] = codegen(
 540                    [tuple((names[i], expressions[i])) 
 541                     for i in range(len(expressions))],
 542                    "C99", name, project, header=False, 
 543                    empty=True, global_vars=constant_syms)
 544            else:
 545                [(c_name, c_code), (h_name, c_header)] = codegen(
 546                    [tuple((names[i], expressions[i])) 
 547                     for i in range(len(expressions))],
 548                    "C99", name, project, header=False, empty=True)
 549            # change strange variable names
 550            c_code = regex.sub(r"out_\d{10}[\d]+", "out", c_code)
 551            c_header = regex.sub(r"out_\d{10}[\d]+", "out", c_header)
 552
 553            c_lines = c_code.splitlines(True)
 554            i = 0
 555            # correct dimension of output array pointers
 556            while i < len(c_lines):
 557                # find function definition
 558                if any(n+"(" in c_lines[i] for n in names):
 559                    # which expression is defined
 560                    [fname] = [n for n in names if n+"(" in c_lines[i]]
 561                    # find shape of expression
 562                    cols = all_expressions[fname].shape[1]
 563                    i += 1
 564                    # replace all 1D arrays with 2D arrays for matrices
 565                    while "}" not in c_lines[i]:
 566                        out = regex.findall("out\[[\d]+\]", c_lines[i])
 567                        if out and cols > 1:
 568                            [num] = regex.findall("[\d]+", out[0])
 569                            num = int(num)
 570                            c_lines[i] = c_lines[i].replace(
 571                                out[0], f"out[{num//cols}][{num%cols}]")
 572                        i += 1
 573                i += 1
 574            c_code = "".join(c_lines)
 575            
 576            # save assinged parameters to another c file
 577            c_def_name = f"{c_name[:-2]}_parameters.c"
 578            header_insert = []
 579            c_definitions = [f'#include "{h_name}"\n']
 580            c_definitions.append("#include <math.h>\n")
 581            c_definitions.append("\n")
 582            
 583            if not_assigned_syms:
 584                header_insert.append(f"/* Please uncomment and assign values in '{c_def_name}'\n")
 585                c_definitions.append(f"/* Please assign values and uncomment in '{h_name}'\n")
 586                for var in sorted([str(i) for i in not_assigned_syms]):
 587                    header_insert.append(f"extern const float {var};\n")
 588                    if var == "g":
 589                        c_definitions.append(f"const float {var} = 9.81;\n")
 590                    else:
 591                        c_definitions.append(f"const float {var} = 0;\n")
 592                header_insert.append("*/ \n")
 593                c_definitions.append("*/ \n")
 594            
 595            for var in sorted([str(i) for i in self.assignment_dict]):
 596                val = ccode(self.assignment_dict[symbols(var)])
 597                header_insert.append(f"extern const float {var};\n")
 598                c_definitions.append(f"const float {var} = {val};\n")
 599
 600
 601            # append cse expressions
 602            for var in sorted([str(j) for j in self.subex_dict], key=lambda x: int(regex.findall("(?<=sub)\d*",x)[0])):
 603                val = ccode(self.subex_dict[symbols(var)])
 604                header_insert.append(f"extern const float {var};\n")
 605                c_definitions.append(f"const float {var} = {val};\n")
 606
 607            
 608            
 609            if header_insert:
 610                header_insert.append("\n")
 611                h_lines = c_header.splitlines(True)
 612                for i in range(len(h_lines)):
 613                    if "#endif" in h_lines[i]:
 614                        h_lines[i:i] = header_insert 
 615                        break
 616                c_header = "".join(h_lines)
 617
 618            # write code files
 619            with open(os.path.join(folder, "C", c_name), "w+") as f:
 620                f.write(c_code)
 621            with open(os.path.join(folder, "C", h_name), "w+") as f:
 622                f.write(c_header)
 623            if header_insert:
 624                with open(os.path.join(folder, "C", c_def_name), "w+") as f:
 625                    f.writelines(c_definitions)
 626                
 627            print("Done")
 628
 629        if julia:
 630            print("Generate julia code")
 631            if not os.path.exists(os.path.join(folder, "julia")):
 632                os.mkdir(os.path.join(folder, "julia"))
 633
 634            jcg = JuliaCodeGen(project=project)
 635            if use_global_vars:
 636                routines = [jcg.routine(names[i],
 637                                        expressions[i],
 638                                        self._sort_variables(
 639                                            (self.var_syms 
 640                                             | self.optional_var_syms)
 641                                            & expressions[i].free_symbols),
 642                                        global_vars=constant_syms) 
 643                            for i in range(len(expressions))]
 644                
 645                # save assigned parameters to beginning of julia file
 646                j_definitions = []
 647                
 648                if not_assigned_syms:
 649                    j_definitions.append("# Please assign values\n")
 650                    for var in sorted([str(i) for i in not_assigned_syms]):
 651                        if var == "g":
 652                            j_definitions.append(f"{var} = 9.81\n")
 653                        else:
 654                            j_definitions.append(f"{var} = 0\n")
 655                    j_definitions.append("\n")
 656
 657                if self.assignment_dict:                
 658                    for var in sorted([str(i) for i in self.assignment_dict]):
 659                        val = julia_code(self.assignment_dict[symbols(var)])
 660                        j_definitions.append(f"{var} = {val}\n")
 661                    j_definitions.append("\n")
 662
 663                # append cse expressions
 664                if self.subex_dict:
 665                    j_definitions.append("# subexpressions due to cse\n")
 666                    for var in sorted([str(j) for j in self.subex_dict], key=lambda x: int(regex.findall("(?<=sub)\d*",x)[0])):
 667                        val = julia_code(self.subex_dict[symbols(var)])
 668                        j_definitions.append(f"{var} = {val}\n")
 669                    j_definitions.append("\n")
 670
 671                j_constants = "".join(j_definitions)
 672            else:
 673                routines = [jcg.routine(names[i],
 674                                        expressions[i],
 675                                        self._sort_variables(
 676                                            expressions[i].free_symbols),
 677                                        global_vars=None) 
 678                            for i in range(len(expressions))]
 679                j_constants = ""
 680                
 681            j_name, j_code = jcg.write(routines,name, header=False)[0]
 682            j_code = j_constants + j_code
 683            
 684            # ensure operator ^ instead of **
 685            j_code = j_code.replace("**","^")
 686            
 687            # write code files
 688            with open(os.path.join(folder, "julia", j_name), "w+") as f:
 689                f.write(j_code)
 690            
 691            print("Done")
 692
 693
 694
 695        if Matlab:
 696            # create folder
 697            if not os.path.exists(os.path.join(folder, "matlab")):
 698                os.mkdir(os.path.join(folder, "matlab"))
 699            m_class = []
 700            m_class.append(f"classdef {name}\n")
 701            m_properties = not_assigned_syms[:]
 702            m_properties.extend([i for i in self.assignment_dict])
 703            # properties
 704            m_class.append(f"\tproperties\n")
 705            for var in m_properties:
 706                m_class.append(f"\t\t{str(var)}\n")
 707            # add cse subexpressions as private properties
 708            if self.subex_dict:
 709                m_class.append("\tend\n\n")
 710                m_class.append(f"\tproperties (Access = private)\n")
 711                for var in [i for i in sorted([str(j) for j in self.subex_dict], key=lambda x: int(regex.findall("(?<=sub)\d*",x)[0]))]:
 712                    m_class.append(f"\t\t{str(var)}\n")
 713                # add subex to m_properties list
 714                m_properties.extend([i for i in sorted([str(j) for j in self.subex_dict], key=lambda x: int(regex.findall("(?<=sub)\d*",x)[0]))])
 715            m_class.append("\tend\n\n")
 716            
 717            # methods
 718            m_class.append(f"\tmethods\n")
 719            
 720            # init function
 721            # function arguments
 722            var_substr = ", ".join(
 723                    [str(not_assigned_syms[i]) 
 724                     for i in range(len(not_assigned_syms))] 
 725                    + [str(j) for j in self.assignment_dict])
 726            m_class.append(f"\t\tfunction obj = {name}({var_substr})\n")
 727            
 728            # default values for not assigned variables
 729            if not_assigned_syms:
 730                m_class.append(f"\t\t\t% TODO: Assign missing variables here:\n")
 731                for var in not_assigned_syms:
 732                    if str(var) == "g":
 733                        m_class.append(f"\t\t\t% if ~exist('{str(var)}','var'); {str(var)} = 9.81; end\n")
 734                    else:
 735                        m_class.append(f"\t\t\t% if ~exist('{str(var)}','var'); {str(var)} = 0; end\n")
 736            # default values for assigned variables
 737            for var in self.assignment_dict:
 738                val = octave_code(self.assignment_dict[var])
 739                m_class.append(f"\t\t\tif ~exist('{str(var)}','var'); {str(var)} = {val}; end\n")
 740            m_class.append("")
 741            # save variables to parameters
 742            for var in not_assigned_syms:
 743                m_class.append(f"\t\t\tobj.{str(var)} = {str(var)};\n")
 744            for var in self.assignment_dict:
 745                m_class.append(f"\t\t\tobj.{str(var)} = {str(var)};\n")
 746            # calculate subexpressions
 747            for var in sorted([str(j) for j in self.subex_dict], key=lambda x: int(regex.findall("(?<=sub)\d*",x)[0])):
 748                val = regex.sub("(?<=\W|^)sub","obj.sub",octave_code(self.subex_dict[symbols(var)]))
 749                m_class.append(f"\t\t\tobj.{str(var)} = {val};\n")       
 750            m_class.append("\t\tend\n\n")
 751            
 752            # Add generated functions
 753            for i in range(len(expressions)):
 754                # generate function
 755                [(m_name, m_code)] = codegen(
 756                    (names[i], expressions[i]), "Octave", project=project, 
 757                    header=False, empty=True, 
 758                    argument_sequence=self._sort_variables(self.all_symbols)
 759                    )
 760                # remove already set variables
 761                m_func = m_code.splitlines(True)
 762                m_func = [f"\t\t{line}" for line in m_func]
 763                m_func[0] = m_func[0].replace("(","(obj, ")
 764                m_func[0] = regex.sub(
 765                    "(" + '|'.join([f', {str(v)}(?=\W)' for v in m_properties])+")",
 766                    "", m_func[0])
 767                # remove unused variable symbols
 768                m_func[0] = regex.sub(
 769                    "(" + '|'.join([f', {str(v)}(?=\W)' for v in self.var_syms.union(self.optional_var_syms).difference(expressions[i].free_symbols)])+")",
 770                    "", m_func[0])
 771                # use obj.variables defined in class parameters
 772                for i in range(1, len(m_func)):
 773                    m_func[i] = regex.sub(f"(?<=\W|^)(?=({'|'.join([str(s) for s in m_properties])})\W)","obj.",m_func[i])        
 774                m_func.append("\n")
 775                m_class.extend(m_func)
 776            
 777            m_class.append("\tend\n")
 778            m_class.append("end\n")
 779            with open(os.path.join(folder, "matlab", f"{name}.m"), "w+") as f:
 780                f.writelines(m_class)
 781        
 782        if latex:
 783            # create folder
 784            if not os.path.exists(os.path.join(folder, "latex")):
 785                os.mkdir(os.path.join(folder, "latex"))
 786
 787            # Document with `\maketitle` command activated
 788            doc = Document(documentclass="article", inputenc="utf8")
 789            if landscape:
 790                doc.packages.append(NoEscape(r"\usepackage[landscape,a4paper,top=2cm,bottom=2cm,left=2.5cm,right=2.5cm,marginparwidth=1.75cm]{geometry}"))
 791            else: 
 792                doc.packages.append(NoEscape(r"\usepackage[a4paper,top=2cm,bottom=2cm,left=2.5cm,right=2.5cm,marginparwidth=1.75cm]{geometry}"))
 793            doc.packages.append(NoEscape(r"\usepackage{amsmath}"))
 794            doc.packages.append(NoEscape(r"\usepackage{graphicx}"))
 795            doc.packages.append(NoEscape(r"\usepackage{breqn}[breakdepth={100}]"))
 796            
 797            doc.preamble.append(Command("title", "Equations of Motion"))
 798            doc.preamble.append(Command("author", "Author: SymbolicKinDyn"))
 799            doc.preamble.append(Command("date", NoEscape(r"\today")))
 800            doc.append(NoEscape(r"\maketitle"))
 801            doc.append(NoEscape(r"\tableofcontents"))
 802            doc.append(NoEscape(r"\newpage"))
 803            
 804            # create symbols and indices for equations
 805            for i in range(len(expressions)):
 806                letter = ""
 807                if "jacobian" in names[i]: letter = "J"
 808                elif "twist" in names[i]: letter = r"V"
 809                elif "kinematics" in names[i]: letter = r"^0T_E"
 810                elif "inertia" in names[i]: letter = "M"
 811                elif "coriolis" in names[i]: letter = "C"
 812                elif "gravity" in names[i]: letter = "g"
 813                elif "regressor" in names[i]: letter = "Y"
 814                elif "parameter_vector" in names[i]: letter = "X"
 815                elif "dynamics" in names[i]: letter = r"\tau"
 816                elif "acceleration" in names[i]: letter = r"\dot V"
 817                if "ddot" in names[i]: letter = r"\ddot "+letter
 818                elif "dot" in names[i]: letter = r"\dot "+letter
 819                if "_ee" in names[i]: letter = r"^E" + letter
 820                elif ("twist" in names[i] 
 821                      or "jacobian" in names[i] 
 822                      or "acceleration" in names[i]): letter = r"^0" + letter
 823                if "hybrid" in names[i]: letter += r"_h"
 824                elif "body" in names[i]: letter += r"_b"
 825                
 826                replacements = [("ddddq", r"\\ddddot q"),
 827                                ("ddddtheta", r"\\ddddot \\theta"),
 828                                ("dddq", r"\\dddot q"),
 829                                ("dddtheta", r"\\dddot \\theta"),
 830                                ("ddq", r"\\ddot q"), 
 831                                ("ddtheta", r"\\ddot \\theta"), 
 832                                ("dq", r"\\dot q"),
 833                                ("dtheta", r"\\dot \\theta")
 834                                ]
 835                with doc.create(Section(regex.sub("_"," ",names[i]))):
 836                    maxlen = 0
 837                    for row in range(expressions[i].shape[0]):
 838                        length = 0
 839                        for column in range(expressions[i].shape[1]):
 840                             length += len(regex.sub(r"(\\left|\\right|\{|\}|\\|_|\^|dot|ddot| |begin|matrix)","",str(expressions[i][row,column])))
 841                        maxlen = max(maxlen, length)
 842                    if maxlen < 120+int(landscape)*100:
 843                        eq = LatexPrinter().doprint(expressions[i])
 844                        for pat, repl in replacements:
 845                            eq = regex.sub(pat, repl, eq)
 846                        # doc.append(NoEscape(r"\begin{footnotesize}"))
 847                        doc.append(NoEscape(r"\[ \resizebox{\ifdim\width>\columnwidth\columnwidth\else\width\fi}{!}{$%"))
 848                        doc.append(NoEscape(r"\boldsymbol{"f"{letter}""} = "f"{eq}"))
 849                        doc.append(NoEscape(r"$} \]"))
 850                    else:
 851                        doc.append(NoEscape(r"\begin{dgroup*}"))
 852                        for row in range(expressions[i].shape[0]):
 853                            for column in range(expressions[i].shape[1]):
 854                                eq = LatexPrinter().doprint(expressions[i][row,column])
 855                                for pat, repl in replacements:
 856                                    eq = regex.sub(pat, repl, eq)
 857                                doc.append(NoEscape(r"\begin{dmath*}"))
 858                                doc.append(NoEscape(f"{letter}_"+"{"+f"{row+1}{','+str(column+1) if expressions[i].shape[1]>1 else ''}" + "}" + " = " + f"{eq}"))
 859                                doc.append(NoEscape(r"\end{dmath*}"))
 860                        doc.append(NoEscape(r"\end{dgroup*}"))
 861                        
 862                    # doc.append(NoEscape(r"\end{footnotesize}"))
 863                    # doc.append("\n")
 864            
 865            # save tex file and compile pdf
 866            doc.generate_pdf(os.path.join(folder, "latex",name), clean_tex=False)
 867    
 868    def generate_graph(self, path: str="output.pdf", include_mb: bool=False) -> None:
 869        """Write pdf graph from robot structure.
 870
 871        Args:
 872            path (str, optional): Path where to save graph. 
 873                Defaults to "output.pdf".
 874            include_mb (bool, optional): Include mass inertia matrix. 
 875                Defaults to False.
 876        """
 877        graph = pydot.Dot("Robot structure", graph_type="digraph")
 878        graph.add_node(pydot.Node("0_l", label="0 (base)", shape="box"))
 879        for i in range(len(self.parent) if self.parent else self.n):
 880            lab = "[[{}, {}, {}, {}], \l [{}, {}, {}, {}], \l [{}, {}, {}, {}], \l [{}, {}, {}, {}]]\l".format(
 881                *self.body_ref_config[i]
 882            )
 883            # joints
 884            vars = [str(x[i]) for x in [self.q,self.qd,self.q2d,self.q3d, self.q4d] if x]
 885            graph.add_node(pydot.Node(f"{i+1}",label="[{}, {}, {}, {}, {}, {}]{}"
 886                                      .format(*self.joint_screw_coord[i],"\n{"+", ".join(vars)+"}" if vars else ""), color="blue"))
 887            graph.add_edge(pydot.Edge(f"{self.parent[i] if self.parent else i}_l",f"{i+1}",
 888                                      label=lab))
 889            # links
 890            if include_mb:
 891                lab = (("[[{}, {}, {}, {}, {}, {}], \l [{}, {}, {}, {}, {}, {}], \l"
 892                        " [{}, {}, {}, {}, {}, {}], \l [{}, {}, {}, {}, {}, {}], \l"
 893                        " [{}, {}, {}, {}, {}, {}], \l [{}, {}, {}, {}, {}, {}]]\l")
 894                    .format(*self.Mb[i]))
 895            graph.add_node(pydot.Node(f"{i+1}_l",shape="box", label=f"{i+1}"+(":\n"+lab if include_mb else "")))
 896            graph.add_edge(pydot.Edge(f"{i+1}",f"{i+1}_l"))
 897        
 898        # end effector
 899        # set ee_parent if not already set
 900        self.ee_parent = self.ee_parent or (len(self.parent) if self.parent else self.n)
 901        if type(self.ee_parent) is list and len(self.parent)>1:
 902            for i in range(len(self.ee_parent)):
 903                # ee node with WEE, WDEE, and W2DEE label in case they are non zero
 904                lab = (f"ee_{i+1}"
 905                       # WEE
 906                       +"{}".format(
 907                           "\n[{}, {}, {}, {}, {}, {}]"
 908                           .format(*self.WEE[i] 
 909                                   if type(self.WEE) is list 
 910                                   else self.WEE)
 911                           if not self.WEE == zeros(6,1) 
 912                           and not (type(self.WEE) is list 
 913                                    and self.WEE[i] == zeros(6,1))
 914                           else "")
 915                       # WDEE
 916                       +"{}".format(
 917                           "\n[{}, {}, {}, {}, {}, {}]"
 918                           .format(*self.WDEE[i] 
 919                                   if type(self.WDEE) is list 
 920                                   else self.WDEE)
 921                           if not self.WDEE == zeros(6,1) 
 922                           and not (type(self.WDEE) is list 
 923                                    and self.WDEE[i] == zeros(6,1))
 924                           else "")
 925                       # W2DEE
 926                       +"{}".format(
 927                           "\n[{}, {}, {}, {}, {}, {}]"
 928                           .format(*self.W2DEE[i] 
 929                                   if type(self.W2DEE) is list 
 930                                   else self.W2DEE)
 931                           if not self.W2DEE == zeros(6,1) 
 932                           and not (type(self.W2DEE) is list 
 933                                    and self.W2DEE[i] == zeros(6,1))
 934                           else ""))
 935                graph.add_node(
 936                    pydot.Node(f"ee_{i+1}",  shape="plaintext", 
 937                              label=lab
 938                    )
 939                )
 940                lab = "[[{}, {}, {}, {}], \l [{}, {}, {}, {}], \l [{}, {}, {}, {}], \l [{}, {}, {}, {}]]\l".format(
 941                    *self.ee[i]
 942                )
 943                graph.add_edge(pydot.Edge(f"{self.ee_parent[i]}_l",f"ee_{i+1}", 
 944                                            label=lab))
 945        else:
 946            # ee node with WEE, WDEE, and W2DEE label in case they are non zero
 947            lab = (f"ee"
 948                   # WEE
 949                   +"{}".format(
 950                       "\n[{}, {}, {}, {}, {}, {}]"
 951                       .format(*self.WEE[0] 
 952                               if type(self.WEE) is list # decide wether [Matrix] or just Matrix
 953                               else self.WEE)
 954                       if not self.WEE == zeros(6,1) # only if non zero
 955                       and not (type(self.WEE) is list and self.WEE[0] == zeros(6,1)) # can be a list too...
 956                       else "")
 957                   # WDEE
 958                   +"{}".format(
 959                       "\n[{}, {}, {}, {}, {}, {}]"
 960                       .format(*self.WDEE[0] 
 961                               if type(self.WDEE) is list 
 962                               else self.WDEE)
 963                       if not self.WDEE == zeros(6,1) 
 964                       and not (type(self.WDEE) is list and self.WDEE[0] == zeros(6,1))
 965                       else "")
 966                   # W2DEE
 967                   +"{}".format(
 968                       "\n[{}, {}, {}, {}, {}, {}]"
 969                       .format(*self.W2DEE[0] 
 970                               if type(self.W2DEE) is list 
 971                               else self.W2DEE)
 972                       if not self.W2DEE == zeros(6,1) 
 973                       and not (type(self.W2DEE) is list and self.W2DEE[0] == zeros(6,1))
 974                       else ""))
 975            graph.add_node(
 976                pydot.Node(f"ee", shape="plaintext",
 977                           label=lab
 978                )
 979            )
 980            lab = "[[{}, {}, {}, {}], \l [{}, {}, {}, {}], \l [{}, {}, {}, {}], \l [{}, {}, {}, {}]]\l".format(
 981                    *self.ee[0] if type(self.ee) is list else self.ee
 982                )
 983            graph.add_edge(pydot.Edge(
 984                f"{self.ee_parent[0] if type(self.ee_parent) is list else self.ee_parent}_l",f"ee",
 985                label=lab
 986                ))
 987        graph.write_pdf(path)
 988        
 989    def _sort_variables(self, vars:list[sympy.Symbol]) -> list[sympy.Symbol]:
 990        """Sort variables for code generation starting with q, qd, qdd, 
 991        continuing with variable symbols (like fx in WEE) and ending 
 992        with constant symbols.
 993
 994        Args:
 995            vars (list of sympy.symbols): Variables to sort.
 996
 997        Returns:
 998            list: Sorted list of variables.
 999        """
1000        # vars as set
1001        vars = set(vars)
1002        # divide into variable and constant symbols
1003        var_syms = self.var_syms.intersection(vars)
1004        optional_var_syms = self.optional_var_syms.intersection(vars)
1005        rest = list(vars.difference(var_syms).difference(optional_var_syms))
1006        
1007        # function to sort symbols by name; returns list
1008        symsort = lambda data: [x for _, x in sorted(zip(list(map(str, data)), data))]
1009        
1010        sorted_syms = []
1011        # go through generalized vectors and sort variables according to their order
1012        for i in self.q:
1013            if i in var_syms:
1014                sorted_syms.append(i)
1015                var_syms.remove(i)
1016        for i in self.qd:
1017            if i in var_syms:
1018                sorted_syms.append(i)
1019                var_syms.remove(i)
1020        for i in self.q2d:
1021            if i in var_syms:
1022                sorted_syms.append(i)
1023                var_syms.remove(i)
1024        if self.q3d:
1025            for i in self.q3d:
1026                if i in var_syms:
1027                    sorted_syms.append(i)
1028                    var_syms.remove(i)
1029        if self.q4d:
1030            for i in self.q4d:
1031                if i in var_syms:
1032                    sorted_syms.append(i)
1033                    var_syms.remove(i)
1034        if var_syms:
1035            sorted_syms += symsort(var_syms)
1036        # now append symbols in external wrenches
1037        for i in self.WEE:
1038            if i in optional_var_syms:
1039                sorted_syms.append(i)
1040                optional_var_syms.remove(i)
1041        for i in self.WDEE:
1042            if i in optional_var_syms:
1043                sorted_syms.append(i)
1044                optional_var_syms.remove(i)
1045        for i in self.W2DEE:
1046            if i in optional_var_syms:
1047                sorted_syms.append(i)
1048                optional_var_syms.remove(i)
1049        if optional_var_syms:
1050            sorted_syms += symsort(optional_var_syms)
1051        # finally sort additional symbols by their name
1052        sorted_syms += symsort(rest)
1053        return sorted_syms
1054
1055class SymbolicKinDyn(_AbstractCodeGeneration):
1056    BODY_FIXED = "body_fixed"
1057    SPATIAL = "spatial"
1058    
1059    def __init__(self, 
1060                 gravity_vector: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix | list]=None, 
1061                 ee: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix | list[MutableDenseMatrix]]=None, 
1062                 body_ref_config: list[MutableDenseMatrix]=[], 
1063                 joint_screw_coord: list[MutableDenseMatrix]=[], 
1064                 config_representation: str="spatial", 
1065                 Mb: list[MutableDenseMatrix]=[], 
1066                 parent: list[int]=[], 
1067                 support: list[list[int]]=[], 
1068                 child: list[list[int]]=[], 
1069                 ee_parent: Optional[int | list[int]]=None,
1070                 q: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix]=None, 
1071                 qd: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix]=None, 
1072                 q2d: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix]=None, 
1073                 q3d: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix]=None, 
1074                 q4d: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix]=None, 
1075                 WEE: MutableDenseMatrix | list[MutableDenseMatrix]=zeros(6, 1),
1076                 WDEE: MutableDenseMatrix | list[MutableDenseMatrix]=zeros(6, 1),
1077                 W2DEE: MutableDenseMatrix | list[MutableDenseMatrix]=zeros(6, 1),
1078                 **kwargs) -> None:
1079        """SymbolicKinDyn
1080        Symbolic tool to compute equations of motion of serial chain 
1081        robots and autogenerate code from the calculated equations. 
1082        This tool supports generation of python, C and Matlab code.
1083
1084        Args:
1085            gravity_vector (sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1086                Vector of gravity. Defaults to None.
1087            ee (sympy.Matrix | list of sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1088                End-effector configuration with reference to last link 
1089                body fixed frame in the chain. This link can be selected 
1090                manually using the parameter ee_parent. 
1091                If there is more than one end-effector use a list of 
1092                transforms instead.
1093                Defaults to None.
1094            body_ref_config (list of sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1095                List of reference configurations of bodies in body-fixed
1096                or spatial representation, dependent on selected 
1097                config_representation. 
1098                Leave empty for dH Parameter usage (dhToScrewCoord(...)). 
1099                Defaults to [].
1100            joint_screw_coord (list of sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1101                List of joint screw coordinates in body-fixed 
1102                or spatial representation, dependent on selected 
1103                config_representation. 
1104                Leave empty for dH Parameter usage (dhToScrewCoord(...)). 
1105                Defaults to [].
1106            config_representation (str, optional): 
1107                Use body fixed or spatial representation for reference 
1108                configuration of bodies and joint screw coordinates.
1109                Has to be "body_fixed" or "spatial". 
1110                Defaults to "spatial".
1111            Mb (list of sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1112                List of Mass Inertia matrices for all links. Only 
1113                necessary for inverse dynamics. Defaults to [].
1114            parent (list, optional): 
1115                list of parent link indices for any joint. Use 0 for world.
1116                Only necessary for tree-like robot structures. 
1117                Defaults to [].
1118            support (list, optional): 
1119                list of lists with one list per link which includes all 
1120                support links beginning with the first link in the chain 
1121                and including the current link.
1122                Only necessary for tree-like robot structures. 
1123                Defaults to [].
1124            child (list, optional): 
1125                list of lists with one list per link which includes all
1126                child links. Use empty list if no child link is present.
1127                Only necessary for tree-like robot structures. 
1128                Defaults to [].
1129            ee_parent (int | list, optional): 
1130                parent link of the end effector frame. If there is more 
1131                than one end-effector, use a list of indices instead.
1132                Defaults to None (= last link).
1133            q (sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1134                (n,1) Generalized position vector. Defaults to None.
1135            qd (sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1136                (n,1) Generalized velocity vector. Defaults to None.
1137            q2d (sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1138                (n,1) Generalized acceleration vector. Defaults to None.
1139            q3d (sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1140                (n,1) Generalized jerk vector. Defaults to None.
1141            q4d (sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1142                (n,1) Generalized jounce vector. Defaults to None.
1143            WEE (sympy.Matrix | list, optional): 
1144                (6,1) WEE (t) = [Mx,My,Mz,Fx,Fy,Fz] is the time varying 
1145                wrench on the EE link. 
1146                If there is more than one end-effector, you can use a 
1147                list containing all wrenches instead.
1148                Defaults to zeros(6, 1).
1149            WDEE (sympy.Matrix | list, optional): 
1150                (6,1) WDEE (t) = [dMx,dMy,dMz,dFx,dFy,dFz] is the derivative 
1151                of the time varying wrench on the EE link. 
1152                If there is more than one end-effector, you can use a 
1153                list containing all wrenches instead.
1154                Defaults to zeros(6, 1).
1155            W2DEE (sympy.Matrix | list, optional): 
1156                (6,1) W2DEE (t) = [ddMx,ddMy,ddMz,ddFx,ddFy,ddFz] is the 
1157                2nd derivative of the time varying wrench on the EE link. 
1158                If there is more than one end-effector, you can use a 
1159                list containing all wrenches instead.
1160                Defaults to zeros(6, 1).
1161            
1162        """
1163        super().__init__()
1164        self.n = None  # degrees of freedom
1165        self.gravity_vector = gravity_vector
1166        self.ee = ee
1167
1168        self.B = [] # List of reference configurations of bodies in body-fixed representation.
1169        self.X = [] # List of joint screw coordinates in body-fixed representation.
1170
1171        self.A = [] # List of reference configurations of bodies in spatial representation.
1172        self.Y = [] # List of joint screw coordinates in spatial representation.
1173        
1174        self.config_representation = config_representation # @property: checks for valid value 
1175        if body_ref_config != []:
1176            self.body_ref_config = body_ref_config # @property: sets A or B
1177        if joint_screw_coord != []:
1178            self.joint_screw_coord = joint_screw_coord # @property: sets X or Y
1179        # support of old syntax
1180        if "A" in kwargs:
1181            self.A = kwargs["A"]
1182            n = len(self.A)
1183            if n:
1184                self.n = n
1185        if "B" in kwargs:
1186            self.B = kwargs["B"]
1187            n = len(self.B)
1188            if n:
1189                self.n = n
1190        if "X" in kwargs:
1191            self.X = kwargs["X"]
1192        if "Y" in kwargs:
1193            self.Y = kwargs["Y"]
1194
1195            
1196        self.Mb = Mb
1197        self.parent = parent
1198        self.child = child
1199        self.support = support
1200        
1201        # costom ee link
1202        self.ee_parent = ee_parent
1203        
1204        # temporary vars
1205        self._FK_C = None
1206        self._A = None
1207        self._a = None
1208        self._V = None  # system twist
1209
1210        
1211        # Multiprocessing
1212        # dict of queues, which saves values and results
1213        self.queue_dict = {}  
1214        # dict of running processes
1215        self.process_dict = {}  
1216        
1217        # generalized vectors end external forces
1218        self.q = q
1219        self.qd = qd
1220        self.q2d = q2d
1221        self.q3d = q3d
1222        self.q4d = q4d
1223        self.WEE = WEE
1224        self.WDEE = WDEE
1225        self.W2DEE = W2DEE
1226
1227        
1228    @property
1229    def config_representation(self) -> str:
1230        return self._config_representation
1231    
1232    @config_representation.setter
1233    def config_representation(self, value: str) -> None:
1234        if value not in {self.BODY_FIXED, self.SPATIAL}:
1235            raise ValueError("config_representation has to be 'body_fixed' or 'spatial'")
1236        self._config_representation = value
1237    
1238    @property
1239    def body_ref_config(self) -> list:
1240        if self.config_representation == self.BODY_FIXED:
1241            return self.B
1242        elif self.config_representation == self.SPATIAL:
1243            return self.A
1244    
1245    @body_ref_config.setter
1246    def body_ref_config(self, value: list[MutableDenseMatrix]) -> None:
1247        n = len(value)
1248        if n:
1249            self.n = n
1250        if self.config_representation == self.BODY_FIXED:
1251            self.B = value
1252        elif self.config_representation == self.SPATIAL:
1253            self.A = value
1254    
1255    @property
1256    def joint_screw_coord(self) -> list:
1257        if self.config_representation == self.BODY_FIXED:
1258            return self.X
1259        elif self.config_representation == self.SPATIAL:
1260            return self.Y
1261    
1262    @joint_screw_coord.setter
1263    def joint_screw_coord(self, value: list[MutableDenseMatrix]) -> None:
1264        if self.config_representation == self.BODY_FIXED:
1265            self.X = value
1266        elif self.config_representation == self.SPATIAL:
1267            self.Y = value
1268    
1269    def closed_form_kinematics_body_fixed(
1270        self, 
1271        q: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix]=None, 
1272        qd: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix]=None, 
1273        q2d: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix]=None, 
1274        simplify: bool=True, 
1275        cse: bool=False, 
1276        parallel: bool=True) -> MutableDenseMatrix:
1277        """Position, Velocity and Acceleration Kinematics using Body 
1278        fixed representation of the twists in closed form.
1279
1280        The following expressions are saved in the class and can be 
1281        code generated afterwards:
1282        
1283            body_acceleration
1284            body_acceleration_ee
1285            body_jacobian_matrix
1286            body_jacobian_matrix_dot 
1287            body_jacobian_matrix_ee
1288            body_jacobian_matrix_ee_dot
1289            body_twist_ee
1290            forward_kinematics
1291            hybrid_acceleration
1292            hybrid_acceleration_ee
1293            hybrid_jacobian_matrix
1294            hybrid_jacobian_matrix_dot
1295            hybrid_jacobian_matrix_ee
1296            hybrid_jacobian_matrix_ee_dot
1297            hybrid_twist_ee
1298
1299        Needs class parameters body_ref_config, joint_screw_coord and ee 
1300        to be defined.
1301
1302        Args:
1303            q (sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1304                (n,1) Generalized position vector. Defaults to None.
1305            qd (sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1306                (n,1) Generalized velocity vector. Defaults to None.
1307            q2d (sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1308                (n,1) Generalized acceleration vector. Defaults to None.
1309            simplify (bool, optional): 
1310                Use simplify command on saved expressions. 
1311                Defaults to True.
1312            cse (bool, optional): 
1313                Use common subexpression elimination. Defaults to False.
1314            parallel (bool, optional): 
1315                Use parallel computation via multiprocessing. 
1316                Defaults to True.
1317        Raises:
1318            ValueError:
1319                Joint screw coordinates and/or reference configuration 
1320                of bodies not set.
1321                
1322        Returns:
1323            sympy.Matrix: Forward kinematics.
1324        """
1325        if not q or not qd or not q2d:
1326            if not self.n:
1327                self.n = len(self.body_ref_config)
1328            if not self.q or not self.qd or not self.q2d:
1329                print(self.q, self.qd, self.q2d)
1330                q, qd, q2d = generalized_vectors(self.n,self._find_start_index())
1331            else:
1332                q, qd, q2d = self.q, self.qd, self.q2d
1333                
1334        self._save_vectors(q, qd, q2d, None, None, ..., ..., ...)
1335        self.n = len(q)
1336        
1337        # prepare ee link selection
1338        if self.ee_parent is None:
1339            self.ee_parent = [self.n]
1340        if type(self.ee) is not list: self.ee = [self.ee]
1341        if type(self.ee_parent) is not list: self.ee_parent = [self.ee_parent]
1342        assert(len(self.ee) == len(self.ee_parent))    
1343        self.n_ee = len(self.ee_parent)
1344        
1345        if parallel:
1346            self._closed_form_kinematics_body_fixed_parallel(
1347                q, qd, q2d, simplify, cse)
1348        else:
1349            self._closed_form_kinematics_body_fixed(
1350                q, qd, q2d, simplify, cse)
1351        return self.fkin
1352
1353    def closed_form_inv_dyn_body_fixed(
1354        self, 
1355        q: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix]=None, 
1356        qd: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix]=None, 
1357        q2d: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix]=None, 
1358        q3d: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix]=None, 
1359        q4d: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix]=None, 
1360        WEE: MutableDenseMatrix | list[MutableDenseMatrix]=..., 
1361        WDEE: MutableDenseMatrix | list[MutableDenseMatrix]=..., 
1362        W2DEE: MutableDenseMatrix | list[MutableDenseMatrix]=..., 
1363        simplify: bool=True, cse: bool=False, 
1364        parallel: bool=True) -> MutableDenseMatrix:
1365        """Inverse dynamics using body fixed representation of the 
1366        twists in closed form. 
1367
1368        The following expressions are saved in the class and can be 
1369        code generated afterwards:
1370            coriolis_centrifugal_matrix
1371            generalized_mass_inertia_matrix
1372            gravity_vector
1373            inverse_dynamics
1374
1375        Args:
1376            q (sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1377                (n,1) Generalized position vector. Defaults to None.
1378            qd (sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1379                (n,1) Generalized velocity vector. Defaults to None.
1380            q2d (sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1381                (n,1) Generalized acceleration vector. Defaults to None.
1382            q3d (sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1383                (n,1) Generalized jerk vector. Defaults to None.
1384            q4d (sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1385                (n,1) Generalized jounce vector. Defaults to None.
1386            WEE (list | sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1387                (6,1) WEE (t) = [Mx,My,Mz,Fx,Fy,Fz] is the time varying 
1388                wrench on the EE link. 
1389                If there is more than one end-effector, you can use a 
1390                list containing all wrenches instead.
1391                Defaults to zeros(6, 1).
1392            WDEE (list | sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1393                (6,1) WDEE (t) = [dMx,dMy,dMz,dFx,dFy,dFz] is the derivative 
1394                of the time varying wrench on the EE link. 
1395                If there is more than one end-effector, you can use a 
1396                list containing all wrenches instead.
1397                Defaults to zeros(6, 1).
1398            W2DEE (list | sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1399                (6,1) W2DEE (t) = [ddMx,ddMy,ddMz,ddFx,ddFy,ddFz] is the 
1400                2nd derivative of the time varying wrench on the EE link. 
1401                If there is more than one end-effector, you can use a 
1402                list containing all wrenches instead.
1403                Defaults to zeros(6, 1).
1404            simplify (bool, optional): 
1405                Use simplify command on saved expressions. 
1406                Defaults to True.
1407            cse (bool, optional): 
1408                Use common subexpression elimination. Defaults to False.
1409            parallel (bool, optional): 
1410                Use parallel computation via multiprocessing. 
1411                Defaults to True.
1412
1413        Raises:
1414            ValueError:
1415                Joint screw coordinates and/or reference configuration 
1416                of bodies not set.
1417        
1418        Returns:
1419            sympy.Matrix: Generalized forces
1420        """
1421        if not q or not qd or not q2d:
1422            if not self.n:
1423                self.n = len(self.body_ref_config)
1424            if not self.q or not self.qd or not self.q2d:
1425                q, qd, q2d = generalized_vectors(self.n,self._find_start_index())
1426            else:
1427                q, qd, q2d, q3d, q4d = self.q, self.qd, self.q2d, self.q3d, self.q4d
1428        
1429        if WEE is Ellipsis:
1430            WEE = self.WEE
1431        if WDEE is Ellipsis:
1432            WDEE = self.WDEE
1433        if W2DEE is Ellipsis:
1434            W2DEE = self.W2DEE
1435        
1436        self._save_vectors(q, qd, q2d, q3d, q4d, WEE, WDEE, W2DEE)
1437        self.n = len(q)
1438        
1439        # prepare ee link selection
1440        if self.ee_parent is None:
1441            self.ee_parent = [self.n]
1442        if type(self.ee_parent) is not list: self.ee_parent = [self.ee_parent]
1443        self.n_ee = len(self.ee_parent)
1444        if self.n_ee > 1:
1445            if type(WEE) is list and len(WEE) > 1:
1446                assert(len(WEE) == len(self.ee_parent))
1447            if type(WDEE) is list and len(WDEE) > 1:
1448                assert(len(WDEE) == len(self.ee_parent))
1449            if type(W2DEE) is list and len(W2DEE) > 1:
1450                assert(len(W2DEE) == len(self.ee_parent)) 
1451        if type(WEE) is not list: WEE = [WEE]
1452        if type(WDEE) is not list: WDEE = [WDEE]
1453        if type(W2DEE) is not list: W2DEE = [W2DEE]
1454        
1455        if parallel:
1456            self._closed_form_inv_dyn_body_fixed_parallel(
1457                q, qd, q2d, q3d, q4d, WEE, WDEE, W2DEE, simplify, cse)
1458        else:
1459            self._closed_form_inv_dyn_body_fixed(
1460                q, qd, q2d, q3d, q4d, WEE, WDEE, W2DEE, simplify, cse)
1461        return self.Q
1462
1463    def _closed_form_kinematics_body_fixed(
1464        self, q: MutableDenseMatrix, qd: MutableDenseMatrix, 
1465        q2d: MutableDenseMatrix, simplify: bool=True, 
1466        cse: bool=False) -> MutableDenseMatrix:
1467        """Position, velocity and acceleration kinematics using 
1468        body fixed representation of the twists in closed form.
1469
1470        The following expressions are saved in the class and can be 
1471        code generated afterwards:
1472            body_acceleration
1473            body_acceleration_ee
1474            body_jacobian_matrix
1475            body_jacobian_matrix_dot 
1476            body_jacobian_matrix_ee
1477            body_jacobian_matrix_ee_dot
1478            body_twist_ee
1479            forward_kinematics
1480            hybrid_acceleration
1481            hybrid_acceleration_ee
1482            hybrid_jacobian_matrix
1483            hybrid_jacobian_matrix_dot
1484            hybrid_jacobian_matrix_ee
1485            hybrid_jacobian_matrix_ee_dot
1486            hybrid_twist_ee
1487
1488            Needs class parameters body_ref_config, joint_screw_coord 
1489            and ee to be defined.
1490
1491        Args:
1492            q (sympy.Matrix): 
1493                (n,1) Generalized position vector.
1494            qd (sympy.Matrix): 
1495                (n,1) Generalized velocity vector.
1496            q2d (sympy.Matrix): 
1497                (n,1) Generalized acceleration vector.
1498            simplify (bool, optional): 
1499                Use simplify command on saved expressions. 
1500                Defaults to True.
1501            cse (bool, optional): 
1502                Use common subexpression elimination. Defaults to False.
1503
1504
1505        Returns:
1506            sympy.Matrix: Forward kinematics.
1507        """
1508        print("Forward kinematics calculation")
1509        self.var_syms.update(q.free_symbols)
1510        self.var_syms.update(qd.free_symbols)
1511        self.var_syms.update(q2d.free_symbols)
1512
1513        self.n = len(q)  # DOF
1514
1515        # calc Forward kinematics
1516        if self.parent and self.support:
1517            FK_C, A = self._calc_A_matrix_tree(q)
1518        else:    
1519            FK_C, A = self._calc_A_matrix(q)
1520        
1521        fkin = [None]*self.n_ee
1522        for i in range(self.n_ee):
1523            fkin[i] = FK_C[self.ee_parent[i]-1]*self.ee[i]
1524            fkin[i] = self.simplify(fkin[i], cse, simplify)    
1525        self.fkin = fkin if len(fkin)>1 else fkin[0]
1526        
1527        if self.J is not None:
1528            J = self.J
1529            V = self._V
1530        else:
1531            # Block diagonal matrix X (6n x n) of the screw coordinate 
1532            # vector associated to all joints in the body frame (Constant)
1533            X = zeros(6*self.n, self.n)
1534            for i in range(self.n):
1535                X[6*i:6*i+6, i] = self.X[i]
1536
1537            # System level Jacobian
1538            J = A*X
1539            J = self.simplify(J, cse, simplify)
1540            self.J = J
1541
1542            # System twist (6n x 1)
1543            V = J*qd
1544            self._V = V
1545
1546        R_i = [None]*self.n_ee
1547        R_BFn = [None]*self.n_ee
1548        Vb_BFn = [None]*self.n_ee
1549        Vh_BFn = [None]*self.n_ee
1550        Vb_ee = [None]*self.n_ee
1551        Vh_ee = [None]*self.n_ee
1552        Jh_ee = [None]*self.n_ee
1553        Jb_ee = [None]*self.n_ee
1554        Jh = [None]*self.n_ee
1555        Jb = [None]*self.n_ee
1556        for i in range(self.n_ee):
1557            # Different Jacobians
1558            R_i[i] = Matrix(fkin[i][:3, :3]).row_join(
1559                zeros(3, 1)).col_join(Matrix([0, 0, 0, 1]).T)
1560            R_i[i] = self.simplify(R_i[i], cse, simplify)
1561            
1562            R_BFn[i] = Matrix(FK_C[self.ee_parent[i]-1][:3, :3]).row_join(
1563                zeros(3, 1)).col_join(Matrix([0, 0, 0, 1]).T)
1564
1565            # Body fixed Jacobian of last moving body 
1566            # (This may not correspond to end-effector frame)
1567            Jb[i] = J[6*(self.ee_parent[i]-1):6*self.ee_parent[i], :] # used to be [-6:,:]
1568            Jb[i] = self.simplify(Jb[i], cse, simplify)
1569            
1570            Vb_BFn[i] = Jb[i]*qd  # Body fixed twist of last moving body
1571            Vb_BFn[i] = self.simplify(Vb_BFn[i], cse, simplify)
1572            
1573            Vh_BFn[i] = SE3AdjMatrix(R_BFn[i])*Vb_BFn[i]
1574            Vh_BFn[i] = self.simplify(Vh_BFn[i], cse, simplify)
1575            
1576            # Body fixed twist of end-effector frame
1577            Vb_ee[i] = SE3AdjMatrix(SE3Inv(self.ee[i]))*Vb_BFn[i]
1578            Vb_ee[i] = self.simplify(Vb_ee[i], cse, simplify)
1579            
1580            # Hybrid twist of end-effector frame
1581            Vh_ee[i] = SE3AdjMatrix(R_i[i])*Vb_ee[i]
1582            Vh_ee[i] = self.simplify(Vh_ee[i], cse, simplify)
1583            
1584            # Body fixed Jacobian of end-effector frame
1585            Jb_ee[i] = SE3AdjMatrix(SE3Inv(self.ee[i]))*Jb[i]
1586            Jb_ee[i] = self.simplify(Jb_ee[i], cse, simplify)
1587            
1588            # Hybrid Jacobian of end-effector frame
1589            Jh_ee[i] = SE3AdjMatrix(R_i[i])*Jb_ee[i]
1590            # Hybrid Jacobian of last moving body
1591            Jh[i] = SE3AdjMatrix(R_i[i])*Jb[i]  
1592
1593            Jh_ee[i] = self.simplify(Jh_ee[i], cse, simplify)
1594            Jh[i] = self.simplify(Jh[i], cse, simplify)
1595            
1596        self.Vb_BFn = Vb_BFn if len(Vb_BFn)>1 else Vb_BFn[0]
1597        self.Vh_BFn = Vh_BFn if len(Vh_BFn)>1 else Vh_BFn[0]
1598        self.Vb_ee = Vb_ee if len(Vb_ee)>1 else Vb_ee[0]
1599        self.Vh_ee = Vh_ee if len(Vh_ee)>1 else Vh_ee[0]
1600        self.Jh_ee = Jh_ee if len(Jh_ee)>1 else Jh_ee[0]
1601        self.Jb_ee = Jb_ee if len(Jb_ee)>1 else Jb_ee[0]
1602        self.Jh = Jh if len(Jh)>1 else Jh[0]
1603        self.Jb = Jb if len(Jb)>1 else Jb[0]
1604        
1605        # Acceleration computations
1606        if self._a is not None:
1607            a = self._a
1608        else:
1609            # Block diagonal matrix a (6n x 6n)
1610            a = zeros(6*self.n, 6*self.n)
1611            for i in range(self.n):
1612                a[6*i:6*i+6, 6*i:6*i+6] = SE3adMatrix(self.X[i])*qd[i]
1613            a = self.simplify(a, cse, simplify)
1614            self._a = a
1615
1616        # System acceleration (6n x 1)
1617        Jdot = -A*a*J  # Sys-level Jacobian time derivative
1618        Jdot = self.simplify(Jdot, cse, simplify)
1619        
1620        self.Jdot = Jdot
1621
1622        Vbd = J*q2d - A*a*V
1623
1624        Vbd_BFn = [None]*self.n_ee
1625        Vhd_BFn = [None]*self.n_ee
1626        Vbd_ee = [None]*self.n_ee
1627        Vhd_ee = [None]*self.n_ee
1628        Jb_dot = [None]*self.n_ee
1629        Jb_ee_dot = [None]*self.n_ee
1630        Jh_dot = [None]*self.n_ee
1631        Jh_ee_dot = [None]*self.n_ee
1632        for i in range(self.n_ee):
