1633            # Hybrid acceleration of the last body
1634            Vbd_BFn[i] = Vbd[6*(self.ee_parent[i]-1):6*self.ee_parent[i], :] # used to be [-6:,:]
1635            Vbd_BFn[i] = self.simplify(Vbd_BFn[i], cse, simplify)
1636            
1637            # Hybrid twist of end-effector frame 
1638            # TODO: check comments
1639            Vhd_BFn[i] = (SE3AdjMatrix(R_BFn[i])*Vbd_BFn[i] 
1640                    + SE3adMatrix(Matrix(Vh_BFn[i][:3, :])
1641                                        .col_join(Matrix([0, 0, 0])))
1642                    * SE3AdjMatrix(R_BFn[i])*Vb_BFn[i])  
1643
1644            Vhd_BFn[i] = self.simplify(Vhd_BFn[i], cse, simplify)
1645            
1646            # Body fixed twist of end-effector frame
1647            # Hybrid acceleration of the EE
1648            Vbd_ee[i] = SE3AdjMatrix(SE3Inv(self.ee[i]))*Vbd_BFn[i]
1649            Vbd_ee[i] = self.simplify(Vbd_ee[i], cse, simplify)
1650            
1651            # Hybrid twist of end-effector frame
1652            Vhd_ee[i] = SE3AdjMatrix(R_i[i])*Vbd_ee[i] + SE3adMatrix(Matrix(
1653                Vh_ee[i][:3, :]).col_join(Matrix([0, 0, 0])))*\
1654                    SE3AdjMatrix(R_i[i])*Vb_ee[i]  
1655            Vhd_ee[i] = self.simplify(Vhd_ee[i], cse, simplify)
1656            
1657            # Body Jacobian time derivative
1658
1659            # For the last moving body
1660            Jb_dot[i] = Jdot[6*(self.ee_parent[i]-1):6*self.ee_parent[i], :] # used to be [-6:,:]
1661
1662            # For the EE
1663            Jb_ee_dot[i] = SE3AdjMatrix(SE3Inv(self.ee[i]))*Jb_dot[i]
1664            Jb_ee_dot[i] = self.simplify(Jb_ee_dot[i], cse, simplify)
1665            
1666            # Hybrid Jacobian time derivative
1667            # For the last moving body
1668            Jh_dot[i] = (SE3AdjMatrix(R_BFn[i])*Jb_dot[i] 
1669                    + SE3adMatrix(Matrix(Vh_BFn[i][:3, :]).col_join(Matrix([0, 0, 0])))
1670                    *SE3AdjMatrix(R_BFn[i])*Jb[i])
1671            Jh_dot[i] = self.simplify(Jh_dot[i], cse, simplify)
1672            
1673            # For the EE
1674            Jh_ee_dot[i] = (SE3AdjMatrix(R_i[i])*Jb_ee_dot[i] 
1675                        + SE3adMatrix(Matrix(Vh_ee[i][:3, :]).col_join(Matrix([0, 0, 0])))
1676                        * SE3AdjMatrix(R_i[i])*Jb_ee[i])
1677            Jh_ee_dot[i] = self.simplify(Jh_ee_dot[i], cse, simplify)
1678            
1679        self.Vbd_BFn = Vbd_BFn if len(Vbd_BFn)>1 else Vbd_BFn[0]
1680        self.Vhd_BFn = Vhd_BFn if len(Vhd_BFn)>1 else Vhd_BFn[0]
1681        self.Vbd_ee = Vbd_ee if len(Vbd_ee)>1 else Vbd_ee[0]
1682        self.Vhd_ee = Vhd_ee if len(Vhd_ee)>1 else Vhd_ee[0]
1683        self.Jb_dot = Jb_dot if len(Jb_dot)>1 else Jb_dot[0]
1684        self.Jb_ee_dot = Jb_ee_dot if len(Jb_ee_dot)>1 else Jb_ee_dot[0]
1685        self.Jh_dot = Jh_dot if len(Jh_dot)>1 else Jh_dot[0]
1686        self.Jh_ee_dot = Jh_ee_dot if len(Jh_ee_dot)>1 else Jh_ee_dot[0]
1687
1688        for e in self._get_expressions():
1689            self.all_symbols.update(e.free_symbols)
1690
1691        print("Done")
1692        return fkin
1693
1694    def _closed_form_inv_dyn_body_fixed(self, q: MutableDenseMatrix, 
1695                                        qd: MutableDenseMatrix, 
1696                                        q2d: MutableDenseMatrix,
1697                                        q3d: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix]=None, 
1698                                        q4d: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix]=None, 
1699                                        WEE: list[MutableDenseMatrix]=[zeros(6, 1)], 
1700                                        WDEE: list[MutableDenseMatrix]=[zeros(6, 1)], 
1701                                        W2DEE: list[MutableDenseMatrix]=[zeros(6, 1)], 
1702                                        simplify: bool=True, 
1703                                        cse: bool=False) -> MutableDenseMatrix:
1704        """Inverse dynamics using body fixed representation of the 
1705        twists in closed form. 
1706
1707        The following expressions are saved in the class and can be code 
1708        generated afterwards:
1709            coriolis_centrifugal_matrix
1710            generalized_mass_inertia_matrix
1711            gravity_vector
1712            inverse_dynamics
1713
1714        Args:
1715            q (sympy.Matrix): (n,1) Generalized position vector.
1716            qd (sympy.Matrix): (n,1 )Generalized velocity vector.
1717            q2d (sympy.Matrix): (n,1) Generalized acceleration vector.
1718            q3d (sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1719                (n,1) Generalized jerk vector. Defaults to None.
1720            q4d (sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1721                (n,1) Generalized jounce vector. Defaults to None.
1722            WEE (list of sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1723                (6,1) WEE (t) = [Mx,My,Mz,Fx,Fy,Fz] is the time varying 
1724                wrench on the EE link. 
1725                Defaults to [zeros(6, 1)].
1726            WDEE (list of sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1727                (6,1) WDEE (t) = [dMx,dMy,dMz,dFx,dFy,dFz] is the derivative 
1728                of the time varying wrench on the EE link. 
1729                Defaults to [zeros(6, 1)].
1730            W2DEE (list of sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1731                (6,1) W2DEE (t) = [ddMx,ddMy,ddMz,ddFx,ddFy,ddFz] is the 
1732                2nd derivative of the time varying wrench on the EE link. 
1733                Defaults to [zeros(6, 1)].
1734            simplify (bool, optional): Use simplify command 
1735                on saved expressions. Defaults to True.
1736            cse (bool, optional): Use common subexpression 
1737                elimination. Defaults to False.
1738
1739        Returns:
1740            sympy.Matrix: Generalized forces
1741        """
1742        print("Inverse dynamics calculation")
1743
1744        self.var_syms.update(q.free_symbols)
1745        self.var_syms.update(qd.free_symbols)
1746        self.var_syms.update(q2d.free_symbols)
1747        if q3d: self.var_syms.update(q3d.free_symbols)
1748        if q4d: self.var_syms.update(q4d.free_symbols)
1749        for W in WEE:
1750            self.optional_var_syms.update(W.free_symbols)
1751        for WD in WDEE:
1752            self.optional_var_syms.update(WD.free_symbols)
1753        for W2D in W2DEE:
1754            self.optional_var_syms.update(W2D.free_symbols)
1755
1756        self.n = len(q)
1757
1758        # calc Forward kinematics
1759        if self.parent and self.support:
1760            FK_C, A = self._calc_A_matrix_tree(q)
1761        else:    
1762            FK_C, A = self._calc_A_matrix(q)
1763        
1764        if self.J is not None:
1765            J = self.J  # system level Jacobian
1766            V = self._V  # system twist
1767        else:
1768            # Block diagonal matrix X (6n x n) of the screw coordinate 
1769            # vector associated to all joints in the body frame (constant)
1770            X = zeros(6*self.n, self.n)
1771            for i in range(self.n):
1772                X[6*i:6*i+6, i] = self.X[i]
1773
1774            # System level Jacobian
1775            J = A*X
1776            J = self.simplify(J, cse, simplify)
1777            self.J = J
1778
1779            # System twist (6n x 1)
1780            V = J*qd
1781            self._V = V
1782
1783        # Acceleration computations
1784        if self._a is not None:
1785            a = self._a
1786        else:
1787            # Block diagonal matrix a (6n x 6n)
1788            a = zeros(6*self.n, 6*self.n)
1789            for i in range(self.n):
1790                a[6*i:6*i+6, 6*i:6*i+6] = SE3adMatrix(self.X[i])*qd[i]
1791            self._a = a
1792
1793        # System acceleration (6n x 1)
1794        Vd = J*q2d - A*a*V
1795
1796        # Block Diagonal Mb (6n x 6n) Mass inertia matrix in body frame 
1797        # (constant)
1798        Mb = zeros(6*self.n, 6*self.n)
1799        for i in range(self.n):
1800            Mb[i*6:i*6+6, i*6:i*6+6] = self.Mb[i]
1801
1802        # Block diagonal matrix b (6n x 6n) used in Coriolis matrix
1803        b = zeros(6*self.n, 6*self.n)
1804        for i in range(self.n):
1805            b[i*6:i*6+6, i*6:i*6+6] = SE3adMatrix(Matrix(V[6*i:6*i+6]))
1806
1807        # Block diagonal matrix Cb (6n x 6n)
1808        Cb = -Mb*A*a - b.T * Mb
1809
1810        # Lets setup the Equations of Motion
1811
1812        # Mass inertia matrix in joint space (n x n)
1813        M = J.T*Mb*J
1814        M = self.simplify(M, cse, simplify)
1815        
1816        # Coriolis-Centrifugal matrix in joint space (n x n)
1817        C = J.T * Cb * J
1818        C = self.simplify(C, cse, simplify)
1819        
1820        # Gravity Term
1821        U = SE3AdjInvMatrix(FK_C[0])
1822        for k in range(1, self.n):
1823            U = U.col_join(SE3AdjInvMatrix(FK_C[k]))
1824
1825        Vd_0 = zeros(6, 1)
1826        Vd_0[3:6, 0] = -Matrix(self.gravity_vector)
1827        Qgrav = J.T*Mb*U*Vd_0
1828        Qgrav = self.simplify(Qgrav, cse, simplify)
1829        
1830        # External Wrench
1831        Wext = zeros(6*self.n, 1)
1832        # WEE (t) is the time varying wrench on the EE link.
1833        for i in range(self.n_ee):
1834            Wext[6*(self.ee_parent[i]-1):6*self.ee_parent[i], 0] = WEE[i if len(WEE) == self.n_ee else 0]
1835        Qext = J.T * Wext
1836
1837        # Generalized forces Q
1838        # Q = M*q2d + C*qd   # without gravity
1839        Q = M*q2d + C*qd + Qgrav + Qext
1840        Q = self.simplify(Q, cse, simplify)
1841        
1842        self.M = M
1843        self.C = C
1844        self.Q = Q
1845        self.Qgrav = Qgrav
1846        
1847        # Regressor matrix for standard inertial parameter identification, Q = Y*X in SE(3)
1848        # mass-inertia parameter vector X         
1849        # m, m*c, m*cy, m*cz, Ixx, Ixy, Ixz, Iyy, Iyz, Izz        
1850        Xr = Matrix([value for i in self.Mb for value in mass_matrix_to_parameter_vector(i)])
1851        # dont calculate with numeric values
1852        if not any([i.is_Float for i in Xr]):
1853            S = Matrix(Identity(len(Xr)))
1854            # Regressor matrix Y   
1855            Yr = zeros(self.n, len(Xr))
1856            for i in range(self.n):
1857                for j in range(len(Xr)):                        
1858                    Yr[i,j] = self.collect_and_subs(Q[i], {k: v for k, v in zip(Xr, S[j,:]) if k not in {0,1}})
1859            Yr = self.simplify(Yr, cse, simplify)
1860            
1861            self.Xr = Xr
1862            self.Yr = Yr
1863
1864        ##### First Order Derivatives of EOM #####
1865        if q3d is not None:        
1866            # First time derivative of Block diagonal matrix a (6n x 6n)
1867            ad = zeros(6*self.n, 6*self.n)
1868            for i in range(self.n):
1869                ad[i*6:i*6+6, i*6:i*6+6] = q2d[i] * SE3adMatrix(self.X[i])
1870
1871            # Third order Forward Kinematics
1872            V2d = J*q3d - A*ad*V - 2*A*a*Vd - A*a*a*V
1873                        
1874            #  First time derivative of Block diagonal matrix b (6n x 6n) 
1875            # used in Coriolis matrix
1876            bd = zeros(6*self.n, 6*self.n)
1877            for i in range(self.n):
1878                bd[i*6:i*6+6, i*6:i*6+6] = SE3adMatrix(Matrix(Vd[i*6:i*6+6]))
1879            
1880            # First time derivative of Mass inertia matrix in joint space (n x n)
1881            Mbd = -Mb*A*a - (Mb*A*a).T
1882            Md = J.T * Mbd * J
1883            Md = self.simplify(Md, cse, simplify)
1884            
1885            # First time derivative of Coriolis-Centrifugal matrix in joint space (n x n)
1886            Cbd = Mb*A*a*A*a - Mb*A*a*a - Mb*A*ad - bd.T * Mb - Cb*A*a - a.T*A.T*Cb
1887            Cd = J.T*Cbd*J
1888            Cd = self.simplify(Cd, cse, simplify)
1889            
1890            # First time derivative of gravity force
1891            Qdgrav = J.T*Mbd*U*Vd_0
1892            Qdgrav = self.simplify(Qdgrav, cse, simplify)
1893            
1894            # First time derivative of External Wrench
1895            Wdext = zeros(6*self.n,1)
1896            for i in range(self.n_ee):
1897                Wdext[6*(self.ee_parent[i]-1):6*self.ee_parent[i], 0] = WDEE[i if len(WDEE) == self.n_ee else 0]
1898            Qdext = J.T*(Wdext - (A*a).T * Wext)
1899            
1900            # Qd = M*q3d + (Md + C)*q2d + Cd*qd  # without gravity 
1901            Qd = M*q3d + (Md + C)*q2d + Cd*qd + Qdgrav + Qdext # with gravity
1902            Qd = self.simplify(Qd, cse, simplify)
1903            
1904            self.Md = Md
1905            self.Cd = Cd
1906            self.Qdgrav = Qdgrav
1907            self.Qd = Qd
1908
1909        ##### Second Order Derivatives of EOM #####
1910        if q3d is not None and q4d is not None:        
1911            # Second time derivative of Block diagonal matrix a (6n x 6n)
1912            a2d = zeros(6*self.n, 6*self.n)
1913            for i in range(self.n):
1914                a2d[i*6:i*6+6, i*6:i*6+6] = SE3adMatrix(self.X[i]) * q3d[i]
1915                
1916            # Second time derivative of Block diagonal matrix b (6n x 6n) 
1917            # used in Coriolis matrix
1918            b2d = zeros(6*self.n, 6*self.n)
1919            for i in range(self.n):
1920                b2d[i*6:i*6+6, i*6:i*6+6] = SE3adMatrix(Matrix(V2d[i*6:i*6+6]))
1921                
1922            # Second time derivative of Mass inertia matrix in joint space (n x n)
1923            Mb2d = (- Mb*A*ad - (Mb*A*ad).T + 2*Mb*A*a*A*a + 2*(Mb*A*a*A*a).T 
1924                    + 2*a.T*A.T*Mb*A*a - Mb*A*a*a - (Mb*A*a*a).T)
1925            M2d = J.T*Mb2d*J
1926            M2d = self.simplify(M2d, cse, simplify)
1927            
1928            # Second time derivative of Coriolis-Centrifugal matrix in joint space (n x n)
1929            Cddot = (- Mb*A*a2d - 3*Mb*A*a*ad - Mb*A*a*a*a - b2d.T*Mb 
1930                     + Mb*A*ad*A*a + Mb*A*a*a*A*a + 2*Mb*A*a*A*ad 
1931                     + 2*Mb*A*a*A*a*a - 2*Mb*A*a*A*a*A*a)
1932            Cb2d = (Cddot - (Cbd + a.T*A.T*Cb)*A*a - a.T*A.T*(Cbd + Cb*A*a) 
1933                    - Cb*A*ad - ad.T*A.T*Cb - Cb*A*a*a - a.T*a.T*A.T*Cb 
1934                    - Cbd*A*a - a.T*A.T*Cbd)
1935            C2d = J.T*Cb2d*J
1936            C2d = self.simplify(C2d, cse, simplify)
1937            
1938            # Second time derivative of gravity force
1939            Q2dgrav = J.T*Mb2d*U*Vd_0
1940            Q2dgrav = self.simplify(Q2dgrav, cse, simplify)
1941            
1942            # Second time derivative of External Wrench
1943            W2dext = zeros(6*self.n,1)
1944            for i in range(self.n_ee):
1945                W2dext[6*(self.ee_parent[i]-1):6*self.ee_parent[i], 0] = W2DEE[i if len(W2DEE) == self.n_ee else 0]
1946            Q2dext = J.T*(W2dext - 2*(A*a).T*Wdext + (2*(A*a*A*a).T - (A*ad).T - (A*a*a).T)*Wext)
1947            
1948            # Second time derivative of generalized forces
1949            # without gravity:
1950            # Q2d = M*q4d + (2*Md + C)*q3d + (M2d + 2*Cd)*q2d + C2d*qd   
1951            # with gravity and external forces:
1952            Q2d = M*q4d + (2*Md + C)*q3d + (M2d + 2*Cd)*q2d + C2d*qd + Q2dgrav + Q2dext
1953            Q2d = self.simplify(Q2d, cse, simplify)
1954            
1955            self.M2d = M2d
1956            self.C2d = C2d
1957            self.Q2dgrav = Q2dgrav
1958            self.Q2d = Q2d
1959
1960        # save used symbols
1961        for e in self._get_expressions():
1962            self.all_symbols.update(e.free_symbols)
1963
1964        print("Done")
1965        return Q
1966
1967    def _closed_form_kinematics_body_fixed_parallel(
1968        self, q: MutableDenseMatrix, qd: MutableDenseMatrix, 
1969        q2d: MutableDenseMatrix, simplify: bool=True, 
1970        cse: bool=False) -> MutableDenseMatrix:
1971        """Position, velocity and acceleration kinematics using 
1972        body fixed representation of the twists in closed form.
1973
1974        The following expressions are saved in the class and can be 
1975        code generated afterwards:
1976            body_acceleration
1977            body_acceleration_ee
1978            body_jacobian_matrix
1979            body_jacobian_matrix_dot 
1980            body_jacobian_matrix_ee
1981            body_jacobian_matrix_ee_dot
1982            body_twist_ee
1983            forward_kinematics
1984            hybrid_acceleration
1985            hybrid_acceleration_ee
1986            hybrid_jacobian_matrix
1987            hybrid_jacobian_matrix_dot
1988            hybrid_jacobian_matrix_ee
1989            hybrid_jacobian_matrix_ee_dot
1990            hybrid_twist_ee
1991
1992        Args:
1993            q (sympy.Matrix): 
1994                (n,1) Generalized position vector.
1995            qd (sympy.Matrix): 
1996                (n,1) Generalized velocity vector.
1997            q2d (sympy.Matrix): 
1998                (n,1) Generalized acceleration vector.
1999            simplify (bool, optional): 
2000                Use simplify command on saved expressions. 
2001                Defaults to True.
2002            cse (bool, optional): 
2003                Use common subexpression elimination. Defaults to False.
2004
2005        Returns:
2006            sympy.Matrix: Forward kinematics.
2007        """
2008        # This method does the same as _closed_form_kinematics_body_fixed.
2009        # Parallel computation is implemented by writing most values 
2010        # in queues, organized in a dict.
2011        # This ensures the correct order for the execution.
2012        # To understand the calculations it is recommended to read the 
2013        # code in _closed_form_kinematics_body_fixed since it is more 
2014        # readable and has the same structure.
2015
2016        print("Forward kinematics calculation")
2017        self.var_syms.update(q.free_symbols)
2018        self.var_syms.update(qd.free_symbols)
2019        self.var_syms.update(q2d.free_symbols)
2020
2021        self.n = len(q)
2022        self.queue_dict["subex_dict"] = Queue()
2023
2024        # calc Forward kinematics
2025        if self.parent and self.support:
2026            FK_C, A = self._calc_A_matrix_tree(q)
2027        else:    
2028            FK_C, A = self._calc_A_matrix(q)
2029        
2030        for i in range(self.n_ee):
2031            self._set_value(f"fkin{i}", FK_C[self.ee_parent[i]-1]*self.ee[i])
2032            self._start_simplification_process(f"fkin{i}", cse, simplify)
2033            
2034        if self.J is not None:
2035            self._set_value("J", self.J)
2036            self._set_value("V", self._V)
2037        else:
2038            # Block diagonal matrix X (6n x n) of the screw coordinate 
2039            # vector associated to all joints in the body frame (Constant)
2040            X = zeros(6*self.n, self.n)
2041            for i in range(self.n):
2042                X[6*i:6*i+6, i] = self.X[i]
2043
2044            # System level Jacobian
2045            self._set_value("J", A*X)
2046            self._start_simplification_process("J", cse, simplify)
2047            # System twist (6n x 1)
2048            self._set_value_as_process("V", lambda: self._get_value("J")*qd)
2049
2050        for i in range(self.n_ee):
2051            # Different Jacobians
2052            self._set_value_as_process(
2053                f"R_i{i}", 
2054                lambda: 
2055                    Matrix(self._get_value(f"fkin{i}")[:3, :3])
2056                    .row_join(zeros(3, 1))
2057                    .col_join(Matrix([0, 0, 0, 1]).T)
2058                )
2059
2060            self._start_simplification_process(f"R_i{i}", cse, simplify)
2061            
2062            self._set_value(f"R_BFn{i}", Matrix(FK_C[self.ee_parent[i]-1][:3, :3]).row_join(
2063                zeros(3, 1)).col_join(Matrix([0, 0, 0, 1]).T)) 
2064
2065            # Body fixed Jacobian of last moving body 
2066            # (This may not correspond to end-effector frame)
2067            self._set_value_as_process(
2068                f"Jb{i}", 
2069                lambda: self._get_value("J")[6*(self.ee_parent[i]-1):6*self.ee_parent[i], :])
2070            self._start_simplification_process(f"Jb{i}", cse, simplify)
2071            
2072            self._set_value_as_process(f"Vb_BFn{i}", lambda: self._get_value(f"Jb{i}")*qd)
2073            # Body fixed twist of last moving body
2074            self._start_simplification_process(f"Vb_BFn{i}", cse, simplify)
2075            
2076            self._set_value_as_process(f"Vh_BFn{i}", lambda: SE3AdjMatrix(
2077                self._get_value(f"R_BFn{i}"))*self._get_value(f"Vb_BFn{i}"))
2078            self._start_simplification_process(f"Vh_BFn{i}", cse, simplify)
2079            
2080            # Body fixed twist of end-effector frame
2081            self._set_value_as_process(f"Vb_ee{i}", lambda: SE3AdjMatrix(
2082                SE3Inv(self.ee[i]))*self._get_value(f"Vb_BFn{i}"))
2083            self._start_simplification_process(f"Vb_ee{i}", cse, simplify)
2084            
2085            # Hybrid twist of end-effector frame
2086            self._set_value_as_process(f"Vh_ee{i}", lambda: SE3AdjMatrix(
2087                self._get_value(f"R_i{i}"))*self._get_value(f"Vb_ee{i}"))
2088            self._start_simplification_process(f"Vh_ee{i}", cse, simplify)
2089            
2090            # Body fixed Jacobian of end-effector frame
2091            self._set_value_as_process(f"Jb_ee{i}", lambda: SE3AdjMatrix(
2092                SE3Inv(self.ee[i]))*self._get_value(f"Jb{i}"))
2093            self._start_simplification_process(f"Jb_ee{i}", cse, simplify)
2094            
2095            # Hybrid Jacobian of end-effector frame
2096            self._set_value_as_process(f"Jh_ee{i}", lambda: SE3AdjMatrix(
2097                self._get_value(f"R_i{i}"))*self._get_value(f"Jb_ee{i}"))
2098            # Hybrid Jacobian of last moving body
2099            self._set_value_as_process(f"Jh{i}", lambda: SE3AdjMatrix(
2100                self._get_value(f"R_i{i}"))*self._get_value(f"Jb{i}"))
2101
2102            self._start_simplification_process(f"Jh_ee{i}", cse, simplify)
2103            self._start_simplification_process(f"Jh{i}", cse, simplify)
2104            
2105        # Acceleration computations
2106        if self._a is not None:
2107            self._set_value("a", self._a)
2108        else:
2109            # Block diagonal matrix a (6n x 6n)
2110            a = zeros(6*self.n, 6*self.n)
2111            for i in range(self.n):
2112                a[6*i:6*i+6, 6*i:6*i+6] = SE3adMatrix(self.X[i])*qd[i]
2113            self._set_value("a", a)
2114            self._start_simplification_process("a", cse, simplify)
2115            
2116        # System acceleration (6n x 1)
2117        # System-level Jacobian time derivative
2118        self._set_value_as_process(
2119            "Jdot", lambda: -A*self._get_value("a")*self._get_value("J"))
2120        self._start_simplification_process("Jdot", cse, simplify)
2121        
2122        self._set_value_as_process("Vbd", lambda: self._get_value(
2123            "J")*q2d - A*self._get_value("a")*self._get_value("V"))
2124
2125        for i in range(self.n_ee):
2126            # Hybrid acceleration of the last body
2127            self._set_value_as_process(
2128                f"Vbd_BFn{i}", lambda: self._get_value("Vbd")[6*(self.ee_parent[i]-1):6*self.ee_parent[i], :])
2129
2130            self._start_simplification_process(f"Vbd_BFn{i}", cse, simplify)
2131            
2132            # Hybrid twist of end-effector frame
2133            self._set_value_as_process(
2134                f"Vhd_BFn{i}", 
2135                lambda: 
2136                    SE3AdjMatrix(self._get_value(f"R_BFn{i}"))
2137                    * self._get_value(f"Vbd_BFn{i}") 
2138                    + SE3adMatrix(Matrix(self._get_value(f"Vh_BFn{i}")[:3, :])
2139                                    .col_join(Matrix([0, 0, 0])))
2140                    * SE3AdjMatrix(self._get_value(f"R_BFn{i}"))
2141                    * self._get_value(f"Vb_BFn{i}")
2142                )
2143
2144            self._start_simplification_process(f"Vhd_BFn{i}", cse, simplify)
2145            
2146            # Body fixed twist of end-effector frame
2147            # Hybrid acceleration of the EE
2148            self._set_value_as_process(f"Vbd_ee{i}", lambda: SE3AdjMatrix(
2149                SE3Inv(self.ee[i]))*self._get_value(f"Vbd_BFn{i}"))
2150            self._start_simplification_process(f"Vbd_ee{i}", cse, simplify)
2151            
2152            # Hybrid twist of end-effector frame
2153            self._set_value_as_process(
2154                f"Vhd_ee{i}", 
2155                lambda: 
2156                    SE3AdjMatrix(self._get_value(f"R_i{i}")) 
2157                    * self._get_value(f"Vbd_ee{i}") 
2158                    + SE3adMatrix(Matrix(self._get_value(f"Vh_ee{i}")[:3, :])
2159                                    .col_join(Matrix([0, 0, 0])))
2160                    * SE3AdjMatrix(self._get_value(f"R_i{i}"))
2161                    * self._get_value(f"Vb_ee{i}")
2162                )  # Hybrid twist of end-effector frame
2163
2164            self._start_simplification_process(f"Vhd_ee{i}", cse, simplify)
2165            
2166            # Body Jacobian time derivative
2167
2168            # For the last moving body
2169            self._set_value_as_process(
2170                f"Jb_dot{i}", lambda: self._get_value("Jdot")[6*(self.ee_parent[i]-1):6*self.ee_parent[i], :])
2171
2172            # For the EE
2173            self._set_value_as_process(f"Jb_ee_dot{i}", lambda: SE3AdjMatrix(
2174                SE3Inv(self.ee[i]))*self._get_value(f"Jb_dot{i}"))
2175            self._start_simplification_process(f"Jb_ee_dot{i}", cse, simplify)
2176            
2177            # Hybrid Jacobian time derivative
2178            # For the last moving body
2179            self._set_value_as_process(
2180                f"Jh_dot{i}", 
2181                lambda: 
2182                    SE3AdjMatrix(self._get_value(f"R_BFn{i}"))
2183                    * self._get_value(f"Jb_dot{i}") 
2184                    + SE3adMatrix(Matrix(self._get_value(f"Vh_BFn{i}")[:3, :])
2185                                    .col_join(Matrix([0, 0, 0])))
2186                    * SE3AdjMatrix(self._get_value(f"R_BFn{i}"))
2187                    * self._get_value(f"Jb{i}")
2188                )
2189            self._start_simplification_process(f"Jh_dot{i}", cse, simplify)
2190            
2191            # For the EE
2192            self._set_value_as_process(
2193                f"Jh_ee_dot{i}", 
2194                lambda: 
2195                    SE3AdjMatrix(self._get_value(f"R_i{i}"))
2196                    * self._get_value(f"Jb_ee_dot{i}") 
2197                    + SE3adMatrix(Matrix(self._get_value(f"Vh_ee{i}")[:3, :])
2198                                    .col_join(Matrix([0, 0, 0])))
2199                    * SE3AdjMatrix(self._get_value(f"R_i{i}"))
2200                    * self._get_value(f"Jb_ee{i}")
2201                )
2202            self._start_simplification_process(f"Jh_ee_dot{i}", cse, simplify)
2203            
2204        self._a = self._get_value("a")
2205        self._V = self._get_value("V")
2206
2207        # variables for Code Generation:
2208        self.J = self._get_value("J")
2209        self.Jdot = self._get_value("Jdot")
2210        self.fkin = [self._get_value(f"fkin{i}") for i in range(self.n_ee)]
2211        self.Jb = [self._get_value(f"Jb{i}") for i in range(self.n_ee)]
2212        self.Jh = [self._get_value(f"Jh{i}") for i in range(self.n_ee)]
2213        self.Vb_ee = [self._get_value(f"Vb_ee{i}") for i in range(self.n_ee)]
2214        self.Vh_ee = [self._get_value(f"Vh_ee{i}") for i in range(self.n_ee)]
2215        self.Jb_ee = [self._get_value(f"Jb_ee{i}") for i in range(self.n_ee)]
2216        self.Jh_ee = [self._get_value(f"Jh_ee{i}") for i in range(self.n_ee)]
2217        self.Vh_BFn = [self._get_value(f"Vh_BFn{i}") for i in range(self.n_ee)]
2218        self.Vb_BFn = [self._get_value(f"Vb_BFn{i}") for i in range(self.n_ee)]
2219        self.Vhd_BFn = [self._get_value(f"Vhd_BFn{i}") for i in range(self.n_ee)]
2220        self.Vbd_BFn = [self._get_value(f"Vbd_BFn{i}") for i in range(self.n_ee)]
2221        self.Vhd_ee = [self._get_value(f"Vhd_ee{i}") for i in range(self.n_ee)]
2222        self.Vbd_ee = [self._get_value(f"Vbd_ee{i}") for i in range(self.n_ee)]
2223        self.Jh_dot = [self._get_value(f"Jh_dot{i}") for i in range(self.n_ee)]
2224        self.Jb_dot = [self._get_value(f"Jb_dot{i}") for i in range(self.n_ee)]
2225        self.Jh_ee_dot = [self._get_value(f"Jh_ee_dot{i}") for i in range(self.n_ee)]
2226        self.Jb_ee_dot = [self._get_value(f"Jb_ee_dot{i}") for i in range(self.n_ee)]
2227
2228        if self.n_ee == 1:
2229            self.fkin = self.fkin[0] 
2230            self.Jb = self.Jb[0] 
2231            self.Jh = self.Jh[0] 
2232            self.Vb_ee = self.Vb_ee[0] 
2233            self.Vh_ee = self.Vh_ee[0] 
2234            self.Jb_ee = self.Jb_ee[0] 
2235            self.Jh_ee = self.Jh_ee[0] 
2236            self.Vh_BFn = self.Vh_BFn[0] 
2237            self.Vb_BFn = self.Vb_BFn[0] 
2238            self.Vhd_BFn = self.Vhd_BFn[0] 
2239            self.Vbd_BFn = self.Vbd_BFn[0] 
2240            self.Vhd_ee = self.Vhd_ee[0] 
2241            self.Vbd_ee = self.Vbd_ee[0] 
2242            self.Jh_dot = self.Jh_dot[0] 
2243            self.Jb_dot = self.Jb_dot[0] 
2244            self.Jh_ee_dot = self.Jh_ee_dot[0] 
2245            self.Jb_ee_dot = self.Jb_ee_dot[0] 
2246        
2247        try:
2248            while True:
2249                self.subex_dict.update(
2250                    self.queue_dict["subex_dict"].get(timeout=0.05))
2251        except queue.Empty:
2252            pass
2253
2254        # empty Queues
2255        for i in self.queue_dict:
2256            self._flush_queue(self.queue_dict[i])
2257        self.queue_dict = {}
2258
2259        # join Processes
2260        for i in self.process_dict:
2261            self.process_dict[i].join()
2262        self.process_dict = {}
2263
2264        # save used symbols
2265        for e in self._get_expressions():
2266            self.all_symbols.update(e.free_symbols)
2267
2268        print("Done")
2269        return self.fkin
2270
2271    def _closed_form_inv_dyn_body_fixed_parallel(
2272        self, 
2273        q: MutableDenseMatrix, 
2274        qd: MutableDenseMatrix, 
2275        q2d: MutableDenseMatrix, 
2276        q3d: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix]=None, 
2277        q4d: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix]=None, 
2278        WEE: list[MutableDenseMatrix]=[zeros(6, 1)], 
2279        WDEE: list[MutableDenseMatrix]=[zeros(6, 1)], 
2280        W2DEE: list[MutableDenseMatrix]=[zeros(6, 1)], 
2281        simplify: bool=True, cse: bool=False) -> MutableDenseMatrix:
2282        """Inverse dynamics using body fixed representation of the 
2283        twists in closed form. 
2284
2285        The following expressions are saved in the class and can be 
2286        code generated afterwards:
2287            coriolis_centrifugal_matrix
2288            generalized_mass_inertia_matrix
2289            gravity_vector
2290            inverse_dynamics
2291
2292        Args:
2293            q (sympy.Matrix): 
2294                (n,1) Generalized position vector.
2295            qd (sympy.Matrix): 
2296                (n,1 )Generalized velocity vector.
2297            q2d (sympy.Matrix): 
2298                (n,1) Generalized acceleration vector.
2299            q3d (sympy.Matrix, optional): 
2300                (n,1) Generalized jerk vector. Defaults to None.
2301            q4d (sympy.Matrix, optional): 
2302                (n,1) Generalized jounce vector. Defaults to None.
2303            WEE (list of sympy.Matrix, optional): 
2304                (6,1) WEE (t) = [Mx,My,Mz,Fx,Fy,Fz] is the time varying 
2305                wrench on the EE link. 
2306                Defaults to [zeros(6, 1)].
2307            WDEE (list of sympy.Matrix, optional): 
2308                (6,1) WDEE (t) = [dMx,dMy,dMz,dFx,dFy,dFz] is the derivative 
2309                of the time varying wrench on the EE link. 
2310                Defaults to [zeros(6, 1)].
2311            W2DEE (list of sympy.Matrix, optional): 
2312                (6,1) W2DEE (t) = [ddMx,ddMy,ddMz,ddFx,ddFy,ddFz] is the 
2313                2nd derivative of the time varying wrench on the EE link. 
2314                Defaults to [zeros(6, 1)].
2315            simplify (bool, optional): 
2316                Use simplify command on saved expressions. 
2317                Defaults to True.
2318            cse (bool, optional): 
2319                Use common subexpression elimination. Defaults to False.
2320
2321        Returns:
2322            sympy.Matrix: Generalized Forces
2323        """
2324        # This method does the same as _closed_form_inv_dyn_body_fixed.
2325        # Parallel computation is implemented by writing most values 
2326        # in queues, organized in a dict.
2327        # This ensures the correct order for the execution.
2328        # To understand the calculations it is recommended to read the 
2329        # code in _closed_form_inv_dyn_body_fixed since it is more 
2330        # readable and has the same structure.
2331
2332        print("Inverse dynamics calculation")
2333
2334        self.var_syms.update(q.free_symbols)
2335        self.var_syms.update(qd.free_symbols)
2336        self.var_syms.update(q2d.free_symbols)
2337        if q3d: self.var_syms.update(q3d.free_symbols)
2338        if q4d: self.var_syms.update(q4d.free_symbols)
2339        for W in WEE:
2340            self.optional_var_syms.update(W.free_symbols)
2341        for WD in WDEE:
2342            self.optional_var_syms.update(WD.free_symbols)
2343        for W2D in W2DEE:
2344            self.optional_var_syms.update(W2D.free_symbols)
2345        
2346        self.n = len(q)
2347        self.queue_dict["subex_dict"] = Queue()
2348
2349        # calc Forward kinematics
2350        if self.parent and self.support:
2351            FK_C, A = self._calc_A_matrix_tree(q)
2352        else:    
2353            FK_C, A = self._calc_A_matrix(q)
2354        
2355        if self.J is not None:
2356            self._set_value("J", self.J)
2357            self._set_value("V", self._V)
2358        else:
2359            # Block diagonal matrix X (6n x n) of the screw coordinate 
2360            # vector associated to all joints in the body frame (Constant)
2361            X = zeros(6*self.n, self.n)
2362            for i in range(self.n):
2363                X[6*i:6*i+6, i] = self.X[i]
2364
2365            # System level Jacobian
2366            self._set_value("J", A*X)
2367            self._start_simplification_process("J", cse, simplify)
2368            
2369            # System twist (6n x 1)
2370            self._set_value_as_process("V", lambda: self._get_value("J")*qd)
2371
2372        # Acceleration computations
2373
2374        if self._a is not None:
2375            a = self._a
2376        else:
2377            # Block diagonal matrix a (6n x 6n)
2378            a = zeros(6*self.n, 6*self.n)
2379            for i in range(self.n):
2380                a[6*i:6*i+6, 6*i:6*i+6] = SE3adMatrix(self.X[i])*qd[i]
2381            self._a = a
2382
2383        # System acceleration (6n x 1)
2384        # Vd = J*q2d - A*a*V
2385        self._set_value_as_process("Vd", lambda: self._get_value(
2386            "J")*q2d - A*a*self._get_value("V"))
2387
2388        # Block Diagonal Mb (6n x 6n) Mass inertia matrix in body frame 
2389        # (Constant)
2390        Mb = zeros(6*self.n, 6*self.n)
2391        for i in range(self.n):
2392            Mb[i*6:i*6+6, i*6:i*6+6] = self.Mb[i]
2393
2394        # Block diagonal matrix b (6n x 6n) used in Coriolis matrix
2395        def _b() -> MutableDenseMatrix:
2396            nonlocal self
2397            b = zeros(6*self.n, 6*self.n)
2398            for i in range(self.n):
2399                b[i*6:i*6+6, i*6:i*6 + 6] = SE3adMatrix(
2400                    Matrix(self._get_value("V")[6*i:6*i+6]))
2401            return b
2402        self._set_value_as_process("b", _b)
2403
2404        # Block diagonal matrix Cb (6n x 6n)
2405        self._set_value_as_process(
2406            "Cb", lambda: -Mb*A*a - self._get_value("b").T * Mb)
2407
2408        # Lets setup the Equations of Motion
2409
2410        # Mass inertia matrix in joint space (n x n)
2411        self._set_value_as_process(
2412            "M", lambda: self._get_value("J").T*Mb*self._get_value("J"))
2413        self._start_simplification_process("M", cse, simplify)
2414        
2415        # Coriolis-Centrifugal matrix in joint space (n x n)
2416        self._set_value_as_process("C", lambda: self._get_value(
2417            "J").T*self._get_value("Cb")*self._get_value("J"))
2418        self._start_simplification_process("C", cse, simplify)
2419        
2420        # Gravity Term
2421        U = SE3AdjInvMatrix(FK_C[0])
2422        for k in range(1, self.n):
2423            U = U.col_join(SE3AdjInvMatrix(FK_C[k]))
2424
2425        Vd_0 = zeros(6, 1)
2426        Vd_0[3:6, 0] = -Matrix(self.gravity_vector)
2427        self._set_value_as_process(
2428            "Qgrav", lambda: self._get_value("J").T*Mb*U*Vd_0)
2429        self._start_simplification_process("Qgrav", cse, simplify)
2430        
2431        # External Wrench
2432        Wext = zeros(6*self.n, 1)
2433        # WEE (t) is the time varying wrench on the EE link.
2434        for i in range(self.n_ee):
2435                Wext[6*(self.ee_parent[i]-1):6*self.ee_parent[i], 0] = WEE[i if len(WEE) == self.n_ee else 0]
2436        self._set_value_as_process(
2437            "Qext", lambda: self._get_value("J").T * Wext)
2438
2439        # Generalized forces Q
2440        self._set_value_as_process(
2441            "Q", 
2442            lambda: 
2443                self._get_value("M") * q2d 
2444                + self._get_value("C") * qd 
2445                + self._get_value("Qgrav") 
2446                + self._get_value("Qext")
2447            )
2448
2449        self._start_simplification_process("Q", cse, simplify)
2450        
2451        # Regressor matrix for standard inertial parameter identification, Q = Y*X in SE(3)
2452        # mass-inertia parameter vector X         
2453        # m, m*c, m*cy, m*cz, Ixx, Ixy, Ixz, Iyy, Iyz, Izz        
2454        Xr = Matrix([value for i in self.Mb for value in mass_matrix_to_parameter_vector(i)])
2455        
2456        if not any([i.is_Float for i in Xr]):
2457        
2458        
2459            def _Yr() -> MutableDenseMatrix:
2460                nonlocal self
2461                S = Matrix(Identity(len(Xr)))
2462                
2463                # Regressor matrix Y   
2464                Yr = zeros(self.n, len(Xr))
2465                for i in range(self.n):
2466                    for j in range(len(Xr)):
2467                        Yr[i,j] = self.collect_and_subs(self._get_value("Q")[i], {k: v for k, v in zip(Xr, S[j,:]) if k not in {0,1}})
2468                return Yr
2469            
2470            self._set_value_as_process("Yr", _Yr)
2471            self._start_simplification_process("Yr", cse, simplify)
2472        
2473            self.Xr = Xr
2474
2475        
2476        ##### First Order Derivatives of EOM #####
2477        if q3d is not None:
2478            # First time derivative of Block diagonal matrix a (6n x 6n)
2479            ad = zeros(6*self.n, 6*self.n)
2480            for i in range(self.n):
2481                ad[i*6:i*6+6, i*6:i*6+6] = q2d[i] * SE3adMatrix(self.X[i])
2482
2483            # Third order Forward Kinematics
2484            self._set_value_as_process(
2485                "V2d", 
2486                lambda: self._get_value("J")*q3d - A*ad*self._get_value("V")
2487                - 2*A*a*self._get_value("Vd") - A*a*a*self._get_value("V"))
2488                        
2489            #  First time derivative of Block diagonal matrix b (6n x 6n) 
2490            # used in Coriolis matrix
2491            def _bd() -> MutableDenseMatrix:
2492                nonlocal self
2493                bd = zeros(6*self.n, 6*self.n)
2494                for i in range(self.n):
2495                    bd[i*6:i*6+6, i*6:i*6+6] = SE3adMatrix(Matrix(self._get_value("Vd")[i*6:i*6+6]))
2496                return bd
2497            self._set_value_as_process("bd", _bd)
2498            
2499            # First time derivative of Mass inertia matrix in joint space (n x n)
2500            Mbd = -Mb*A*a - (Mb*A*a).T
2501            self._set_value_as_process(
2502                "Md",
2503                lambda: self._get_value("J").T * Mbd * self._get_value("J"))
2504            self._start_simplification_process("Md", cse, simplify)
2505            
2506            # First time derivative of Coriolis-Centrifugal matrix in joint space (n x n)
2507            self._set_value_as_process(
2508                "Cbd",
2509                lambda: Mb*A*a*A*a - Mb*A*a*a - Mb*A*ad - self._get_value("bd").T * Mb 
2510                        - self._get_value("Cb")*A*a - a.T*A.T*self._get_value("Cb"))
2511            self._set_value_as_process(
2512                "Cd", 
2513                lambda: self._get_value("J").T*self._get_value("Cbd")*self._get_value("J"))
2514            self._start_simplification_process("Cd", cse, simplify)
2515            
2516            # First time derivative of gravity force
2517            self._set_value_as_process(
2518                "Qdgrav",
2519                lambda: self._get_value("J").T*Mbd*U*Vd_0)
2520            self._start_simplification_process("Qdgrav", cse, simplify)
2521            
2522            # First time derivative of External Wrench
2523            Wdext = zeros(6*self.n,1)
2524            for i in range(self.n_ee):
2525                Wdext[6*(self.ee_parent[i]-1):6*self.ee_parent[i], 0] = WDEE[i if len(WDEE) == self.n_ee else 0]
2526            self._set_value_as_process(
2527                "Qdext",
2528                lambda: self._get_value("J").T*(Wdext - (A*a).T * Wext))
2529            
2530            self._set_value_as_process(
2531                "Qd",
2532                lambda: self._get_value("M")*q3d 
2533                        + (self._get_value("Md") + self._get_value("C"))*q2d 
2534                        + self._get_value("Cd")*qd + self._get_value("Qdgrav") 
2535                        + self._get_value("Qdext")
2536            )
2537            self._start_simplification_process("Qd", cse, simplify)
2538            
2539        ##### Second Order Derivatives of EOM #####
2540        if q3d is not None and q4d is not None:        
2541            # Second time derivative of Block diagonal matrix a (6n x 6n)
2542            a2d = zeros(6*self.n, 6*self.n)
2543            for i in range(self.n):
2544                a2d[i*6:i*6+6, i*6:i*6+6] = SE3adMatrix(self.X[i]) * q3d[i]
2545                
2546            # Second time derivative of Block diagonal matrix b (6n x 6n) 
2547            # used in Coriolis matrix
2548            def _b2d() -> MutableDenseMatrix:
2549                nonlocal self
2550                b2d = zeros(6*self.n, 6*self.n)
2551                for i in range(self.n):
2552                    b2d[i*6:i*6+6, i*6:i*6+6] = SE3adMatrix(
2553                        Matrix(self._get_value("V2d")[i*6:i*6+6]))
2554                return b2d
2555            self._set_value_as_process("b2d", _b2d)
2556                
2557            # Second time derivative of Mass inertia matrix in joint space (n x n)
2558            Mb2d = (- Mb*A*ad - (Mb*A*ad).T + 2*Mb*A*a*A*a + 2*(Mb*A*a*A*a).T 
2559                    + 2*a.T*A.T*Mb*A*a - Mb*A*a*a - (Mb*A*a*a).T)
2560            self._set_value_as_process(
2561                "M2d",
2562                lambda: self._get_value("J").T*Mb2d*self._get_value("J"))
2563            self._start_simplification_process("M2d", cse, simplify)
2564            
2565            # Second time derivative of Coriolis-Centrifugal matrix in joint space (n x n)
2566            self._set_value_as_process(
2567                "Cddot",
2568                lambda: - Mb*A*a2d - 3*Mb*A*a*ad - Mb*A*a*a*a 
2569                        - self._get_value("b2d").T*Mb 
2570                        + Mb*A*ad*A*a + Mb*A*a*a*A*a + 2*Mb*A*a*A*ad 
2571                        + 2*Mb*A*a*A*a*a - 2*Mb*A*a*A*a*A*a
2572            )
2573            self._set_value_as_process(
2574                "Cb2d",
2575                lambda: self._get_value("Cddot") 
2576                        - (self._get_value("Cbd") + a.T*A.T*self._get_value("Cb"))*A*a 
2577                        - a.T*A.T*(self._get_value("Cbd") + self._get_value("Cb")*A*a) 
2578                        - self._get_value("Cb")*A*ad - ad.T*A.T*self._get_value("Cb") 
2579                        - self._get_value("Cb")*A*a*a - a.T*a.T*A.T*self._get_value("Cb") 
2580                        - self._get_value("Cbd")*A*a - a.T*A.T*self._get_value("Cbd")
2581            )
2582            self._set_value_as_process(
2583                "C2d",
2584                lambda: self._get_value("J").T*self._get_value("Cb2d")*self._get_value("J")
2585            )
2586            self._start_simplification_process("C2d", cse, simplify)
2587            
2588            # Second time derivative of gravity force
2589            self._set_value_as_process(
2590                "Q2dgrav",
2591                lambda: self._get_value("J").T*Mb2d*U*Vd_0
2592            )
2593            self._start_simplification_process("Q2dgrav", cse, simplify)
2594            
2595            # Second time derivative of External Wrench
2596            W2dext = zeros(6*self.n,1)
2597            for i in range(self.n_ee):
2598                W2dext[6*(self.ee_parent[i]-1):6*self.ee_parent[i], 0] = W2DEE[i if len(W2DEE) == self.n_ee else 0]
2599            self._set_value_as_process(
2600                "Q2dext",
2601                lambda: self._get_value("J").T
2602                        * (W2dext - 2*(A*a).T*Wdext + (2*(A*a*A*a).T - (A*ad).T - (A*a*a).T)*Wext) 
2603            )
2604            
2605            # Second time derivative of generalized forces
2606            # with gravity and external forces:
2607            self._set_value_as_process(
2608                "Q2d",
2609                lambda: self._get_value("M")*q4d 
2610                        + (2*self._get_value("Md") + self._get_value("C"))*q3d 
2611                        + (self._get_value("M2d") + 2*self._get_value("Cd"))*q2d 
2612                        + self._get_value("C2d")*qd 
2613                        + self._get_value("Q2dgrav") 
2614                        + self._get_value("Q2dext") 
2615            )
2616            self._start_simplification_process("Q2d", cse, simplify)
2617            
2618
2619        self._V = self._get_value("V")
2620        self.J = self._get_value("J")
2621        self.M = self._get_value("M")
2622        self.C = self._get_value("C")
2623        self.Qgrav = self._get_value("Qgrav")
2624        self.Q = self._get_value("Q")
2625        if self.Xr is not None:
2626            self.Yr = self._get_value("Yr")    
2627        if q3d is not None:
2628            self.Md = self._get_value("Md")
2629            self.Cd = self._get_value("Cd")
2630            self.Qdgrav = self._get_value("Qdgrav")
2631            self.Qd = self._get_value("Qd")
2632        if q3d is not None and q4d is not None:
2633            self.M2d = self._get_value("M2d")
2634            self.C2d = self._get_value("C2d")
2635            self.Q2dgrav = self._get_value("Q2dgrav")
2636            self.Q2d = self._get_value("Q2d")
2637
2638        try:
2639            while True:
2640                self.subex_dict.update(
2641                    self.queue_dict["subex_dict"].get(timeout=0.05))
2642        except queue.Empty:
2643            pass
2644
2645        # empty Queues
2646        for i in self.queue_dict:
2647            self._flush_queue(self.queue_dict[i])
2648        self.queue_dict = {}
2649
2650        # join Processes
2651        for i in self.process_dict:
2652            self.process_dict[i].join()
2653        self.process_dict = {}
2654
2655        # save used symbols
2656        for e in self._get_expressions():
2657            self.all_symbols.update(e.free_symbols)
2658
2659        print("Done")
2660        return self.Q
2661
2662    def partial_factor(self, exp: sympy.Expr) -> sympy.Expr:
2663        """Partial factor simplification for sympy expression.
2664
2665        Args:
2666            exp (sympy.Expr): sympy expression.
2667
2668        Returns:
2669            sympy.Expr: modified sympy expression.
2670        """
2671        # split up matrices
2672        if (type(exp) == sympy.matrices.immutable.ImmutableDenseMatrix
2673            or type(exp) == sympy.matrices.dense.MutableDenseMatrix):
2674            new_expr = zeros(*exp.shape)
2675            for i in range(exp.shape[0]):
2676                for j in range(exp.shape[1]):
2677                    new_expr[i,j] = self.partial_factor(exp[i,j])
2678            return new_expr
2679            
2680        # seach for factors
2681        factor_map = defaultdict(set)
2682        const, additive_terms = exp.as_coeff_add()
2683        for term1, term2 in combinations(additive_terms, 2):
2684            common_terms = (
2685                set(term1.as_coeff_mul()[-1])
2686                & set(term2.as_coeff_mul()[-1])
2687            )
2688            if common_terms:
2689                common_factor = sympy.Mul(*common_terms)
2690                factor_map[common_factor] |= {term1, term2}
2691        
2692        # sort by number of operations represented by the terms
2693        factor_list = sorted(
2694            factor_map.items(),
2695            key = lambda i: (i[0].count_ops() + 1) * len(i[1])
2696        )[::-1]
2697
2698        # rebuild expression
2699        used = set()
2700        new_expr = nsimplify(0)
2701        for item in factor_list:
2702            factor = item[0]
2703            appearances = item[-1]
2704            terms = 0
2705            for instance in appearances:
2706                if instance not in used:
2707                    terms += instance.as_coefficient(factor)
2708                    used.add(instance)
2709            new_expr += factor * terms
2710        for term in set(additive_terms) - used:
2711            new_expr += term
2712        return new_expr + const
2713
2714    def collect_and_subs(self, ex: sympy.Expr, terms: dict) -> sympy.Expr:
2715        for key in terms:
2716            if key.is_Atom:
2717                ex = ex.subs(key,terms[key])
2718            else:
2719                ex = ex.expand().collect(key).subs(key,terms[key])
2720        return ex
2721    
2722    def simplify(self, exp: sympy.Expr, cse: bool=False, simplify: bool=True) -> sympy.Expr:
2723        """Faster simplify implementation for sympy expressions.
2724        Expressions can be different simplified as with sympy.simplify.
2725
2726        Args:
2727            exp (sympy expression): 
2728                Expression to simplify.
2729            cse (bool, optional): 
2730                Use common subexpression elimination. Defaults to False.
2731            simplify (bool, optional): 
2732                deactivate simplification by setting simplify to False. 
2733                Defaults to True.
2734
2735        Returns:
2736            sympy expression: Simplified expression.
2737        """
2738        if cse:
2739            exp = self._cse_expression(exp)
2740        if simplify:
2741            if (type(exp) == sympy.matrices.immutable.ImmutableDenseMatrix
2742                    or type(exp) == sympy.matrices.dense.MutableDenseMatrix):
2743                # fasten simplification of symmetric matrices
2744                if exp.is_square:
2745                    # test if matrix is symmetric
2746                    # numeric test is faster than is_symmetric method  for 
2747                    # long expressions
2748                    
2749                    # create matrix with randon values
2750                    num = lambdify(list(exp.free_symbols), exp, "numpy")(
2751                        *(random.random() for i in exp.free_symbols))
2752                    # if (random) matrix is symmetric, we have to simplify 
2753                    # less values
2754                    if numpy.allclose(num, num.T):
2755                        shape = exp.shape
2756                        m_exp = exp.as_mutable()
2757                        # simplify values only once in symmetric matrices
2758                        for i in range(shape[0]):
2759                            for j in range(i):
2760                                m_exp[i, j] = self.simplify(exp[i, j])
2761                                if i != j:
2762                                    m_exp[j, i] = exp[j, i]
2763                        return Matrix(m_exp)
2764            if type(exp) == sympy.matrices.dense.MutableDenseMatrix:
2765                exp = exp.as_immutable()
2766            exp = fu(exp)  # fast function to simplify sin and cos expressions
2767            exp = cancel(exp)
2768            exp = factor(exp)
2769            exp = powsimp(exp)
2770            exp = self.partial_factor(exp)
2771            exp = exp.doit()
2772        return exp
2773
2774    def _create_topology_lists(self,robot: URDF) -> None:
2775        """Generate parent, support and child list from URDF.
2776
2777        Args:
2778            robot (URDF): URDF of robot.
2779        """
2780        # names of all links in urdf
2781        link_names = [link.name for link in robot.links] 
2782        parent_names = [] # names of parent links corresponding link_names
2783        connection_type = [] # 0 for fixed, None for base, 1 else
2784        body_index = [] # index of link; -1 for fixed links
2785        parent = [] # parent array
2786        child = [] # child array
2787        support = [] # support array
2788        # find parent link names and search for fixed joints
2789        for name in link_names:
2790            for joint in robot.joints:
2791                if joint.child == name:
2792                    parent_names.append(joint.parent)
2793                    body_index.append(None) # specify later
2794                    if joint.joint_type == "fixed":
2795                        connection_type.append(0)
2796                    else:
2797                        connection_type.append(1)
2798                    break
2799            else: # base link
2800                parent_names.append(None)
2801                connection_type.append(None)
2802                body_index.append(0)
2803
2804        # generate body indices concatenating fixed bodies
2805        while None in body_index:
2806            i1 = body_index.index(None) # i of current link
2807            # update until parent is already specified
2808            while body_index[link_names.index(parent_names[i1])] is None:
2809                i1 = link_names.index(parent_names[i1])
2810            # fixed links get index -1
2811            if connection_type[i1] == 0:
2812                body_index[i1] = -1
2813                continue
2814            i2 = link_names.index(parent_names[i1]) # i of parent link
2815            while body_index[i2] == -1: # find forst non fixed parent
2816                i2 = link_names.index(parent_names[i2])
2817            index = body_index[i2]+1 # body index
2818            while index in body_index: # find first unused index
2819                index+=1
2820            body_index[i1] = index
2821            
2822        parent = [None for _ in range(max(body_index))] 
2823        child = [[] for _ in range(max(body_index))]
2824        support = [[] for _ in range(max(body_index))]
2825
2826        # fill parent, child and support array
2827        for i in range(len(body_index)):
2828            idx = body_index[i] # get index of current body
2829            if idx <= 0: # ignore base and fixed bodys
2830                continue
2831            i1 = link_names.index(parent_names[i]) # parent index
2832            while body_index[i1] == -1: # find first non fixed parent
2833                i1 = link_names.index(parent_names[i1])
2834            parent[idx-1] = body_index[i1] # save parent index
2835            if body_index[i1] > 0: # ignore base
2836                child[body_index[i1]-1].append(idx) # save child to parent
2837            i2 = i
2838            while body_index[i2] != 0: # save all indices in support path
2839                if  body_index[i2] > 0: # ignore fixed links
2840                    support[idx-1].append(body_index[i2])
2841                i2 = link_names.index(parent_names[i2])
2842            support[idx-1].reverse()
2843        self.support = support
2844        self.child = child
2845        self.parent = parent
2846            
2847    def _nsimplify(
2848        self, num: float, *args, max_denominator: int=0, tolerance: Optional[float]=None, **kwargs
2849        ) -> sympy.Expr | float:
2850        """Find a simple sympy representation for a number like 1/2 
2851        instead of 0.5. This function extends sympy.nsimplify with a 
2852        parameter to specify a maximum denominator to avoid simplifications
2853        like 13/157.  
2854
2855        Args:
2856            num (float): number to simplify.
2857            max_denominator (int, optional): 
2858                maximum denominator to use. Use 0 to deactivate. 
2859                Defaults to 0.
2860            tolerance (float, optional): 
2861                tolerance for simplify_numbers. Defaults to 0.0001.
2862            
2863        Returns:
2864            sympy.Expr | float: simplified number.
2865        """
2866        if tolerance:
2867            if numpy.abs(num) < tolerance:
2868                return 0
2869            elif numpy.abs(1-num) < tolerance:
2870                return 1
2871            elif numpy.abs(-1-num) < tolerance:
2872                return -1 
2873        ex = nsimplify(num,*args, rational=False, tolerance=tolerance, **kwargs)
2874        if not max_denominator:
2875            return ex
2876        if ex.is_rational:
2877            try:
2878                try:
2879                    d = ex.denominator()
2880                except TypeError:
2881                    d = ex.denominator 
2882                if d > max_denominator:
2883                    return num    
2884            except ValueError:
2885                return ex
2886        elif type(ex) in {sympy.core.add.Add, sympy.core.power.Pow}:
2887            return num
2888        for i in regex.findall("(?<=Rational\(\d*, )\d*", sympy.srepr(ex)):
2889            if abs(int(i)) > max_denominator:
2890                return num
2891        return ex
2892        
2893    def load_from_urdf(self, path: str, symbolic: bool=False, 
2894                       cse: bool=False, simplify_numbers: bool=True,  
2895                       tolerance: float=0.0001, max_denominator: int=9) -> None:
2896        """Load robot from urdf.
2897
2898        Args:
2899            path (str): path to URDF.
2900            symbolic (bool, optional): 
2901                generate symbols for numeric values. 
2902                Defaults to False.
2903            cse (bool, optional): 
2904                use common subexpression elimination. Defaults to False.
2905            simplify_numbers (bool, optional): 
2906                Use eg. pi/2 instead of 1.5708. Defaults to True.
2907            tolerance (float, optional): 
2908                tolerance for simplify_numbers. Defaults to 0.0001.
2909            max_denominator (int, optional): 
2910                Maximum denominator to use for simplify numbers to avoid
2911                values like 13/153. Use 0 to deactivate. Defaults to 9.
2912
2913        Raises:
2914            NotImplementedError: supports only the joint types 
2915                "revolute", "continuous" and "prismatic".
2916        """        
2917        # load URDF
2918        robot = URDF.from_xml_file(path)
2919        
2920        self.config_representation = self.BODY_FIXED
2921        self.B = []
2922        self.X = []
2923        
2924        # get parent, child and support array
2925        self._create_topology_lists(robot)
2926        # init some variables for later
2927        fixed_origin = None
2928        fixed_links = []
2929        DOF = 0
2930        xyz_rpy_syms = []
2931        
2932        # count DOF
2933        for joint in robot.joints:
2934            if joint.joint_type in ["revolute", "continuous", "prismatic"]:
2935                DOF += 1
2936            elif joint.joint_type in ["fixed"]:
2937                pass
2938            else:
2939                raise NotImplementedError(
2940                    "Joint type '" + joint.joint_type+"' not implemented yet!")
2941
2942        ji = 0  # joint index of used joints
2943        jia = 0  # joint index of all joints (fixed included)
2944        joint_origins = []
2945        joint_origins_dict = {}
2946        for joint in robot.joints:
2947            name = joint.name
2948            
2949            # get SE3 pose from xyzrpy
2950            origin = xyz_rpy_to_matrix(joint.origin.xyz+joint.origin.rpy)
2951            if symbolic:
2952                xyz_rpy = Matrix(joint.origin.xyz+joint.origin.rpy)
2953                # substitute variables
2954                xyz_rpy_syms.append(
2955                    symbols(" ".join([name+"_%s" % s 
2956                                      for s in ["x", "y", "z", "roll", "pitch", "yar"]])))
2957                xyzrpylist = []
2958                if simplify_numbers:
2959                    # replace values like 3.142 with pi
2960                    for i in range(6):
2961                        if (self._nsimplify(xyz_rpy[i], 
2962                                           tolerance=tolerance, 
2963                                           max_denominator=max_denominator) 
2964                            in [0, -1, 1, pi, -pi, pi/2, -pi/2, 3*pi/2, -3*pi/2]
2965                            ):
2966                            xyzrpylist.append(
2967                                self._nsimplify(xyz_rpy[i], tolerance=tolerance,
2968                                                max_denominator=max_denominator))
2969                        else:
2970                            xyzrpylist.append(xyz_rpy_syms[jia][i])
2971                            self.assignment_dict[xyz_rpy_syms[jia]
2972                                                 [i]] = xyz_rpy[i]
2973                else:
2974                    # replace all values unequal 0, abs(1) with symbolic values
2975                    for i in range(6):
2976                        if xyz_rpy[i] == 0:
2977                            xyzrpylist.append(0)
2978                        elif xyz_rpy[i] == 1:
2979                            xyzrpylist.append(1)
2980                        elif xyz_rpy[i] == -1:
2981                            xyzrpylist.append(-1)
2982                        else:
2983                            xyzrpylist.append(xyz_rpy_syms[jia][i])
2984                            self.assignment_dict[xyz_rpy_syms[jia]
2985                                                 [i]] = xyz_rpy[i]
2986                # get new SE3 Pose from xyzrpy
2987                origin = xyz_rpy_to_matrix(xyzrpylist)
2988                if cse:
2989                    origin = self._cse_expression(origin)
2990            elif simplify_numbers:
2991                for i in range(4):
2992                    for j in range(4):
2993                        origin[i, j] = self._nsimplify(
2994                            origin[i, j], [pi], tolerance=tolerance,
2995                            max_denominator=max_denominator)
2996            # save SE3 pose in list
2997            joint_origins.append(origin)
2998            joint_origins_dict[name] = origin
2999            
3000            # add fixed parents to origin
3001            if joint.joint_type in ["revolute", "continuous", "prismatic"]:
3002                axis = Matrix(joint.axis)
3003                
3004                # calc fixed origin from parent origins:
3005                fixed_origin = Matrix(Identity(4))
3006                parent_joint = copy.copy(joint)
3007                while True :
3008                    try:
3009                        parent_joint = robot.joint_map[robot.parent_map[parent_joint.parent][0]]
3010                    except KeyError: # base_link has no parent
3011                        break
3012                    if parent_joint.type == "fixed":
3013                        fixed_origin = joint_origins_dict[parent_joint.name] * fixed_origin
3014                    else: # stop when last non fixed joint is reached
3015                        break
3016
3017                # transform
3018                origin = fixed_origin * origin 
3019                
3020                if simplify_numbers:
3021                    for i in range(3):
3022                        axis[i] = self._nsimplify(axis[i], [pi], tolerance=tolerance,
3023                                            max_denominator=max_denominator)
3024                
3025                self.B.append(Matrix(origin))
3026
3027                if joint.joint_type in ["revolute", "continuous"]:
3028                    self.X.append(Matrix(axis).col_join(Matrix([0, 0, 0])))
3029                else:
3030                    self.X.append(Matrix(Matrix([0, 0, 0])).col_join(axis))
3031                ji += 1
3032            elif joint.joint_type == "fixed":
3033                fixed_links.append((joint.parent, joint.child))
3034            jia += 1
3035
3036        self.Mb = []
3037        i = 0
3038        first_non_fixed = 1
3039        for link in robot.links:
3040            name = link.name
3041            # ignore base link
3042            if i < first_non_fixed:
3043                if name in [x[1] for x in fixed_links]:
3044                    first_non_fixed += 1
3045                i += 1
3046                continue
3047            inertia = Matrix(link.inertial.inertia.to_matrix())
3048            mass = link.inertial.mass
3049            inertiaorigin = xyz_rpy_to_matrix(link.inertial.origin.xyz+link.inertial.origin.rpy)
3050            if symbolic:
3051                I_syms = symbols("Ixx_%s Ixy_%s Ixz_%s Iyy_%s Iyz_%s Izz_%s" % (
3052                    name, name, name, name, name, name))
3053                c_syms = symbols("cx_%s cy_%s cz_%s" % (name, name, name))
3054                I = inertia_matrix(*I_syms)
3055                m = symbols("m_%s" % name)
3056                cg = Matrix([*c_syms])
3057            else:
3058                I = Matrix(inertia)
3059                m = mass
3060                cg = Matrix(inertiaorigin[0:3, 3])
3061            M = mass_matrix_mixed_data(m, I, cg)
3062            # if link is child of fixed joint
3063            if name in [x[1] for x in fixed_links]:
3064                parent_joint = robot.joint_map[robot.parent_map[name][0]]
3065                while True:
3066                    if parent_joint.type == 'fixed':
3067                        M = (SE3AdjInvMatrix(joint_origins_dict[parent_joint.name]).T 
3068                             * M * SE3AdjInvMatrix(joint_origins_dict[parent_joint.name]))
3069                    else:
3070                        break
3071                    try:
3072                        parent_joint = robot.joint_map[robot.parent_map[parent_joint.parent][0]]
3073                    except KeyError:
3074                        break      
3075                # j = i
3076                # # transform Mass matrix
3077                # while robot.links[j].name in [x[1] for x in fixed_links]:
3078                #     M = (SE3AdjInvMatrix(joint_origins[j-1]).T 
3079                #          * M * SE3AdjInvMatrix(joint_origins[j-1]))
3080                #     j -= 1
3081                try:
3082                    self.Mb[-1] += M
3083                except IndexError: # Base dynamics not important
3084                    pass
3085                i += 1
3086                continue
3087            self.Mb.append(M)
3088            i += 1
3089        if simplify_numbers and not symbolic:
3090            for M in self.Mb:
3091                for i in range(6):
3092                    for j in range(6):
3093                        M[i, j] = self._nsimplify(
3094                            M[i, j], [pi], tolerance=tolerance,
3095                            max_denominator=max_denominator)
3096        if self.ee is None:
3097            self.ee = [transformation_matrix()]
3098        if self.gravity_vector is None:
3099            self.gravity_vector = Matrix([0,0,-9.81])
3100        if self.ee_parent is None:
3101            self.ee_parent = DOF
3102        return

3122    def dh_to_screw_coord(self, DH_param_table: MutableDenseMatrix) -> None:
3123        """Build screw coordinate paramters (joint axis frames and 
3124        body reference frames) from a given modified Denavit-Hartenberg 
3125        (DH) parameter table.
3126        Joint screw coordinates and reference configurations of bodies 
3127        are directly applied to class.
3128
3129        Args:
3130            DH_param_table (array_like): 
3131                Table with modified DH parameters (n,5) 
3132                -> (gamma,alpha,d,theta,r)
3133        """
3134        number_of_frames = DH_param_table.shape[0]
3135        self.B = []
3136        self.X = []
3137        for i in range(number_of_frames):
3138            # Reference configurations of bodies (i.e. of body-fixed 
3139            # reference frames) w.r.t their previous bodies
3140            # gamma, alpha, d, theta,r
3141            frame = DH_param_table[i, :]
3142            gamma = frame[0]
3143            alpha = frame[1]
3144            d = frame[2]
3145            theta = frame[3]
3146            r = frame[4]
3147            self.B.append(SO3Exp(Matrix([1, 0, 0]), alpha)
3148                          .row_join(Matrix([d, 0, 0]))
3149                          .col_join(Matrix([0, 0, 0, 1]).T)
3150                          * SO3Exp(Matrix([0, 0, 1]), theta)
3151                          .row_join(Matrix([0, 0, r]))
3152                          .col_join(Matrix([0, 0, 0, 1]).T)
3153                          )
3154
3155            #  Joint screw coordinates in body-fixed representation
3156            if gamma == 0:
3157                self.X.append(Matrix([0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0]))
3158            else:
3159                self.X.append(Matrix([0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1]))

3161    def _set_value_as_process(self, name: str, target: Callable) -> None:
3162        """Set return value of target as value to queue in 
3163        self.queue_dict with identifier name.
3164
3165        Args:
3166            name (str): Identifier.
3167            target (function): function, which returns value. 
3168        """
3169        if name not in self.queue_dict:
3170            self.queue_dict[name] = Queue()
3171        if name in self.process_dict:
3172            print("already there")
3173        self.process_dict[name] = Process(
3174            target=lambda: self._set_value(name, target()), args=(), name=name)
3175        self.process_dict[name].start()

3188    def _start_simplification_process(
3189        self, name: str, cse: bool=False, simplify: bool=True) -> None:
3190        """Start Process, which simplifies and overwrites value in 
3191        queue from self.queue_dict.
3192
3193        Args:
3194            name (str): Identifier
3195            cse (bool, optional): 
3196                Use common subexpression elimination. Defaults to False.
3197            simplify (bool, optional): 
3198                deactivate simplification by setting simplify to False. 
3199                Defaults to True.
3200        """
3201        if not simplify: 
3202            if not cse:
3203                return
3204            else:
3205                self._start_cse_process(name)
3206                return
3207        if name not in self.queue_dict:
3208            self.queue_dict[name] = Queue()
3209        self.process_dict[name+"_simplify"] = Process(
3210            target=self._simplify_parallel, 
3211            args=(name, cse,), 
3212            name=name+"_simplify")
3213        self.process_dict[name+"_simplify"].start()
3214        return

3218        queue from self.queue_dict.

3220        Args:
3221            name (str): Identifier
3222        """

3224            self.queue_dict[name] = Queue()
3225        self.process_dict[name+"_cse"] = Process(
3226            target=self._cse_parallel, 
3227            args=(name,), 
3228            name=name+"_cse")
3229        self.process_dict[name+"_cse"].start()

3244    def _simplify_parallel(self, name: str, cse: bool=False) -> None:
3245        """Take value from self.queue_dict, simplify it and put it in 
3246        again.
3247
3248        Args:
3249            name (str): Identifier
3250            cse (bool, optional): 
3251                Use common subexpression elimination. Defaults to False.
3252        """
3253        value = self.simplify(self.queue_dict[name].get(), cse)
3254        self.queue_dict[name].put(value)

3256    def _cse_parallel(self, name: str) -> None:
3257        """Take value from self.queue_dict, generate cse_expressions and 
3258        put it in again.

3260        Args:
3261            name (str): Identifier
3262        """
3263        value = self._cse_expression(self.queue_dict[name].get())

3266    def _flush_queue(self, q: Queue) -> None:
3267        """Flush all items in queue
3268
3269        Args:
3270            q (Queue): Queue to flush
3271        """
3272        try:
3273            while True:
3274                q.get(block=False)
3275        except queue.Empty:
3276            pass

3278    def _individual_numbered_symbols(
3279        self, exclude: list=[], i: list[int]=[0]) -> Generator[sympy.Symbol, None, None]:
3280        """create individual symbol names for subexpressions using 
3281        multiprocessing.
3282
3283        Args:
3284            exclude (list, optional): 
3285                List of names, which should not be used. Defaults to [].
3286            i (list, optional): 
3287                List with starting value -1 as first value. Is used as 
3288                counter and should not be set. Defaults to [0].
3289
3290        Returns:
3291            sympy.numbered_symbols:  Symbols
3292        """
3293        i[0] += 1
3294        prefix="sub%s_%s_" % (
3295            "_".join([str(j) for j in multiprocessing.current_process()._identity]), 
3296            i[0]
3297            )
3298        prefix = prefix.replace("sub_","sub0_")
3299        return numbered_symbols(
3300            prefix=prefix, 
3301            exclude=exclude)
3302
3303    def _cse_expression(self, exp: sympy.Expr) -> sympy.Expr:
3304        """Use common subexpression elimination to shorten expression.
3305        The used subexpressions are saved to the class internal 
3306        subex_dict.
3307
3308        Args:
3309            exp (Sympy expression): Expression to shorten using cse.
3310
3311        Returns:
3312            Sympy expression: Shortened expression.
3313        """
3314        # cse expression
3315        r, e = sympy.cse([exp, exp], self._individual_numbered_symbols(
3316            exclude=self.all_symbols), order="canonical", ignore=self.var_syms)
3317        # add subexpressions to dict
3318        for (sym, val) in r:
3319            self.subex_dict[sym] = val
3320            # for multiprocessing save in queue
3321            try:
3322                self.queue_dict["subex_dict"].put(self.subex_dict)
3323            except:
3324                pass
3325            # update used symbols
3326            self.all_symbols.update({sym})
3327        return e[0]
3328

3330        """Get list of all generated expressions.
3331
3332        Returns:
3333            list: generated expressions.
3334        """
3335        expression_dict = self.get_expressions_dict()
3336        expressions = [expression_dict[i] for i in expression_dict]
3337        return expressions
