3339    def _calc_A_matrix(
3340        self, q: MutableDenseMatrix
3341        ) -> tuple[list[MutableDenseMatrix], MutableDenseMatrix]:
3342        """Calculate forward kinematics and the block diagonal matrix 
3343        A (6n x 6n) of the Adjoint of body frame for serial robots.
3344
3345        Args:
3346            q (sympy.MutableDenseMatrix): 
3347                Generalized position vector.
3348
3349        Raises:
3350            ValueError: 
3351                Joint screw coordinates or body reference configuration 
3352                not found.
3353
3354        Returns:
3355            tuple[list[MutableDenseMatrix], MutableDenseMatrix]: (FK, A)
3356        """
3357        # calc Forward kinematics
3358        if self._FK_C is not None:
3359            FK_C = self._FK_C
3360        elif self.A:
3361            # print("Using absolute configuration (A) of the body frames")
3362            FK_f = [SE3Exp(self.Y[0], q[0])]
3363            FK_C = [FK_f[0]*self.A[0]]
3364            for i in range(1, self.n):
3365                FK_f.append(FK_f[i-1]*SE3Exp(self.Y[i], q[i]))
3366                FK_C.append(FK_f[i]*self.A[i])
3367            self._FK_C = FK_C
3368            if not self.X:
3369                # Joint screw coordinates in body-fixed representation 
3370                # computed from screw coordinates in IFR
3371                self.X = [SE3AdjInvMatrix(
3372                    self.A[i])*self.Y[i] for i in range(self.n)]
3373
3374        elif self.B:
3375            # print('Using relative configuration (B) of the body frames')
3376            FK_C = [self.B[0]*SE3Exp(self.X[0], q[0])]
3377            for i in range(1, self.n):
3378                FK_C.append(FK_C[i-1]*self.B[i]*SE3Exp(self.X[i], q[i]))
3379            self._FK_C = FK_C
3380        else:
3381            # 'Absolute (A) or Relative (B) configuration of the bodies should be provided in class!'
3382            raise ValueError("Joint screw coordinates and/or reference configuration of bodies not set.")
3383
3384        # Block diagonal matrix A (6n x 6n) of the Adjoint of body frame
3385        if self._A is not None:
3386            A = self._A
3387        else:
3388            A = Matrix(Identity(6*self.n))
3389            for i in range(self.n):
3390                for j in range(i):
3391                    Crel = SE3Inv(FK_C[i])*FK_C[j]
3392                    AdCrel = SE3AdjMatrix(Crel)
3393                    r = 6*(i)
3394                    c = 6*(j)
3395                    A[r:r+6, c:c+6] = AdCrel
3396            self._A = A
3397        return FK_C, A
3398
3399    def _calc_A_matrix_tree(
3400        self, q: MutableDenseMatrix
3401        ) -> tuple[list[MutableDenseMatrix], MutableDenseMatrix]:
3402        """Calculate forward kinematics and the block diagonal matrix 
3403        A (6n x 6n) of the Adjoint of body frame for tree like robot 
3404        structures.
3405
3406        Args:
3407            q (sympy.MutableDenseMatrix): 
3408                Generalized position vector.
3409
3410        Raises:
3411            ValueError: 
3412                Joint screw coordinates or body reference configuration 
3413                not found.
3414
3415        Returns:
3416            tuple[list[MutableDenseMatrix], MutableDenseMatrix]: (FK, A)
3417        """
3418        if self._FK_C is not None:
3419            FK_C = self._FK_C
3420        elif self.A:
3421            # print("Using absolute configuration (A) of the body frames")
3422            FK_f = []
3423            FK_C = []
3424            for i in range(self.n):
3425                if self.parent[i] == 0: # bodies with no predecessor
3426                    # Initialization for the first body
3427                    FK_f.append(SE3Exp(self.Y[i], q[i]))
3428                    FK_C.append(FK_f[i]*self.A[i])
3429                else:
3430                    FK_f.append(FK_f[self.parent[i]-1]*SE3Exp(self.Y[i], q[i]))
3431                    FK_C.append(FK_f[i]*self.A[i])      
3432            self._FK_C = FK_C
3433            if not self.X:
3434                # Joint screw coordinates in body-fixed representation 
3435                # computed from screw coordinates in IFR
3436                self.X = [SE3AdjInvMatrix(
3437                    self.A[i])*self.Y[i] for i in range(self.n)]
3438
3439        elif self.B:
3440            # print('Using relative configuration (B) of the body frames')
3441            FK_C = []
3442            for i in range(self.n):
3443                if self.parent[i] == 0: # bodies with no predecessor
3444                    # Initialization for the first body
3445                    FK_C.append(self.B[i]*SE3Exp(self.X[i], q[i]))
3446                else:
3447                    FK_C.append(FK_C[self.parent[i]-1]*self.B[i]*SE3Exp(self.X[i], q[i]))
3448        else:
3449            # 'Absolute (A) or Relative (B) configuration of the bodies should be provided in class!'
3450            raise ValueError("Joint screw coordinates and/or reference configuration of bodies not set.")
3451
3452        # Block diagonal matrix A (6n x 6n) of the Adjoint of body frame
3453        if self._A is not None:
3454            A = self._A
3455        else:
3456            A = Matrix(Identity(6*self.n))
3457            for i in range(self.n):        
3458                if True:
3459                # if self.parent[i] != 0:
3460                    for k in self.support[i]:
3461                        j = k-1
3462                        Crel = SE3Inv(FK_C[i])*FK_C[j]
3463                        AdCrel = SE3AdjMatrix(Crel)
3464                        r = 6*(i)
3465                        c = 6*(j)
3466                        A[r:r+6, c:c+6] = AdCrel
3467            self._A = A
3468        return FK_C, A
3469    
3470    def _find_start_index(self) -> int:
3471        """Guess if 0 or 1 is the first index in the robot by analysing 
3472        used variable names.
3473
3474        Returns:
3475            int: index.
3476        """
3477        # search all symbols
3478        syms = set()
3479        for i in self.Mb:
3480            syms.update(i.free_symbols)
3481        for i in self.body_ref_config:
3482            syms.update(i.free_symbols)
3483        for i in self.joint_screw_coord:
3484            syms.update(i.free_symbols)
3485        # search all indices in symbols
3486        indices = []
3487        for i in syms:
3488            indices.extend(regex.findall("\d+",str(i)))
3489        #find smalles used index
3490        if indices:
3491            if min([int(i) for i in indices]) == 0:
3492                return 0
3493            if max([int(i) for i in indices]) == self.n -1:
3494                return 0
3495        return 1

3497    def _save_vectors(self, q: MutableDenseMatrix, qd: MutableDenseMatrix, 
3498                      q2d: MutableDenseMatrix, q3d: MutableDenseMatrix, 
3499                      q4d: MutableDenseMatrix, WEE: MutableDenseMatrix, 
3500                      WDEE: MutableDenseMatrix, W2DEE: MutableDenseMatrix) -> None:
3501        """Save generalized vectors als class parameter.
3502
3503        Args:
3504            q (sympy.Matrix): 
3505                (n,1) Generalized position vector.
3506            qd (sympy.Matrix): 
3507                (n,1) Generalized velocity vector.
3508            q2d (sympy.Matrix): 
3509                (n,1) Generalized acceleration vector.
3510            q3d (sympy.Matrix): 
3511                (n,1) Generalized jerk vector.
3512            q4d (sympy.Matrix): 
3513                (n,1) Generalized jounce vector.
3514            WEE (sympy.Matrix): 
3515                (6,1) WEE (t) = [Mx,My,Mz,Fx,Fy,Fz] is the time varying 
3516                wrench on the EE link. 
3517            WDEE (sympy.Matrix): 
3518                (6,1) WDEE (t) = [dMx,dMy,dMz,dFx,dFy,dFz] is the derivative 
3519                of the time varying wrench on the EE link. 
3520            W2DEE (sympy.Matrix): 
3521                (6,1) W2DEE (t) = [ddMx,ddMy,ddMz,ddFx,ddFy,ddFz] is the 
3522                2nd derivative of the time varying wrench on the EE link. 
3523        """
3524        if not self.q: self.q = q 
3525        if not self.qd: self.qd = qd 
3526        if not self.q2d: self.q2d = q2d 
3527        if not self.q3d: self.q3d = q3d 
3528        if not self.q4d: self.q4d = q4d
3529        if self.WEE == zeros(6,1) and WEE is not Ellipsis: self.WEE = WEE
3530        if self.WDEE == zeros(6,1) and WDEE is not Ellipsis: self.WDEE = WDEE
3531        if self.W2DEE == zeros(6,1) and W2DEE is not Ellipsis: self.W2DEE = W2DEE
3532        
3533    def _time_derivative(self, expression: sympy.Expr, level: int=1) -> sympy.Expr:
3534        """Generate time derivative of expression by substituting 
3535        generalized vectors with time dependent functions,
3536        let sympy calculate the time derivative, and resubstitute the 
3537        generalized vectors.
3538
3539        Used for unit testing.
3540        
3541        Warning: This does not support external wrenches yet.
3542
3543        Args:
3544            expression (sympy.Expr): 
3545                expression dependent on generalized vectors.
3546            level (int, optional): 
3547                Order of derivative to evaluate. Defaults to 1.
3548
3549        Returns:
3550            sympy.Expr: Derived expression.
3551        """
3552        # generate dynamic symbols as substitutes
3553        startindex = 1
3554        if self.n > 1:
3555            subq = Matrix(sympy.physics.mechanics.dynamicsymbols(
3556                " ".join(f"subq{i}" for i in range(startindex,startindex+self.n))))
3557            subqd =  subq.diff()
3558            subq2d = subqd.diff() 
3559            subq3d = subq2d.diff() 
3560            subq4d = subq3d.diff() 
3561        else:
3562            subq = Matrix([sympy.physics.mechanics.dynamicsymbols(
3563                " ".join(f"subq{i}" for i in range(startindex,startindex+self.n)))])
3564            subqd =  subq.diff()
3565            subq2d = subqd.diff() 
3566            subq3d = subq2d.diff() 
3567            subq4d = subq3d.diff()
3568        # substitute
3569        expression = (expression.subs(zip(self.q,subq))
3570                                .subs(zip(self.qd,subqd))
3571                                .subs(zip(self.q2d,subq2d))
3572                                .subs(zip(self.q3d,subq3d))
3573                                .subs(zip(self.q4d,subq4d)))
3574        # derivative
3575        for _ in range(level):
3576            expression = expression.diff("t")
3577        # resubstitute
3578        expression = (expression.subs(zip(subq4d,self.q4d))
3579                                .subs(zip(subq3d,self.q3d))
3580                                .subs(zip(subq2d,self.q2d))
3581                                .subs(zip(subqd,self.qd))
3582                                .subs(zip(subq,self.q))
3583                                )
3584        return expression
3585    
3586    def __repr__(self) -> str:
3587        return (f"SymbolicKinDyn(ee={self.ee}, "
3588               f"body_ref_config={self.body_ref_config}, "
3589               f"joint_screw_coord={self.joint_screw_coord}, "

3591               f"Mb={self.Mb}, "

3602               f"WDEE={self.WDEE}, "

class SymbolicKinDyn(_AbstractCodeGeneration): 
1056class SymbolicKinDyn(_AbstractCodeGeneration):
1057    BODY_FIXED = "body_fixed"

1060    def __init__(self, 
1061                 gravity_vector: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix | list]=None, 
1062                 ee: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix | list[MutableDenseMatrix]]=None, 
1063                 body_ref_config: list[MutableDenseMatrix]=[], 
1064                 joint_screw_coord: list[MutableDenseMatrix]=[], 
1065                 config_representation: str="spatial", 
1066                 Mb: list[MutableDenseMatrix]=[], 
1067                 parent: list[int]=[], 
1068                 support: list[list[int]]=[], 
1069                 child: list[list[int]]=[], 
1070                 ee_parent: Optional[int | list[int]]=None,
1071                 q: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix]=None, 
1072                 qd: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix]=None, 
1073                 q2d: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix]=None, 
1074                 q3d: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix]=None, 
1075                 q4d: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix]=None, 
1076                 WEE: MutableDenseMatrix | list[MutableDenseMatrix]=zeros(6, 1),
1077                 WDEE: MutableDenseMatrix | list[MutableDenseMatrix]=zeros(6, 1),
1078                 W2DEE: MutableDenseMatrix | list[MutableDenseMatrix]=zeros(6, 1),
1079                 **kwargs) -> None:
1080        """SymbolicKinDyn
1081        Symbolic tool to compute equations of motion of serial chain 
1082        robots and autogenerate code from the calculated equations. 
1083        This tool supports generation of python, C and Matlab code.
1084
1085        Args:
1086            gravity_vector (sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1087                Vector of gravity. Defaults to None.
1088            ee (sympy.Matrix | list of sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1089                End-effector configuration with reference to last link 
1090                body fixed frame in the chain. This link can be selected 
1091                manually using the parameter ee_parent. 
1092                If there is more than one end-effector use a list of 
1093                transforms instead.
1094                Defaults to None.
1095            body_ref_config (list of sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1096                List of reference configurations of bodies in body-fixed
1097                or spatial representation, dependent on selected 
1098                config_representation. 
1099                Leave empty for dH Parameter usage (dhToScrewCoord(...)). 
1100                Defaults to [].
1101            joint_screw_coord (list of sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1102                List of joint screw coordinates in body-fixed 
1103                or spatial representation, dependent on selected 
1104                config_representation. 
1105                Leave empty for dH Parameter usage (dhToScrewCoord(...)). 
1106                Defaults to [].
1107            config_representation (str, optional): 
1108                Use body fixed or spatial representation for reference 
1109                configuration of bodies and joint screw coordinates.
1110                Has to be "body_fixed" or "spatial". 
1111                Defaults to "spatial".
1112            Mb (list of sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1113                List of Mass Inertia matrices for all links. Only 
1114                necessary for inverse dynamics. Defaults to [].
1115            parent (list, optional): 
1116                list of parent link indices for any joint. Use 0 for world.
1117                Only necessary for tree-like robot structures. 
1118                Defaults to [].
1119            support (list, optional): 
1120                list of lists with one list per link which includes all 
1121                support links beginning with the first link in the chain 
1122                and including the current link.
1123                Only necessary for tree-like robot structures. 
1124                Defaults to [].
1125            child (list, optional): 
1126                list of lists with one list per link which includes all
1127                child links. Use empty list if no child link is present.
1128                Only necessary for tree-like robot structures. 
1129                Defaults to [].
1130            ee_parent (int | list, optional): 
1131                parent link of the end effector frame. If there is more 
1132                than one end-effector, use a list of indices instead.
1133                Defaults to None (= last link).
1134            q (sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1135                (n,1) Generalized position vector. Defaults to None.
1136            qd (sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1137                (n,1) Generalized velocity vector. Defaults to None.
1138            q2d (sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1139                (n,1) Generalized acceleration vector. Defaults to None.
1140            q3d (sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1141                (n,1) Generalized jerk vector. Defaults to None.
1142            q4d (sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1143                (n,1) Generalized jounce vector. Defaults to None.
1144            WEE (sympy.Matrix | list, optional): 
1145                (6,1) WEE (t) = [Mx,My,Mz,Fx,Fy,Fz] is the time varying 
1146                wrench on the EE link. 
1147                If there is more than one end-effector, you can use a 
1148                list containing all wrenches instead.
1149                Defaults to zeros(6, 1).
1150            WDEE (sympy.Matrix | list, optional): 
1151                (6,1) WDEE (t) = [dMx,dMy,dMz,dFx,dFy,dFz] is the derivative 
1152                of the time varying wrench on the EE link. 
1153                If there is more than one end-effector, you can use a 
1154                list containing all wrenches instead.
1155                Defaults to zeros(6, 1).
1156            W2DEE (sympy.Matrix | list, optional): 
1157                (6,1) W2DEE (t) = [ddMx,ddMy,ddMz,ddFx,ddFy,ddFz] is the 
1158                2nd derivative of the time varying wrench on the EE link. 
1159                If there is more than one end-effector, you can use a 
1160                list containing all wrenches instead.
1161                Defaults to zeros(6, 1).
1162            
1163        """
1164        super().__init__()
1165        self.n = None  # degrees of freedom
1166        self.gravity_vector = gravity_vector
1167        self.ee = ee
1168
1169        self.B = [] # List of reference configurations of bodies in body-fixed representation.
1170        self.X = [] # List of joint screw coordinates in body-fixed representation.
1171
1172        self.A = [] # List of reference configurations of bodies in spatial representation.
1173        self.Y = [] # List of joint screw coordinates in spatial representation.
1174        
1175        self.config_representation = config_representation # @property: checks for valid value 
1176        if body_ref_config != []:
1177            self.body_ref_config = body_ref_config # @property: sets A or B
1178        if joint_screw_coord != []:
1179            self.joint_screw_coord = joint_screw_coord # @property: sets X or Y
1180        # support of old syntax
1181        if "A" in kwargs:
1182            self.A = kwargs["A"]
1183            n = len(self.A)
1184            if n:
1185                self.n = n
1186        if "B" in kwargs:
1187            self.B = kwargs["B"]
1188            n = len(self.B)
1189            if n:
1190                self.n = n
1191        if "X" in kwargs:
1192            self.X = kwargs["X"]
1193        if "Y" in kwargs:
1194            self.Y = kwargs["Y"]
1195
1196            
1197        self.Mb = Mb
1198        self.parent = parent
1199        self.child = child
1200        self.support = support
1201        
1202        # costom ee link
1203        self.ee_parent = ee_parent
1204        
1205        # temporary vars
1206        self._FK_C = None
1207        self._A = None
1208        self._a = None
1209        self._V = None  # system twist
1210
1211        
1212        # Multiprocessing
1213        # dict of queues, which saves values and results
1214        self.queue_dict = {}  
1215        # dict of running processes
1216        self.process_dict = {}  
1217        
1218        # generalized vectors end external forces
1219        self.q = q
1220        self.qd = qd
1221        self.q2d = q2d
1222        self.q3d = q3d
1223        self.q4d = q4d
1224        self.WEE = WEE
1225        self.WDEE = WDEE
1226        self.W2DEE = W2DEE

1270    def closed_form_kinematics_body_fixed(
1271        self, 
1272        q: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix]=None, 
1273        qd: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix]=None, 
1274        q2d: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix]=None, 
1275        simplify: bool=True, 
1276        cse: bool=False, 
1277        parallel: bool=True) -> MutableDenseMatrix:
1278        """Position, Velocity and Acceleration Kinematics using Body 
1279        fixed representation of the twists in closed form.
1280
1281        The following expressions are saved in the class and can be 
1282        code generated afterwards:
1283        
1284            body_acceleration
1285            body_acceleration_ee
1286            body_jacobian_matrix
1287            body_jacobian_matrix_dot 
1288            body_jacobian_matrix_ee
1289            body_jacobian_matrix_ee_dot
1290            body_twist_ee
1291            forward_kinematics
1292            hybrid_acceleration
1293            hybrid_acceleration_ee
1294            hybrid_jacobian_matrix
1295            hybrid_jacobian_matrix_dot
1296            hybrid_jacobian_matrix_ee
1297            hybrid_jacobian_matrix_ee_dot
1298            hybrid_twist_ee
1299
1300        Needs class parameters body_ref_config, joint_screw_coord and ee 
1301        to be defined.
1302
1303        Args:
1304            q (sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1305                (n,1) Generalized position vector. Defaults to None.
1306            qd (sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1307                (n,1) Generalized velocity vector. Defaults to None.
1308            q2d (sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1309                (n,1) Generalized acceleration vector. Defaults to None.
1310            simplify (bool, optional): 
1311                Use simplify command on saved expressions. 
1312                Defaults to True.
1313            cse (bool, optional): 
1314                Use common subexpression elimination. Defaults to False.
1315            parallel (bool, optional): 
1316                Use parallel computation via multiprocessing. 
1317                Defaults to True.
1318        Raises:
1319            ValueError:
1320                Joint screw coordinates and/or reference configuration 
1321                of bodies not set.
1322                
1323        Returns:
1324            sympy.Matrix: Forward kinematics.
1325        """
1326        if not q or not qd or not q2d:
1327            if not self.n:
1328                self.n = len(self.body_ref_config)
1329            if not self.q or not self.qd or not self.q2d:
1330                print(self.q, self.qd, self.q2d)
1331                q, qd, q2d = generalized_vectors(self.n,self._find_start_index())
1332            else:
1333                q, qd, q2d = self.q, self.qd, self.q2d
1334                
1335        self._save_vectors(q, qd, q2d, None, None, ..., ..., ...)
1336        self.n = len(q)
1337        
1338        # prepare ee link selection
1339        if self.ee_parent is None:
1340            self.ee_parent = [self.n]
1341        if type(self.ee) is not list: self.ee = [self.ee]
1342        if type(self.ee_parent) is not list: self.ee_parent = [self.ee_parent]
1343        assert(len(self.ee) == len(self.ee_parent))    
1344        self.n_ee = len(self.ee_parent)
1345        
1346        if parallel:
1347            self._closed_form_kinematics_body_fixed_parallel(
1348                q, qd, q2d, simplify, cse)
1349        else:
1350            self._closed_form_kinematics_body_fixed(
1351                q, qd, q2d, simplify, cse)
1352        return self.fkin
1353
1354    def closed_form_inv_dyn_body_fixed(
1355        self, 
1356        q: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix]=None, 
1357        qd: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix]=None, 
1358        q2d: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix]=None, 
1359        q3d: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix]=None, 
1360        q4d: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix]=None, 
1361        WEE: MutableDenseMatrix | list[MutableDenseMatrix]=..., 
1362        WDEE: MutableDenseMatrix | list[MutableDenseMatrix]=..., 
1363        W2DEE: MutableDenseMatrix | list[MutableDenseMatrix]=..., 
1364        simplify: bool=True, cse: bool=False, 
1365        parallel: bool=True) -> MutableDenseMatrix:
1366        """Inverse dynamics using body fixed representation of the 
1367        twists in closed form. 
1368
1369        The following expressions are saved in the class and can be 
1370        code generated afterwards:
1371            coriolis_centrifugal_matrix
1372            generalized_mass_inertia_matrix
1373            gravity_vector
1374            inverse_dynamics
1375
1376        Args:
1377            q (sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1378                (n,1) Generalized position vector. Defaults to None.
1379            qd (sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1380                (n,1) Generalized velocity vector. Defaults to None.
1381            q2d (sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1382                (n,1) Generalized acceleration vector. Defaults to None.
1383            q3d (sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1384                (n,1) Generalized jerk vector. Defaults to None.
1385            q4d (sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1386                (n,1) Generalized jounce vector. Defaults to None.
1387            WEE (list | sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1388                (6,1) WEE (t) = [Mx,My,Mz,Fx,Fy,Fz] is the time varying 
1389                wrench on the EE link. 
1390                If there is more than one end-effector, you can use a 
1391                list containing all wrenches instead.
1392                Defaults to zeros(6, 1).
1393            WDEE (list | sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1394                (6,1) WDEE (t) = [dMx,dMy,dMz,dFx,dFy,dFz] is the derivative 
1395                of the time varying wrench on the EE link. 
1396                If there is more than one end-effector, you can use a 
1397                list containing all wrenches instead.
1398                Defaults to zeros(6, 1).
1399            W2DEE (list | sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1400                (6,1) W2DEE (t) = [ddMx,ddMy,ddMz,ddFx,ddFy,ddFz] is the 
1401                2nd derivative of the time varying wrench on the EE link. 
1402                If there is more than one end-effector, you can use a 
1403                list containing all wrenches instead.
1404                Defaults to zeros(6, 1).
1405            simplify (bool, optional): 
1406                Use simplify command on saved expressions. 
1407                Defaults to True.
1408            cse (bool, optional): 
1409                Use common subexpression elimination. Defaults to False.
1410            parallel (bool, optional): 
1411                Use parallel computation via multiprocessing. 
1412                Defaults to True.
1413
1414        Raises:
1415            ValueError:
1416                Joint screw coordinates and/or reference configuration 
1417                of bodies not set.
1418        
1419        Returns:
1420            sympy.Matrix: Generalized forces
1421        """
1422        if not q or not qd or not q2d:
1423            if not self.n:
1424                self.n = len(self.body_ref_config)
1425            if not self.q or not self.qd or not self.q2d:
1426                q, qd, q2d = generalized_vectors(self.n,self._find_start_index())
1427            else:
1428                q, qd, q2d, q3d, q4d = self.q, self.qd, self.q2d, self.q3d, self.q4d
1429        
1430        if WEE is Ellipsis:
1431            WEE = self.WEE
1432        if WDEE is Ellipsis:
1433            WDEE = self.WDEE
1434        if W2DEE is Ellipsis:
1435            W2DEE = self.W2DEE
1436        
1437        self._save_vectors(q, qd, q2d, q3d, q4d, WEE, WDEE, W2DEE)
1438        self.n = len(q)
1439        
1440        # prepare ee link selection
1441        if self.ee_parent is None:
1442            self.ee_parent = [self.n]
1443        if type(self.ee_parent) is not list: self.ee_parent = [self.ee_parent]
1444        self.n_ee = len(self.ee_parent)
1445        if self.n_ee > 1:
1446            if type(WEE) is list and len(WEE) > 1:
1447                assert(len(WEE) == len(self.ee_parent))
1448            if type(WDEE) is list and len(WDEE) > 1:
1449                assert(len(WDEE) == len(self.ee_parent))
1450            if type(W2DEE) is list and len(W2DEE) > 1:
1451                assert(len(W2DEE) == len(self.ee_parent)) 
1452        if type(WEE) is not list: WEE = [WEE]
1453        if type(WDEE) is not list: WDEE = [WDEE]
1454        if type(W2DEE) is not list: W2DEE = [W2DEE]
1455        
1456        if parallel:
1457            self._closed_form_inv_dyn_body_fixed_parallel(
1458                q, qd, q2d, q3d, q4d, WEE, WDEE, W2DEE, simplify, cse)
1459        else:
1460            self._closed_form_inv_dyn_body_fixed(
1461                q, qd, q2d, q3d, q4d, WEE, WDEE, W2DEE, simplify, cse)
1462        return self.Q
1463
1464    def _closed_form_kinematics_body_fixed(
1465        self, q: MutableDenseMatrix, qd: MutableDenseMatrix, 
1466        q2d: MutableDenseMatrix, simplify: bool=True, 
1467        cse: bool=False) -> MutableDenseMatrix:
1468        """Position, velocity and acceleration kinematics using 
1469        body fixed representation of the twists in closed form.
1470
1471        The following expressions are saved in the class and can be 
1472        code generated afterwards:
1473            body_acceleration
1474            body_acceleration_ee
1475            body_jacobian_matrix
1476            body_jacobian_matrix_dot 
1477            body_jacobian_matrix_ee
1478            body_jacobian_matrix_ee_dot
1479            body_twist_ee
1480            forward_kinematics
1481            hybrid_acceleration
1482            hybrid_acceleration_ee
1483            hybrid_jacobian_matrix
1484            hybrid_jacobian_matrix_dot
1485            hybrid_jacobian_matrix_ee
1486            hybrid_jacobian_matrix_ee_dot
1487            hybrid_twist_ee
1488
1489            Needs class parameters body_ref_config, joint_screw_coord 
1490            and ee to be defined.
1491
1492        Args:
1493            q (sympy.Matrix): 
1494                (n,1) Generalized position vector.
1495            qd (sympy.Matrix): 
1496                (n,1) Generalized velocity vector.
1497            q2d (sympy.Matrix): 
1498                (n,1) Generalized acceleration vector.
1499            simplify (bool, optional): 
1500                Use simplify command on saved expressions. 
1501                Defaults to True.
1502            cse (bool, optional): 
1503                Use common subexpression elimination. Defaults to False.
1504
1505
1506        Returns:
1507            sympy.Matrix: Forward kinematics.
1508        """
1509        print("Forward kinematics calculation")
1510        self.var_syms.update(q.free_symbols)
1511        self.var_syms.update(qd.free_symbols)
1512        self.var_syms.update(q2d.free_symbols)
1513
1514        self.n = len(q)  # DOF
1515
1516        # calc Forward kinematics
1517        if self.parent and self.support:
1518            FK_C, A = self._calc_A_matrix_tree(q)
1519        else:    
1520            FK_C, A = self._calc_A_matrix(q)
1521        
1522        fkin = [None]*self.n_ee
1523        for i in range(self.n_ee):
1524            fkin[i] = FK_C[self.ee_parent[i]-1]*self.ee[i]
1525            fkin[i] = self.simplify(fkin[i], cse, simplify)    
1526        self.fkin = fkin if len(fkin)>1 else fkin[0]
1527        
1528        if self.J is not None:
1529            J = self.J
1530            V = self._V
1531        else:
1532            # Block diagonal matrix X (6n x n) of the screw coordinate 
1533            # vector associated to all joints in the body frame (Constant)
1534            X = zeros(6*self.n, self.n)
1535            for i in range(self.n):
1536                X[6*i:6*i+6, i] = self.X[i]
1537
1538            # System level Jacobian
1539            J = A*X
1540            J = self.simplify(J, cse, simplify)
1541            self.J = J
1542
1543            # System twist (6n x 1)
1544            V = J*qd
1545            self._V = V
1546
1547        R_i = [None]*self.n_ee
1548        R_BFn = [None]*self.n_ee
1549        Vb_BFn = [None]*self.n_ee
1550        Vh_BFn = [None]*self.n_ee
1551        Vb_ee = [None]*self.n_ee
1552        Vh_ee = [None]*self.n_ee
1553        Jh_ee = [None]*self.n_ee
1554        Jb_ee = [None]*self.n_ee
1555        Jh = [None]*self.n_ee
1556        Jb = [None]*self.n_ee
1557        for i in range(self.n_ee):
1558            # Different Jacobians
1559            R_i[i] = Matrix(fkin[i][:3, :3]).row_join(
1560                zeros(3, 1)).col_join(Matrix([0, 0, 0, 1]).T)
1561            R_i[i] = self.simplify(R_i[i], cse, simplify)
1562            
1563            R_BFn[i] = Matrix(FK_C[self.ee_parent[i]-1][:3, :3]).row_join(
1564                zeros(3, 1)).col_join(Matrix([0, 0, 0, 1]).T)
1565
1566            # Body fixed Jacobian of last moving body 
1567            # (This may not correspond to end-effector frame)
1568            Jb[i] = J[6*(self.ee_parent[i]-1):6*self.ee_parent[i], :] # used to be [-6:,:]
1569            Jb[i] = self.simplify(Jb[i], cse, simplify)
1570            
1571            Vb_BFn[i] = Jb[i]*qd  # Body fixed twist of last moving body
1572            Vb_BFn[i] = self.simplify(Vb_BFn[i], cse, simplify)
1573            
1574            Vh_BFn[i] = SE3AdjMatrix(R_BFn[i])*Vb_BFn[i]
1575            Vh_BFn[i] = self.simplify(Vh_BFn[i], cse, simplify)
1576            
1577            # Body fixed twist of end-effector frame
1578            Vb_ee[i] = SE3AdjMatrix(SE3Inv(self.ee[i]))*Vb_BFn[i]
1579            Vb_ee[i] = self.simplify(Vb_ee[i], cse, simplify)
1580            
1581            # Hybrid twist of end-effector frame
1582            Vh_ee[i] = SE3AdjMatrix(R_i[i])*Vb_ee[i]
1583            Vh_ee[i] = self.simplify(Vh_ee[i], cse, simplify)
1584            
1585            # Body fixed Jacobian of end-effector frame
1586            Jb_ee[i] = SE3AdjMatrix(SE3Inv(self.ee[i]))*Jb[i]
1587            Jb_ee[i] = self.simplify(Jb_ee[i], cse, simplify)
1588            
1589            # Hybrid Jacobian of end-effector frame
1590            Jh_ee[i] = SE3AdjMatrix(R_i[i])*Jb_ee[i]
1591            # Hybrid Jacobian of last moving body
1592            Jh[i] = SE3AdjMatrix(R_i[i])*Jb[i]  
1593
1594            Jh_ee[i] = self.simplify(Jh_ee[i], cse, simplify)
1595            Jh[i] = self.simplify(Jh[i], cse, simplify)
1596            
1597        self.Vb_BFn = Vb_BFn if len(Vb_BFn)>1 else Vb_BFn[0]
1598        self.Vh_BFn = Vh_BFn if len(Vh_BFn)>1 else Vh_BFn[0]
1599        self.Vb_ee = Vb_ee if len(Vb_ee)>1 else Vb_ee[0]
1600        self.Vh_ee = Vh_ee if len(Vh_ee)>1 else Vh_ee[0]
1601        self.Jh_ee = Jh_ee if len(Jh_ee)>1 else Jh_ee[0]
1602        self.Jb_ee = Jb_ee if len(Jb_ee)>1 else Jb_ee[0]
1603        self.Jh = Jh if len(Jh)>1 else Jh[0]
1604        self.Jb = Jb if len(Jb)>1 else Jb[0]
1605        
1606        # Acceleration computations
1607        if self._a is not None:
1608            a = self._a
1609        else:
1610            # Block diagonal matrix a (6n x 6n)
1611            a = zeros(6*self.n, 6*self.n)
1612            for i in range(self.n):
1613                a[6*i:6*i+6, 6*i:6*i+6] = SE3adMatrix(self.X[i])*qd[i]
1614            a = self.simplify(a, cse, simplify)
1615            self._a = a
1616
1617        # System acceleration (6n x 1)
1618        Jdot = -A*a*J  # Sys-level Jacobian time derivative
1619        Jdot = self.simplify(Jdot, cse, simplify)
1620        
1621        self.Jdot = Jdot
1622
1623        Vbd = J*q2d - A*a*V
1624
1625        Vbd_BFn = [None]*self.n_ee
1626        Vhd_BFn = [None]*self.n_ee
1627        Vbd_ee = [None]*self.n_ee
1628        Vhd_ee = [None]*self.n_ee
1629        Jb_dot = [None]*self.n_ee
1630        Jb_ee_dot = [None]*self.n_ee
1631        Jh_dot = [None]*self.n_ee
1632        Jh_ee_dot = [None]*self.n_ee
1633        for i in range(self.n_ee):
1634            # Hybrid acceleration of the last body
1635            Vbd_BFn[i] = Vbd[6*(self.ee_parent[i]-1):6*self.ee_parent[i], :] # used to be [-6:,:]
1636            Vbd_BFn[i] = self.simplify(Vbd_BFn[i], cse, simplify)
1637            
1638            # Hybrid twist of end-effector frame 
1639            # TODO: check comments
1640            Vhd_BFn[i] = (SE3AdjMatrix(R_BFn[i])*Vbd_BFn[i] 
1641                    + SE3adMatrix(Matrix(Vh_BFn[i][:3, :])
1642                                        .col_join(Matrix([0, 0, 0])))
1643                    * SE3AdjMatrix(R_BFn[i])*Vb_BFn[i])  
1644
1645            Vhd_BFn[i] = self.simplify(Vhd_BFn[i], cse, simplify)
1646            
1647            # Body fixed twist of end-effector frame
1648            # Hybrid acceleration of the EE
1649            Vbd_ee[i] = SE3AdjMatrix(SE3Inv(self.ee[i]))*Vbd_BFn[i]
1650            Vbd_ee[i] = self.simplify(Vbd_ee[i], cse, simplify)
1651            
1652            # Hybrid twist of end-effector frame
1653            Vhd_ee[i] = SE3AdjMatrix(R_i[i])*Vbd_ee[i] + SE3adMatrix(Matrix(
1654                Vh_ee[i][:3, :]).col_join(Matrix([0, 0, 0])))*\
1655                    SE3AdjMatrix(R_i[i])*Vb_ee[i]  
1656            Vhd_ee[i] = self.simplify(Vhd_ee[i], cse, simplify)
1657            
1658            # Body Jacobian time derivative
1659
1660            # For the last moving body
1661            Jb_dot[i] = Jdot[6*(self.ee_parent[i]-1):6*self.ee_parent[i], :] # used to be [-6:,:]
1662
1663            # For the EE
1664            Jb_ee_dot[i] = SE3AdjMatrix(SE3Inv(self.ee[i]))*Jb_dot[i]
1665            Jb_ee_dot[i] = self.simplify(Jb_ee_dot[i], cse, simplify)
1666            
1667            # Hybrid Jacobian time derivative
1668            # For the last moving body
1669            Jh_dot[i] = (SE3AdjMatrix(R_BFn[i])*Jb_dot[i] 
1670                    + SE3adMatrix(Matrix(Vh_BFn[i][:3, :]).col_join(Matrix([0, 0, 0])))
1671                    *SE3AdjMatrix(R_BFn[i])*Jb[i])
1672            Jh_dot[i] = self.simplify(Jh_dot[i], cse, simplify)
1673            
1674            # For the EE
1675            Jh_ee_dot[i] = (SE3AdjMatrix(R_i[i])*Jb_ee_dot[i] 
1676                        + SE3adMatrix(Matrix(Vh_ee[i][:3, :]).col_join(Matrix([0, 0, 0])))
1677                        * SE3AdjMatrix(R_i[i])*Jb_ee[i])
1678            Jh_ee_dot[i] = self.simplify(Jh_ee_dot[i], cse, simplify)
1679            
1680        self.Vbd_BFn = Vbd_BFn if len(Vbd_BFn)>1 else Vbd_BFn[0]
1681        self.Vhd_BFn = Vhd_BFn if len(Vhd_BFn)>1 else Vhd_BFn[0]
1682        self.Vbd_ee = Vbd_ee if len(Vbd_ee)>1 else Vbd_ee[0]
1683        self.Vhd_ee = Vhd_ee if len(Vhd_ee)>1 else Vhd_ee[0]
1684        self.Jb_dot = Jb_dot if len(Jb_dot)>1 else Jb_dot[0]
1685        self.Jb_ee_dot = Jb_ee_dot if len(Jb_ee_dot)>1 else Jb_ee_dot[0]
1686        self.Jh_dot = Jh_dot if len(Jh_dot)>1 else Jh_dot[0]
1687        self.Jh_ee_dot = Jh_ee_dot if len(Jh_ee_dot)>1 else Jh_ee_dot[0]
1688
1689        for e in self._get_expressions():
1690            self.all_symbols.update(e.free_symbols)
1691
1692        print("Done")
1693        return fkin
1694
1695    def _closed_form_inv_dyn_body_fixed(self, q: MutableDenseMatrix, 
1696                                        qd: MutableDenseMatrix, 
1697                                        q2d: MutableDenseMatrix,
1698                                        q3d: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix]=None, 
1699                                        q4d: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix]=None, 
1700                                        WEE: list[MutableDenseMatrix]=[zeros(6, 1)], 
1701                                        WDEE: list[MutableDenseMatrix]=[zeros(6, 1)], 
1702                                        W2DEE: list[MutableDenseMatrix]=[zeros(6, 1)], 
1703                                        simplify: bool=True, 
1704                                        cse: bool=False) -> MutableDenseMatrix:
1705        """Inverse dynamics using body fixed representation of the 
1706        twists in closed form. 
1707
1708        The following expressions are saved in the class and can be code 
1709        generated afterwards:
1710            coriolis_centrifugal_matrix
1711            generalized_mass_inertia_matrix
1712            gravity_vector
1713            inverse_dynamics
1714
1715        Args:
1716            q (sympy.Matrix): (n,1) Generalized position vector.
1717            qd (sympy.Matrix): (n,1 )Generalized velocity vector.
1718            q2d (sympy.Matrix): (n,1) Generalized acceleration vector.
1719            q3d (sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1720                (n,1) Generalized jerk vector. Defaults to None.
1721            q4d (sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1722                (n,1) Generalized jounce vector. Defaults to None.
1723            WEE (list of sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1724                (6,1) WEE (t) = [Mx,My,Mz,Fx,Fy,Fz] is the time varying 
1725                wrench on the EE link. 
1726                Defaults to [zeros(6, 1)].
1727            WDEE (list of sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1728                (6,1) WDEE (t) = [dMx,dMy,dMz,dFx,dFy,dFz] is the derivative 
1729                of the time varying wrench on the EE link. 
1730                Defaults to [zeros(6, 1)].
1731            W2DEE (list of sympy.Matrix, optional): 
1732                (6,1) W2DEE (t) = [ddMx,ddMy,ddMz,ddFx,ddFy,ddFz] is the 
1733                2nd derivative of the time varying wrench on the EE link. 
1734                Defaults to [zeros(6, 1)].
1735            simplify (bool, optional): Use simplify command 
1736                on saved expressions. Defaults to True.
1737            cse (bool, optional): Use common subexpression 
1738                elimination. Defaults to False.
1739
1740        Returns:
1741            sympy.Matrix: Generalized forces
1742        """
1743        print("Inverse dynamics calculation")
1744
1745        self.var_syms.update(q.free_symbols)
1746        self.var_syms.update(qd.free_symbols)
1747        self.var_syms.update(q2d.free_symbols)
1748        if q3d: self.var_syms.update(q3d.free_symbols)
1749        if q4d: self.var_syms.update(q4d.free_symbols)
1750        for W in WEE:
1751            self.optional_var_syms.update(W.free_symbols)
1752        for WD in WDEE:
1753            self.optional_var_syms.update(WD.free_symbols)
1754        for W2D in W2DEE:
1755            self.optional_var_syms.update(W2D.free_symbols)
1756
1757        self.n = len(q)
1758
1759        # calc Forward kinematics
1760        if self.parent and self.support:
1761            FK_C, A = self._calc_A_matrix_tree(q)
1762        else:    
1763            FK_C, A = self._calc_A_matrix(q)
1764        
1765        if self.J is not None:
1766            J = self.J  # system level Jacobian
1767            V = self._V  # system twist
1768        else:
1769            # Block diagonal matrix X (6n x n) of the screw coordinate 
1770            # vector associated to all joints in the body frame (constant)
1771            X = zeros(6*self.n, self.n)
1772            for i in range(self.n):
1773                X[6*i:6*i+6, i] = self.X[i]
1774
1775            # System level Jacobian
1776            J = A*X
1777            J = self.simplify(J, cse, simplify)
1778            self.J = J
1779
1780            # System twist (6n x 1)
1781            V = J*qd
1782            self._V = V
1783
1784        # Acceleration computations
1785        if self._a is not None:
1786            a = self._a
1787        else:
1788            # Block diagonal matrix a (6n x 6n)
1789            a = zeros(6*self.n, 6*self.n)
1790            for i in range(self.n):
1791                a[6*i:6*i+6, 6*i:6*i+6] = SE3adMatrix(self.X[i])*qd[i]
1792            self._a = a
1793
1794        # System acceleration (6n x 1)
1795        Vd = J*q2d - A*a*V
1796
1797        # Block Diagonal Mb (6n x 6n) Mass inertia matrix in body frame 
1798        # (constant)
1799        Mb = zeros(6*self.n, 6*self.n)
1800        for i in range(self.n):
1801            Mb[i*6:i*6+6, i*6:i*6+6] = self.Mb[i]
1802
1803        # Block diagonal matrix b (6n x 6n) used in Coriolis matrix
1804        b = zeros(6*self.n, 6*self.n)
1805        for i in range(self.n):
1806            b[i*6:i*6+6, i*6:i*6+6] = SE3adMatrix(Matrix(V[6*i:6*i+6]))
1807
1808        # Block diagonal matrix Cb (6n x 6n)
1809        Cb = -Mb*A*a - b.T * Mb
1810
1811        # Lets setup the Equations of Motion
1812
1813        # Mass inertia matrix in joint space (n x n)
1814        M = J.T*Mb*J
1815        M = self.simplify(M, cse, simplify)
1816        
1817        # Coriolis-Centrifugal matrix in joint space (n x n)
1818        C = J.T * Cb * J
1819        C = self.simplify(C, cse, simplify)
1820        
1821        # Gravity Term
1822        U = SE3AdjInvMatrix(FK_C[0])
1823        for k in range(1, self.n):
1824            U = U.col_join(SE3AdjInvMatrix(FK_C[k]))
1825
1826        Vd_0 = zeros(6, 1)
1827        Vd_0[3:6, 0] = -Matrix(self.gravity_vector)
1828        Qgrav = J.T*Mb*U*Vd_0
1829        Qgrav = self.simplify(Qgrav, cse, simplify)
1830        
1831        # External Wrench
1832        Wext = zeros(6*self.n, 1)
1833        # WEE (t) is the time varying wrench on the EE link.
1834        for i in range(self.n_ee):
1835            Wext[6*(self.ee_parent[i]-1):6*self.ee_parent[i], 0] = WEE[i if len(WEE) == self.n_ee else 0]
1836        Qext = J.T * Wext
1837
1838        # Generalized forces Q
1839        # Q = M*q2d + C*qd   # without gravity
1840        Q = M*q2d + C*qd + Qgrav + Qext
1841        Q = self.simplify(Q, cse, simplify)
1842        
1843        self.M = M
1844        self.C = C
1845        self.Q = Q
1846        self.Qgrav = Qgrav
1847        
1848        # Regressor matrix for standard inertial parameter identification, Q = Y*X in SE(3)
1849        # mass-inertia parameter vector X         
1850        # m, m*c, m*cy, m*cz, Ixx, Ixy, Ixz, Iyy, Iyz, Izz        
1851        Xr = Matrix([value for i in self.Mb for value in mass_matrix_to_parameter_vector(i)])
1852        # dont calculate with numeric values
1853        if not any([i.is_Float for i in Xr]):
1854            S = Matrix(Identity(len(Xr)))
1855            # Regressor matrix Y   
1856            Yr = zeros(self.n, len(Xr))
1857            for i in range(self.n):
1858                for j in range(len(Xr)):                        
1859                    Yr[i,j] = self.collect_and_subs(Q[i], {k: v for k, v in zip(Xr, S[j,:]) if k not in {0,1}})
1860            Yr = self.simplify(Yr, cse, simplify)
1861            
1862            self.Xr = Xr
1863            self.Yr = Yr
1864
1865        ##### First Order Derivatives of EOM #####
1866        if q3d is not None:        
1867            # First time derivative of Block diagonal matrix a (6n x 6n)
1868            ad = zeros(6*self.n, 6*self.n)
1869            for i in range(self.n):
1870                ad[i*6:i*6+6, i*6:i*6+6] = q2d[i] * SE3adMatrix(self.X[i])
1871
1872            # Third order Forward Kinematics
1873            V2d = J*q3d - A*ad*V - 2*A*a*Vd - A*a*a*V
1874                        
1875            #  First time derivative of Block diagonal matrix b (6n x 6n) 
1876            # used in Coriolis matrix
1877            bd = zeros(6*self.n, 6*self.n)
1878            for i in range(self.n):
1879                bd[i*6:i*6+6, i*6:i*6+6] = SE3adMatrix(Matrix(Vd[i*6:i*6+6]))
1880            
1881            # First time derivative of Mass inertia matrix in joint space (n x n)
1882            Mbd = -Mb*A*a - (Mb*A*a).T
1883            Md = J.T * Mbd * J
1884            Md = self.simplify(Md, cse, simplify)
1885            
1886            # First time derivative of Coriolis-Centrifugal matrix in joint space (n x n)
1887            Cbd = Mb*A*a*A*a - Mb*A*a*a - Mb*A*ad - bd.T * Mb - Cb*A*a - a.T*A.T*Cb
1888            Cd = J.T*Cbd*J
1889            Cd = self.simplify(Cd, cse, simplify)
1890            
1891            # First time derivative of gravity force
1892            Qdgrav = J.T*Mbd*U*Vd_0
1893            Qdgrav = self.simplify(Qdgrav, cse, simplify)
1894            
1895            # First time derivative of External Wrench
1896            Wdext = zeros(6*self.n,1)
1897            for i in range(self.n_ee):
1898                Wdext[6*(self.ee_parent[i]-1):6*self.ee_parent[i], 0] = WDEE[i if len(WDEE) == self.n_ee else 0]
1899            Qdext = J.T*(Wdext - (A*a).T * Wext)
1900            
1901            # Qd = M*q3d + (Md + C)*q2d + Cd*qd  # without gravity 
1902            Qd = M*q3d + (Md + C)*q2d + Cd*qd + Qdgrav + Qdext # with gravity
1903            Qd = self.simplify(Qd, cse, simplify)
1904            
1905            self.Md = Md
1906            self.Cd = Cd
1907            self.Qdgrav = Qdgrav
1908            self.Qd = Qd
1909
1910        ##### Second Order Derivatives of EOM #####
1911        if q3d is not None and q4d is not None:        
1912            # Second time derivative of Block diagonal matrix a (6n x 6n)
1913            a2d = zeros(6*self.n, 6*self.n)
1914            for i in range(self.n):
1915                a2d[i*6:i*6+6, i*6:i*6+6] = SE3adMatrix(self.X[i]) * q3d[i]
1916                
1917            # Second time derivative of Block diagonal matrix b (6n x 6n) 
1918            # used in Coriolis matrix
1919            b2d = zeros(6*self.n, 6*self.n)
1920            for i in range(self.n):
1921                b2d[i*6:i*6+6, i*6:i*6+6] = SE3adMatrix(Matrix(V2d[i*6:i*6+6]))
1922                
1923            # Second time derivative of Mass inertia matrix in joint space (n x n)
1924            Mb2d = (- Mb*A*ad - (Mb*A*ad).T + 2*Mb*A*a*A*a + 2*(Mb*A*a*A*a).T 
1925                    + 2*a.T*A.T*Mb*A*a - Mb*A*a*a - (Mb*A*a*a).T)
1926            M2d = J.T*Mb2d*J
1927            M2d = self.simplify(M2d, cse, simplify)
1928            
1929            # Second time derivative of Coriolis-Centrifugal matrix in joint space (n x n)
1930            Cddot = (- Mb*A*a2d - 3*Mb*A*a*ad - Mb*A*a*a*a - b2d.T*Mb 
1931                     + Mb*A*ad*A*a + Mb*A*a*a*A*a + 2*Mb*A*a*A*ad 
1932                     + 2*Mb*A*a*A*a*a - 2*Mb*A*a*A*a*A*a)
1933            Cb2d = (Cddot - (Cbd + a.T*A.T*Cb)*A*a - a.T*A.T*(Cbd + Cb*A*a) 
1934                    - Cb*A*ad - ad.T*A.T*Cb - Cb*A*a*a - a.T*a.T*A.T*Cb 
1935                    - Cbd*A*a - a.T*A.T*Cbd)
1936            C2d = J.T*Cb2d*J
1937            C2d = self.simplify(C2d, cse, simplify)
1938            
1939            # Second time derivative of gravity force
1940            Q2dgrav = J.T*Mb2d*U*Vd_0
1941            Q2dgrav = self.simplify(Q2dgrav, cse, simplify)
1942            
1943            # Second time derivative of External Wrench
1944            W2dext = zeros(6*self.n,1)
1945            for i in range(self.n_ee):
1946                W2dext[6*(self.ee_parent[i]-1):6*self.ee_parent[i], 0] = W2DEE[i if len(W2DEE) == self.n_ee else 0]
1947            Q2dext = J.T*(W2dext - 2*(A*a).T*Wdext + (2*(A*a*A*a).T - (A*ad).T - (A*a*a).T)*Wext)
1948            
1949            # Second time derivative of generalized forces
1950            # without gravity:
1951            # Q2d = M*q4d + (2*Md + C)*q3d + (M2d + 2*Cd)*q2d + C2d*qd   
1952            # with gravity and external forces:
1953            Q2d = M*q4d + (2*Md + C)*q3d + (M2d + 2*Cd)*q2d + C2d*qd + Q2dgrav + Q2dext
1954            Q2d = self.simplify(Q2d, cse, simplify)
1955            
1956            self.M2d = M2d
1957            self.C2d = C2d
1958            self.Q2dgrav = Q2dgrav
1959            self.Q2d = Q2d
1960
1961        # save used symbols
1962        for e in self._get_expressions():
1963            self.all_symbols.update(e.free_symbols)
1964
1965        print("Done")
1966        return Q
1967
1968    def _closed_form_kinematics_body_fixed_parallel(
1969        self, q: MutableDenseMatrix, qd: MutableDenseMatrix, 
1970        q2d: MutableDenseMatrix, simplify: bool=True, 
1971        cse: bool=False) -> MutableDenseMatrix:
1972        """Position, velocity and acceleration kinematics using 
1973        body fixed representation of the twists in closed form.
1974
1975        The following expressions are saved in the class and can be 
1976        code generated afterwards:
1977            body_acceleration
1978            body_acceleration_ee
1979            body_jacobian_matrix
1980            body_jacobian_matrix_dot 
1981            body_jacobian_matrix_ee
1982            body_jacobian_matrix_ee_dot
1983            body_twist_ee
1984            forward_kinematics
1985            hybrid_acceleration
1986            hybrid_acceleration_ee
1987            hybrid_jacobian_matrix
1988            hybrid_jacobian_matrix_dot
1989            hybrid_jacobian_matrix_ee
1990            hybrid_jacobian_matrix_ee_dot
1991            hybrid_twist_ee
1992
1993        Args:
1994            q (sympy.Matrix): 
1995                (n,1) Generalized position vector.
1996            qd (sympy.Matrix): 
1997                (n,1) Generalized velocity vector.
1998            q2d (sympy.Matrix): 
1999                (n,1) Generalized acceleration vector.
2000            simplify (bool, optional): 
2001                Use simplify command on saved expressions. 
2002                Defaults to True.
2003            cse (bool, optional): 
2004                Use common subexpression elimination. Defaults to False.
2005
2006        Returns:
2007            sympy.Matrix: Forward kinematics.
2008        """
2009        # This method does the same as _closed_form_kinematics_body_fixed.
2010        # Parallel computation is implemented by writing most values 
2011        # in queues, organized in a dict.
2012        # This ensures the correct order for the execution.
2013        # To understand the calculations it is recommended to read the 
2014        # code in _closed_form_kinematics_body_fixed since it is more 
2015        # readable and has the same structure.
2016
2017        print("Forward kinematics calculation")
2018        self.var_syms.update(q.free_symbols)
2019        self.var_syms.update(qd.free_symbols)
2020        self.var_syms.update(q2d.free_symbols)
2021
2022        self.n = len(q)
2023        self.queue_dict["subex_dict"] = Queue()
2024
2025        # calc Forward kinematics
2026        if self.parent and self.support:
2027            FK_C, A = self._calc_A_matrix_tree(q)
2028        else:    
2029            FK_C, A = self._calc_A_matrix(q)
2030        
2031        for i in range(self.n_ee):
2032            self._set_value(f"fkin{i}", FK_C[self.ee_parent[i]-1]*self.ee[i])
2033            self._start_simplification_process(f"fkin{i}", cse, simplify)
2034            
2035        if self.J is not None:
2036            self._set_value("J", self.J)
2037            self._set_value("V", self._V)
2038        else:
2039            # Block diagonal matrix X (6n x n) of the screw coordinate 
2040            # vector associated to all joints in the body frame (Constant)
2041            X = zeros(6*self.n, self.n)
2042            for i in range(self.n):
2043                X[6*i:6*i+6, i] = self.X[i]
2044
2045            # System level Jacobian
2046            self._set_value("J", A*X)
2047            self._start_simplification_process("J", cse, simplify)
2048            # System twist (6n x 1)
2049            self._set_value_as_process("V", lambda: self._get_value("J")*qd)
2050
2051        for i in range(self.n_ee):
2052            # Different Jacobians
2053            self._set_value_as_process(
2054                f"R_i{i}", 
2055                lambda: 
2056                    Matrix(self._get_value(f"fkin{i}")[:3, :3])
2057                    .row_join(zeros(3, 1))
2058                    .col_join(Matrix([0, 0, 0, 1]).T)
2059                )
2060
2061            self._start_simplification_process(f"R_i{i}", cse, simplify)
2062            
2063            self._set_value(f"R_BFn{i}", Matrix(FK_C[self.ee_parent[i]-1][:3, :3]).row_join(
2064                zeros(3, 1)).col_join(Matrix([0, 0, 0, 1]).T)) 
2065
2066            # Body fixed Jacobian of last moving body 
2067            # (This may not correspond to end-effector frame)
2068            self._set_value_as_process(
2069                f"Jb{i}", 
2070                lambda: self._get_value("J")[6*(self.ee_parent[i]-1):6*self.ee_parent[i], :])
2071            self._start_simplification_process(f"Jb{i}", cse, simplify)
2072            
2073            self._set_value_as_process(f"Vb_BFn{i}", lambda: self._get_value(f"Jb{i}")*qd)
2074            # Body fixed twist of last moving body
2075            self._start_simplification_process(f"Vb_BFn{i}", cse, simplify)
2076            
2077            self._set_value_as_process(f"Vh_BFn{i}", lambda: SE3AdjMatrix(
2078                self._get_value(f"R_BFn{i}"))*self._get_value(f"Vb_BFn{i}"))
2079            self._start_simplification_process(f"Vh_BFn{i}", cse, simplify)
2080            
2081            # Body fixed twist of end-effector frame
2082            self._set_value_as_process(f"Vb_ee{i}", lambda: SE3AdjMatrix(
2083                SE3Inv(self.ee[i]))*self._get_value(f"Vb_BFn{i}"))
2084            self._start_simplification_process(f"Vb_ee{i}", cse, simplify)
2085            
2086            # Hybrid twist of end-effector frame
2087            self._set_value_as_process(f"Vh_ee{i}", lambda: SE3AdjMatrix(
2088                self._get_value(f"R_i{i}"))*self._get_value(f"Vb_ee{i}"))
2089            self._start_simplification_process(f"Vh_ee{i}", cse, simplify)
2090            
2091            # Body fixed Jacobian of end-effector frame
2092            self._set_value_as_process(f"Jb_ee{i}", lambda: SE3AdjMatrix(
2093                SE3Inv(self.ee[i]))*self._get_value(f"Jb{i}"))
2094            self._start_simplification_process(f"Jb_ee{i}", cse, simplify)
2095            
2096            # Hybrid Jacobian of end-effector frame
2097            self._set_value_as_process(f"Jh_ee{i}", lambda: SE3AdjMatrix(
2098                self._get_value(f"R_i{i}"))*self._get_value(f"Jb_ee{i}"))
2099            # Hybrid Jacobian of last moving body
2100            self._set_value_as_process(f"Jh{i}", lambda: SE3AdjMatrix(
2101                self._get_value(f"R_i{i}"))*self._get_value(f"Jb{i}"))
2102
2103            self._start_simplification_process(f"Jh_ee{i}", cse, simplify)
2104            self._start_simplification_process(f"Jh{i}", cse, simplify)
2105            
2106        # Acceleration computations
2107        if self._a is not None:
2108            self._set_value("a", self._a)
2109        else:
2110            # Block diagonal matrix a (6n x 6n)
2111            a = zeros(6*self.n, 6*self.n)
2112            for i in range(self.n):
2113                a[6*i:6*i+6, 6*i:6*i+6] = SE3adMatrix(self.X[i])*qd[i]
2114            self._set_value("a", a)
2115            self._start_simplification_process("a", cse, simplify)
2116            
2117        # System acceleration (6n x 1)
2118        # System-level Jacobian time derivative
2119        self._set_value_as_process(
2120            "Jdot", lambda: -A*self._get_value("a")*self._get_value("J"))
2121        self._start_simplification_process("Jdot", cse, simplify)
2122        
2123        self._set_value_as_process("Vbd", lambda: self._get_value(
2124            "J")*q2d - A*self._get_value("a")*self._get_value("V"))
2125
2126        for i in range(self.n_ee):
2127            # Hybrid acceleration of the last body
2128            self._set_value_as_process(
2129                f"Vbd_BFn{i}", lambda: self._get_value("Vbd")[6*(self.ee_parent[i]-1):6*self.ee_parent[i], :])
2130
2131            self._start_simplification_process(f"Vbd_BFn{i}", cse, simplify)
2132            
2133            # Hybrid twist of end-effector frame
2134            self._set_value_as_process(
2135                f"Vhd_BFn{i}", 
2136                lambda: 
2137                    SE3AdjMatrix(self._get_value(f"R_BFn{i}"))
2138                    * self._get_value(f"Vbd_BFn{i}") 
2139                    + SE3adMatrix(Matrix(self._get_value(f"Vh_BFn{i}")[:3, :])
2140                                    .col_join(Matrix([0, 0, 0])))
2141                    * SE3AdjMatrix(self._get_value(f"R_BFn{i}"))
2142                    * self._get_value(f"Vb_BFn{i}")
2143                )
2144
2145            self._start_simplification_process(f"Vhd_BFn{i}", cse, simplify)
2146            
2147            # Body fixed twist of end-effector frame
2148            # Hybrid acceleration of the EE
2149            self._set_value_as_process(f"Vbd_ee{i}", lambda: SE3AdjMatrix(
2150                SE3Inv(self.ee[i]))*self._get_value(f"Vbd_BFn{i}"))
2151            self._start_simplification_process(f"Vbd_ee{i}", cse, simplify)
2152            
2153            # Hybrid twist of end-effector frame
2154            self._set_value_as_process(
2155                f"Vhd_ee{i}", 
2156                lambda: 
2157                    SE3AdjMatrix(self._get_value(f"R_i{i}")) 
2158                    * self._get_value(f"Vbd_ee{i}") 
2159                    + SE3adMatrix(Matrix(self._get_value(f"Vh_ee{i}")[:3, :])
2160                                    .col_join(Matrix([0, 0, 0])))
2161                    * SE3AdjMatrix(self._get_value(f"R_i{i}"))
2162                    * self._get_value(f"Vb_ee{i}")
2163                )  # Hybrid twist of end-effector frame
2164
2165            self._start_simplification_process(f"Vhd_ee{i}", cse, simplify)
2166            
2167            # Body Jacobian time derivative
2168
2169            # For the last moving body
2170            self._set_value_as_process(
2171                f"Jb_dot{i}", lambda: self._get_value("Jdot")[6*(self.ee_parent[i]-1):6*self.ee_parent[i], :])
2172
2173            # For the EE
2174            self._set_value_as_process(f"Jb_ee_dot{i}", lambda: SE3AdjMatrix(
2175                SE3Inv(self.ee[i]))*self._get_value(f"Jb_dot{i}"))
2176            self._start_simplification_process(f"Jb_ee_dot{i}", cse, simplify)
2177            
2178            # Hybrid Jacobian time derivative
2179            # For the last moving body
2180            self._set_value_as_process(
2181                f"Jh_dot{i}", 
2182                lambda: 
2183                    SE3AdjMatrix(self._get_value(f"R_BFn{i}"))
2184                    * self._get_value(f"Jb_dot{i}") 
2185                    + SE3adMatrix(Matrix(self._get_value(f"Vh_BFn{i}")[:3, :])
2186                                    .col_join(Matrix([0, 0, 0])))
2187                    * SE3AdjMatrix(self._get_value(f"R_BFn{i}"))
2188                    * self._get_value(f"Jb{i}")
2189                )
2190            self._start_simplification_process(f"Jh_dot{i}", cse, simplify)
2191            
2192            # For the EE
2193            self._set_value_as_process(
2194                f"Jh_ee_dot{i}", 
2195                lambda: 
2196                    SE3AdjMatrix(self._get_value(f"R_i{i}"))
2197                    * self._get_value(f"Jb_ee_dot{i}") 
2198                    + SE3adMatrix(Matrix(self._get_value(f"Vh_ee{i}")[:3, :])
2199                                    .col_join(Matrix([0, 0, 0])))
2200                    * SE3AdjMatrix(self._get_value(f"R_i{i}"))
2201                    * self._get_value(f"Jb_ee{i}")
2202                )
2203            self._start_simplification_process(f"Jh_ee_dot{i}", cse, simplify)
2204            
2205        self._a = self._get_value("a")
2206        self._V = self._get_value("V")
2207
2208        # variables for Code Generation:
2209        self.J = self._get_value("J")
2210        self.Jdot = self._get_value("Jdot")
2211        self.fkin = [self._get_value(f"fkin{i}") for i in range(self.n_ee)]
2212        self.Jb = [self._get_value(f"Jb{i}") for i in range(self.n_ee)]
2213        self.Jh = [self._get_value(f"Jh{i}") for i in range(self.n_ee)]
2214        self.Vb_ee = [self._get_value(f"Vb_ee{i}") for i in range(self.n_ee)]
2215        self.Vh_ee = [self._get_value(f"Vh_ee{i}") for i in range(self.n_ee)]
2216        self.Jb_ee = [self._get_value(f"Jb_ee{i}") for i in range(self.n_ee)]
2217        self.Jh_ee = [self._get_value(f"Jh_ee{i}") for i in range(self.n_ee)]
2218        self.Vh_BFn = [self._get_value(f"Vh_BFn{i}") for i in range(self.n_ee)]
2219        self.Vb_BFn = [self._get_value(f"Vb_BFn{i}") for i in range(self.n_ee)]
2220        self.Vhd_BFn = [self._get_value(f"Vhd_BFn{i}") for i in range(self.n_ee)]
2221        self.Vbd_BFn = [self._get_value(f"Vbd_BFn{i}") for i in range(self.n_ee)]
2222        self.Vhd_ee = [self._get_value(f"Vhd_ee{i}") for i in range(self.n_ee)]
2223        self.Vbd_ee = [self._get_value(f"Vbd_ee{i}") for i in range(self.n_ee)]
2224        self.Jh_dot = [self._get_value(f"Jh_dot{i}") for i in range(self.n_ee)]
2225        self.Jb_dot = [self._get_value(f"Jb_dot{i}") for i in range(self.n_ee)]
2226        self.Jh_ee_dot = [self._get_value(f"Jh_ee_dot{i}") for i in range(self.n_ee)]
2227        self.Jb_ee_dot = [self._get_value(f"Jb_ee_dot{i}") for i in range(self.n_ee)]
2228
2229        if self.n_ee == 1:
2230            self.fkin = self.fkin[0] 
2231            self.Jb = self.Jb[0] 
2232            self.Jh = self.Jh[0] 
2233            self.Vb_ee = self.Vb_ee[0] 
2234            self.Vh_ee = self.Vh_ee[0] 
2235            self.Jb_ee = self.Jb_ee[0] 
2236            self.Jh_ee = self.Jh_ee[0] 
2237            self.Vh_BFn = self.Vh_BFn[0] 
2238            self.Vb_BFn = self.Vb_BFn[0] 
2239            self.Vhd_BFn = self.Vhd_BFn[0] 
2240            self.Vbd_BFn = self.Vbd_BFn[0] 
2241            self.Vhd_ee = self.Vhd_ee[0] 
2242            self.Vbd_ee = self.Vbd_ee[0] 
2243            self.Jh_dot = self.Jh_dot[0] 
2244            self.Jb_dot = self.Jb_dot[0] 
2245            self.Jh_ee_dot = self.Jh_ee_dot[0] 
2246            self.Jb_ee_dot = self.Jb_ee_dot[0] 
2247        
2248        try:
2249            while True:
2250                self.subex_dict.update(
2251                    self.queue_dict["subex_dict"].get(timeout=0.05))
2252        except queue.Empty:
2253            pass
2254
2255        # empty Queues
2256        for i in self.queue_dict:
2257            self._flush_queue(self.queue_dict[i])
2258        self.queue_dict = {}
2259
2260        # join Processes
2261        for i in self.process_dict:
2262            self.process_dict[i].join()
2263        self.process_dict = {}
2264
2265        # save used symbols
2266        for e in self._get_expressions():
2267            self.all_symbols.update(e.free_symbols)
2268
2269        print("Done")
2270        return self.fkin
2271
2272    def _closed_form_inv_dyn_body_fixed_parallel(
2273        self, 
2274        q: MutableDenseMatrix, 
2275        qd: MutableDenseMatrix, 
2276        q2d: MutableDenseMatrix, 
2277        q3d: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix]=None, 
2278        q4d: Optional[MutableDenseMatrix]=None, 
2279        WEE: list[MutableDenseMatrix]=[zeros(6, 1)], 
2280        WDEE: list[MutableDenseMatrix]=[zeros(6, 1)], 
2281        W2DEE: list[MutableDenseMatrix]=[zeros(6, 1)], 
2282        simplify: bool=True, cse: bool=False) -> MutableDenseMatrix:
2283        """Inverse dynamics using body fixed representation of the 
2284        twists in closed form. 
2285
2286        The following expressions are saved in the class and can be 
2287        code generated afterwards:
2288            coriolis_centrifugal_matrix
2289            generalized_mass_inertia_matrix
2290            gravity_vector
2291            inverse_dynamics
2292
2293        Args:
2294            q (sympy.Matrix): 
2295                (n,1) Generalized position vector.
2296            qd (sympy.Matrix): 
2297                (n,1 )Generalized velocity vector.
2298            q2d (sympy.Matrix): 
2299                (n,1) Generalized acceleration vector.
2300            q3d (sympy.Matrix, optional): 
2301                (n,1) Generalized jerk vector. Defaults to None.
2302            q4d (sympy.Matrix, optional): 
2303                (n,1) Generalized jounce vector. Defaults to None.
2304            WEE (list of sympy.Matrix, optional): 
2305                (6,1) WEE (t) = [Mx,My,Mz,Fx,Fy,Fz] is the time varying 
2306                wrench on the EE link. 
2307                Defaults to [zeros(6, 1)].
2308            WDEE (list of sympy.Matrix, optional): 
2309                (6,1) WDEE (t) = [dMx,dMy,dMz,dFx,dFy,dFz] is the derivative 
2310                of the time varying wrench on the EE link. 
2311                Defaults to [zeros(6, 1)].
2312            W2DEE (list of sympy.Matrix, optional): 
2313                (6,1) W2DEE (t) = [ddMx,ddMy,ddMz,ddFx,ddFy,ddFz] is the 
2314                2nd derivative of the time varying wrench on the EE link. 
2315                Defaults to [zeros(6, 1)].
2316            simplify (bool, optional): 
2317                Use simplify command on saved expressions. 
2318                Defaults to True.
2319            cse (bool, optional): 
2320                Use common subexpression elimination. Defaults to False.
2321
2322        Returns:
2323            sympy.Matrix: Generalized Forces
2324        """
2325        # This method does the same as _closed_form_inv_dyn_body_fixed.
2326        # Parallel computation is implemented by writing most values 
2327        # in queues, organized in a dict.
2328        # This ensures the correct order for the execution.
2329        # To understand the calculations it is recommended to read the 
2330        # code in _closed_form_inv_dyn_body_fixed since it is more 
2331        # readable and has the same structure.
2332
2333        print("Inverse dynamics calculation")
2334
2335        self.var_syms.update(q.free_symbols)
2336        self.var_syms.update(qd.free_symbols)
2337        self.var_syms.update(q2d.free_symbols)
2338        if q3d: self.var_syms.update(q3d.free_symbols)
2339        if q4d: self.var_syms.update(q4d.free_symbols)
2340        for W in WEE:
2341            self.optional_var_syms.update(W.free_symbols)
2342        for WD in WDEE:
2343            self.optional_var_syms.update(WD.free_symbols)
2344        for W2D in W2DEE:
2345            self.optional_var_syms.update(W2D.free_symbols)
2346        
2347        self.n = len(q)
2348        self.queue_dict["subex_dict"] = Queue()
2349
2350        # calc Forward kinematics
2351        if self.parent and self.support:
2352            FK_C, A = self._calc_A_matrix_tree(q)
2353        else:    
2354            FK_C, A = self._calc_A_matrix(q)
2355        
2356        if self.J is not None:
2357            self._set_value("J", self.J)
2358            self._set_value("V", self._V)
2359        else:
2360            # Block diagonal matrix X (6n x n) of the screw coordinate 
2361            # vector associated to all joints in the body frame (Constant)
2362            X = zeros(6*self.n, self.n)
2363            for i in range(self.n):
2364                X[6*i:6*i+6, i] = self.X[i]
2365
2366            # System level Jacobian
2367            self._set_value("J", A*X)
2368            self._start_simplification_process("J", cse, simplify)
2369            
2370            # System twist (6n x 1)
2371            self._set_value_as_process("V", lambda: self._get_value("J")*qd)
2372
2373        # Acceleration computations
2374
2375        if self._a is not None:
2376            a = self._a
2377        else:
2378            # Block diagonal matrix a (6n x 6n)
2379            a = zeros(6*self.n, 6*self.n)
2380            for i in range(self.n):
2381                a[6*i:6*i+6, 6*i:6*i+6] = SE3adMatrix(self.X[i])*qd[i]
2382            self._a = a
2383
2384        # System acceleration (6n x 1)
2385        # Vd = J*q2d - A*a*V
2386        self._set_value_as_process("Vd", lambda: self._get_value(
2387            "J")*q2d - A*a*self._get_value("V"))
2388
2389        # Block Diagonal Mb (6n x 6n) Mass inertia matrix in body frame 
2390        # (Constant)
2391        Mb = zeros(6*self.n, 6*self.n)
2392        for i in range(self.n):
2393            Mb[i*6:i*6+6, i*6:i*6+6] = self.Mb[i]
2394
2395        # Block diagonal matrix b (6n x 6n) used in Coriolis matrix
2396        def _b() -> MutableDenseMatrix:
2397            nonlocal self
2398            b = zeros(6*self.n, 6*self.n)
2399            for i in range(self.n):
2400                b[i*6:i*6+6, i*6:i*6 + 6] = SE3adMatrix(
2401                    Matrix(self._get_value("V")[6*i:6*i+6]))
2402            return b
2403        self._set_value_as_process("b", _b)
2404
2405        # Block diagonal matrix Cb (6n x 6n)
2406        self._set_value_as_process(
2407            "Cb", lambda: -Mb*A*a - self._get_value("b").T * Mb)
2408
2409        # Lets setup the Equations of Motion
2410
2411        # Mass inertia matrix in joint space (n x n)
2412        self._set_value_as_process(
2413            "M", lambda: self._get_value("J").T*Mb*self._get_value("J"))
2414        self._start_simplification_process("M", cse, simplify)
2415        
2416        # Coriolis-Centrifugal matrix in joint space (n x n)
2417        self._set_value_as_process("C", lambda: self._get_value(
2418            "J").T*self._get_value("Cb")*self._get_value("J"))
2419        self._start_simplification_process("C", cse, simplify)
2420        
2421        # Gravity Term
2422        U = SE3AdjInvMatrix(FK_C[0])
2423        for k in range(1, self.n):
2424            U = U.col_join(SE3AdjInvMatrix(FK_C[k]))
2425
2426        Vd_0 = zeros(6, 1)
2427        Vd_0[3:6, 0] = -Matrix(self.gravity_vector)
2428        self._set_value_as_process(
2429            "Qgrav", lambda: self._get_value("J").T*Mb*U*Vd_0)
2430        self._start_simplification_process("Qgrav", cse, simplify)
2431        
2432        # External Wrench
2433        Wext = zeros(6*self.n, 1)
2434        # WEE (t) is the time varying wrench on the EE link.
2435        for i in range(self.n_ee):
2436                Wext[6*(self.ee_parent[i]-1):6*self.ee_parent[i], 0] = WEE[i if len(WEE) == self.n_ee else 0]
2437        self._set_value_as_process(
2438            "Qext", lambda: self._get_value("J").T * Wext)
2439
2440        # Generalized forces Q
2441        self._set_value_as_process(
2442            "Q", 
2443            lambda: 
2444                self._get_value("M") * q2d 
2445                + self._get_value("C") * qd 
2446                + self._get_value("Qgrav") 
2447                + self._get_value("Qext")
2448            )
2449
2450        self._start_simplification_process("Q", cse, simplify)
2451        
2452        # Regressor matrix for standard inertial parameter identification, Q = Y*X in SE(3)
2453        # mass-inertia parameter vector X         
2454        # m, m*c, m*cy, m*cz, Ixx, Ixy, Ixz, Iyy, Iyz, Izz        
2455        Xr = Matrix([value for i in self.Mb for value in mass_matrix_to_parameter_vector(i)])
2456        
2457        if not any([i.is_Float for i in Xr]):
2458        
2459        
2460            def _Yr() -> MutableDenseMatrix:
2461                nonlocal self
2462                S = Matrix(Identity(len(Xr)))
2463                
2464                # Regressor matrix Y   
2465                Yr = zeros(self.n, len(Xr))
2466                for i in range(self.n):
2467                    for j in range(len(Xr)):
2468                        Yr[i,j] = self.collect_and_subs(self._get_value("Q")[i], {k: v for k, v in zip(Xr, S[j,:]) if k not in {0,1}})
2469                return Yr
2470            
2471            self._set_value_as_process("Yr", _Yr)
2472            self._start_simplification_process("Yr", cse, simplify)
2473        
2474            self.Xr = Xr
2475
2476        
2477        ##### First Order Derivatives of EOM #####
2478        if q3d is not None:
2479            # First time derivative of Block diagonal matrix a (6n x 6n)
2480            ad = zeros(6*self.n, 6*self.n)
2481            for i in range(self.n):
2482                ad[i*6:i*6+6, i*6:i*6+6] = q2d[i] * SE3adMatrix(self.X[i])
2483
2484            # Third order Forward Kinematics
2485            self._set_value_as_process(
2486                "V2d", 
2487                lambda: self._get_value("J")*q3d - A*ad*self._get_value("V")
2488                - 2*A*a*self._get_value("Vd") - A*a*a*self._get_value("V"))
2489                        
2490            #  First time derivative of Block diagonal matrix b (6n x 6n) 
2491            # used in Coriolis matrix
2492            def _bd() -> MutableDenseMatrix:
2493                nonlocal self
2494                bd = zeros(6*self.n, 6*self.n)
2495                for i in range(self.n):
2496                    bd[i*6:i*6+6, i*6:i*6+6] = SE3adMatrix(Matrix(self._get_value("Vd")[i*6:i*6+6]))
2497                return bd
2498            self._set_value_as_process("bd", _bd)
2499            
2500            # First time derivative of Mass inertia matrix in joint space (n x n)
2501            Mbd = -Mb*A*a - (Mb*A*a).T
2502            self._set_value_as_process(
2503                "Md",
2504                lambda: self._get_value("J").T * Mbd * self._get_value("J"))
2505            self._start_simplification_process("Md", cse, simplify)
2506            
2507            # First time derivative of Coriolis-Centrifugal matrix in joint space (n x n)
2508            self._set_value_as_process(
2509                "Cbd",
2510                lambda: Mb*A*a*A*a - Mb*A*a*a - Mb*A*ad - self._get_value("bd").T * Mb 
2511                        - self._get_value("Cb")*A*a - a.T*A.T*self._get_value("Cb"))
2512            self._set_value_as_process(
2513                "Cd", 
2514                lambda: self._get_value("J").T*self._get_value("Cbd")*self._get_value("J"))
2515            self._start_simplification_process("Cd", cse, simplify)
2516            
2517            # First time derivative of gravity force
2518            self._set_value_as_process(
2519                "Qdgrav",
2520                lambda: self._get_value("J").T*Mbd*U*Vd_0)
2521            self._start_simplification_process("Qdgrav", cse, simplify)
2522            
2523            # First time derivative of External Wrench
2524            Wdext = zeros(6*self.n,1)
2525            for i in range(self.n_ee):
2526                Wdext[6*(self.ee_parent[i]-1):6*self.ee_parent[i], 0] = WDEE[i if len(WDEE) == self.n_ee else 0]
2527            self._set_value_as_process(
2528                "Qdext",
2529                lambda: self._get_value("J").T*(Wdext - (A*a).T * Wext))
2530            
2531            self._set_value_as_process(
2532                "Qd",
2533                lambda: self._get_value("M")*q3d 
2534                        + (self._get_value("Md") + self._get_value("C"))*q2d 
2535                        + self._get_value("Cd")*qd + self._get_value("Qdgrav") 
2536                        + self._get_value("Qdext")
2537            )
2538            self._start_simplification_process("Qd", cse, simplify)
2539            
2540        ##### Second Order Derivatives of EOM #####
2541        if q3d is not None and q4d is not None:        
2542            # Second time derivative of Block diagonal matrix a (6n x 6n)
2543            a2d = zeros(6*self.n, 6*self.n)
2544            for i in range(self.n):
2545                a2d[i*6:i*6+6, i*6:i*6+6] = SE3adMatrix(self.X[i]) * q3d[i]
2546                
2547            # Second time derivative of Block diagonal matrix b (6n x 6n) 
2548            # used in Coriolis matrix
2549            def _b2d() -> MutableDenseMatrix:
2550                nonlocal self
2551                b2d = zeros(6*self.n, 6*self.n)
2552                for i in range(self.n):
2553                    b2d[i*6:i*6+6, i*6:i*6+6] = SE3adMatrix(
2554                        Matrix(self._get_value("V2d")[i*6:i*6+6]))
2555                return b2d
2556            self._set_value_as_process("b2d", _b2d)
2557                
2558            # Second time derivative of Mass inertia matrix in joint space (n x n)
2559            Mb2d = (- Mb*A*ad - (Mb*A*ad).T + 2*Mb*A*a*A*a + 2*(Mb*A*a*A*a).T
