2560                    + 2*a.T*A.T*Mb*A*a - Mb*A*a*a - (Mb*A*a*a).T)
2561            self._set_value_as_process(
2562                "M2d",
2563                lambda: self._get_value("J").T*Mb2d*self._get_value("J"))
2564            self._start_simplification_process("M2d", cse, simplify)
2565            
2566            # Second time derivative of Coriolis-Centrifugal matrix in joint space (n x n)
2567            self._set_value_as_process(
2568                "Cddot",
2569                lambda: - Mb*A*a2d - 3*Mb*A*a*ad - Mb*A*a*a*a 
2570                        - self._get_value("b2d").T*Mb 
2571                        + Mb*A*ad*A*a + Mb*A*a*a*A*a + 2*Mb*A*a*A*ad 
2572                        + 2*Mb*A*a*A*a*a - 2*Mb*A*a*A*a*A*a
2573            )
2574            self._set_value_as_process(
2575                "Cb2d",
2576                lambda: self._get_value("Cddot") 
2577                        - (self._get_value("Cbd") + a.T*A.T*self._get_value("Cb"))*A*a 
2578                        - a.T*A.T*(self._get_value("Cbd") + self._get_value("Cb")*A*a) 
2579                        - self._get_value("Cb")*A*ad - ad.T*A.T*self._get_value("Cb") 
2580                        - self._get_value("Cb")*A*a*a - a.T*a.T*A.T*self._get_value("Cb") 
2581                        - self._get_value("Cbd")*A*a - a.T*A.T*self._get_value("Cbd")
2582            )
2583            self._set_value_as_process(
2584                "C2d",
2585                lambda: self._get_value("J").T*self._get_value("Cb2d")*self._get_value("J")
2586            )
2587            self._start_simplification_process("C2d", cse, simplify)
2588            
2589            # Second time derivative of gravity force
2590            self._set_value_as_process(
2591                "Q2dgrav",
2592                lambda: self._get_value("J").T*Mb2d*U*Vd_0
2593            )
2594            self._start_simplification_process("Q2dgrav", cse, simplify)
2595            
2596            # Second time derivative of External Wrench
2597            W2dext = zeros(6*self.n,1)
2598            for i in range(self.n_ee):
2599                W2dext[6*(self.ee_parent[i]-1):6*self.ee_parent[i], 0] = W2DEE[i if len(W2DEE) == self.n_ee else 0]
2600            self._set_value_as_process(
2601                "Q2dext",
2602                lambda: self._get_value("J").T
2603                        * (W2dext - 2*(A*a).T*Wdext + (2*(A*a*A*a).T - (A*ad).T - (A*a*a).T)*Wext) 
2604            )
2605            
2606            # Second time derivative of generalized forces
2607            # with gravity and external forces:
2608            self._set_value_as_process(
2609                "Q2d",
2610                lambda: self._get_value("M")*q4d 
2611                        + (2*self._get_value("Md") + self._get_value("C"))*q3d 
2612                        + (self._get_value("M2d") + 2*self._get_value("Cd"))*q2d 
2613                        + self._get_value("C2d")*qd 
2614                        + self._get_value("Q2dgrav") 
2615                        + self._get_value("Q2dext") 
2616            )
2617            self._start_simplification_process("Q2d", cse, simplify)
2618            
2619
2620        self._V = self._get_value("V")
2621        self.J = self._get_value("J")
2622        self.M = self._get_value("M")
2623        self.C = self._get_value("C")
2624        self.Qgrav = self._get_value("Qgrav")
2625        self.Q = self._get_value("Q")
2626        if self.Xr is not None:
2627            self.Yr = self._get_value("Yr")    
2628        if q3d is not None:
2629            self.Md = self._get_value("Md")
2630            self.Cd = self._get_value("Cd")
2631            self.Qdgrav = self._get_value("Qdgrav")
2632            self.Qd = self._get_value("Qd")
2633        if q3d is not None and q4d is not None:
2634            self.M2d = self._get_value("M2d")
2635            self.C2d = self._get_value("C2d")
2636            self.Q2dgrav = self._get_value("Q2dgrav")
2637            self.Q2d = self._get_value("Q2d")
2638
2639        try:
2640            while True:
2641                self.subex_dict.update(
2642                    self.queue_dict["subex_dict"].get(timeout=0.05))
2643        except queue.Empty:
2644            pass
2645
2646        # empty Queues
2647        for i in self.queue_dict:
2648            self._flush_queue(self.queue_dict[i])
2649        self.queue_dict = {}
2650
2651        # join Processes
2652        for i in self.process_dict:
2653            self.process_dict[i].join()
2654        self.process_dict = {}
2655
2656        # save used symbols
2657        for e in self._get_expressions():
2658            self.all_symbols.update(e.free_symbols)
2659
2660        print("Done")
2661        return self.Q
2662
2663    def partial_factor(self, exp: sympy.Expr) -> sympy.Expr:
2664        """Partial factor simplification for sympy expression.
2665
2666        Args:
2667            exp (sympy.Expr): sympy expression.
2668
2669        Returns:
2670            sympy.Expr: modified sympy expression.
2671        """
2672        # split up matrices
2673        if (type(exp) == sympy.matrices.immutable.ImmutableDenseMatrix
2674            or type(exp) == sympy.matrices.dense.MutableDenseMatrix):
2675            new_expr = zeros(*exp.shape)
2676            for i in range(exp.shape[0]):
2677                for j in range(exp.shape[1]):
2678                    new_expr[i,j] = self.partial_factor(exp[i,j])
2679            return new_expr
2680            
2681        # seach for factors
2682        factor_map = defaultdict(set)
2683        const, additive_terms = exp.as_coeff_add()
2684        for term1, term2 in combinations(additive_terms, 2):
2685            common_terms = (
2686                set(term1.as_coeff_mul()[-1])
2687                & set(term2.as_coeff_mul()[-1])
2688            )
2689            if common_terms:
2690                common_factor = sympy.Mul(*common_terms)
2691                factor_map[common_factor] |= {term1, term2}
2692        
2693        # sort by number of operations represented by the terms
2694        factor_list = sorted(
2695            factor_map.items(),
2696            key = lambda i: (i[0].count_ops() + 1) * len(i[1])
2697        )[::-1]
2698
2699        # rebuild expression
2700        used = set()
2701        new_expr = nsimplify(0)
2702        for item in factor_list:
2703            factor = item[0]
2704            appearances = item[-1]
2705            terms = 0
2706            for instance in appearances:
2707                if instance not in used:
2708                    terms += instance.as_coefficient(factor)
2709                    used.add(instance)
2710            new_expr += factor * terms
2711        for term in set(additive_terms) - used:
2712            new_expr += term
2713        return new_expr + const
2714
2715    def collect_and_subs(self, ex: sympy.Expr, terms: dict) -> sympy.Expr:
2716        for key in terms:
2717            if key.is_Atom:
2718                ex = ex.subs(key,terms[key])
2719            else:
2720                ex = ex.expand().collect(key).subs(key,terms[key])
2721        return ex
2722    
2723    def simplify(self, exp: sympy.Expr, cse: bool=False, simplify: bool=True) -> sympy.Expr:
2724        """Faster simplify implementation for sympy expressions.
2725        Expressions can be different simplified as with sympy.simplify.
2726
2727        Args:
2728            exp (sympy expression): 
2729                Expression to simplify.
2730            cse (bool, optional): 
2731                Use common subexpression elimination. Defaults to False.
2732            simplify (bool, optional): 
2733                deactivate simplification by setting simplify to False. 
2734                Defaults to True.
2735
2736        Returns:
2737            sympy expression: Simplified expression.
2738        """
2739        if cse:
2740            exp = self._cse_expression(exp)
2741        if simplify:
2742            if (type(exp) == sympy.matrices.immutable.ImmutableDenseMatrix
2743                    or type(exp) == sympy.matrices.dense.MutableDenseMatrix):
2744                # fasten simplification of symmetric matrices
2745                if exp.is_square:
2746                    # test if matrix is symmetric
2747                    # numeric test is faster than is_symmetric method  for 
2748                    # long expressions
2749                    
2750                    # create matrix with randon values
2751                    num = lambdify(list(exp.free_symbols), exp, "numpy")(
2752                        *(random.random() for i in exp.free_symbols))
2753                    # if (random) matrix is symmetric, we have to simplify 
2754                    # less values
2755                    if numpy.allclose(num, num.T):
2756                        shape = exp.shape
2757                        m_exp = exp.as_mutable()
2758                        # simplify values only once in symmetric matrices
2759                        for i in range(shape[0]):
2760                            for j in range(i):
2761                                m_exp[i, j] = self.simplify(exp[i, j])
2762                                if i != j:
2763                                    m_exp[j, i] = exp[j, i]
2764                        return Matrix(m_exp)
2765            if type(exp) == sympy.matrices.dense.MutableDenseMatrix:
2766                exp = exp.as_immutable()
2767            exp = fu(exp)  # fast function to simplify sin and cos expressions
2768            exp = cancel(exp)
2769            exp = factor(exp)
2770            exp = powsimp(exp)
2771            exp = self.partial_factor(exp)
2772            exp = exp.doit()
2773        return exp
2774
2775    def _create_topology_lists(self,robot: URDF) -> None:
2776        """Generate parent, support and child list from URDF.
2777
2778        Args:
2779            robot (URDF): URDF of robot.
2780        """
2781        # names of all links in urdf
2782        link_names = [link.name for link in robot.links] 
2783        parent_names = [] # names of parent links corresponding link_names
2784        connection_type = [] # 0 for fixed, None for base, 1 else
2785        body_index = [] # index of link; -1 for fixed links
2786        parent = [] # parent array
2787        child = [] # child array
2788        support = [] # support array
2789        # find parent link names and search for fixed joints
2790        for name in link_names:
2791            for joint in robot.joints:
2792                if joint.child == name:
2793                    parent_names.append(joint.parent)
2794                    body_index.append(None) # specify later
2795                    if joint.joint_type == "fixed":
2796                        connection_type.append(0)
2797                    else:
2798                        connection_type.append(1)
2799                    break
2800            else: # base link
2801                parent_names.append(None)
2802                connection_type.append(None)
2803                body_index.append(0)
2804
2805        # generate body indices concatenating fixed bodies
2806        while None in body_index:
2807            i1 = body_index.index(None) # i of current link
2808            # update until parent is already specified
2809            while body_index[link_names.index(parent_names[i1])] is None:
2810                i1 = link_names.index(parent_names[i1])
2811            # fixed links get index -1
2812            if connection_type[i1] == 0:
2813                body_index[i1] = -1
2814                continue
2815            i2 = link_names.index(parent_names[i1]) # i of parent link
2816            while body_index[i2] == -1: # find forst non fixed parent
2817                i2 = link_names.index(parent_names[i2])
2818            index = body_index[i2]+1 # body index
2819            while index in body_index: # find first unused index
2820                index+=1
2821            body_index[i1] = index
2822            
2823        parent = [None for _ in range(max(body_index))] 
2824        child = [[] for _ in range(max(body_index))]
2825        support = [[] for _ in range(max(body_index))]
2826
2827        # fill parent, child and support array
2828        for i in range(len(body_index)):
2829            idx = body_index[i] # get index of current body
2830            if idx <= 0: # ignore base and fixed bodys
2831                continue
2832            i1 = link_names.index(parent_names[i]) # parent index
2833            while body_index[i1] == -1: # find first non fixed parent
2834                i1 = link_names.index(parent_names[i1])
2835            parent[idx-1] = body_index[i1] # save parent index
2836            if body_index[i1] > 0: # ignore base
2837                child[body_index[i1]-1].append(idx) # save child to parent
2838            i2 = i
2839            while body_index[i2] != 0: # save all indices in support path
2840                if  body_index[i2] > 0: # ignore fixed links
2841                    support[idx-1].append(body_index[i2])
2842                i2 = link_names.index(parent_names[i2])
2843            support[idx-1].reverse()
2844        self.support = support
2845        self.child = child
2846        self.parent = parent
2847            
2848    def _nsimplify(
2849        self, num: float, *args, max_denominator: int=0, tolerance: Optional[float]=None, **kwargs
2850        ) -> sympy.Expr | float:
2851        """Find a simple sympy representation for a number like 1/2 
2852        instead of 0.5. This function extends sympy.nsimplify with a 
2853        parameter to specify a maximum denominator to avoid simplifications
2854        like 13/157.  
2855
2856        Args:
2857            num (float): number to simplify.
2858            max_denominator (int, optional): 
2859                maximum denominator to use. Use 0 to deactivate. 
2860                Defaults to 0.
2861            tolerance (float, optional): 
2862                tolerance for simplify_numbers. Defaults to 0.0001.
2863            
2864        Returns:
2865            sympy.Expr | float: simplified number.
2866        """
2867        if tolerance:
2868            if numpy.abs(num) < tolerance:
2869                return 0
2870            elif numpy.abs(1-num) < tolerance:
2871                return 1
2872            elif numpy.abs(-1-num) < tolerance:
2873                return -1 
2874        ex = nsimplify(num,*args, rational=False, tolerance=tolerance, **kwargs)
2875        if not max_denominator:
2876            return ex
2877        if ex.is_rational:
2878            try:
2879                try:
2880                    d = ex.denominator()
2881                except TypeError:
2882                    d = ex.denominator 
2883                if d > max_denominator:
2884                    return num    
2885            except ValueError:
2886                return ex
2887        elif type(ex) in {sympy.core.add.Add, sympy.core.power.Pow}:
2888            return num
2889        for i in regex.findall("(?<=Rational\(\d*, )\d*", sympy.srepr(ex)):
2890            if abs(int(i)) > max_denominator:
2891                return num
2892        return ex
2893        
2894    def load_from_urdf(self, path: str, symbolic: bool=False, 
2895                       cse: bool=False, simplify_numbers: bool=True,  
2896                       tolerance: float=0.0001, max_denominator: int=9) -> None:
2897        """Load robot from urdf.
2898
2899        Args:
2900            path (str): path to URDF.
2901            symbolic (bool, optional): 
2902                generate symbols for numeric values. 
2903                Defaults to False.
2904            cse (bool, optional): 
2905                use common subexpression elimination. Defaults to False.
2906            simplify_numbers (bool, optional): 
2907                Use eg. pi/2 instead of 1.5708. Defaults to True.
2908            tolerance (float, optional): 
2909                tolerance for simplify_numbers. Defaults to 0.0001.
2910            max_denominator (int, optional): 
2911                Maximum denominator to use for simplify numbers to avoid
2912                values like 13/153. Use 0 to deactivate. Defaults to 9.
2913
2914        Raises:
2915            NotImplementedError: supports only the joint types 
2916                "revolute", "continuous" and "prismatic".
2917        """        
2918        # load URDF
2919        robot = URDF.from_xml_file(path)
2920        
2921        self.config_representation = self.BODY_FIXED
2922        self.B = []
2923        self.X = []
2924        
2925        # get parent, child and support array
2926        self._create_topology_lists(robot)
2927        # init some variables for later
2928        fixed_origin = None
2929        fixed_links = []
2930        DOF = 0
2931        xyz_rpy_syms = []
2932        
2933        # count DOF
2934        for joint in robot.joints:
2935            if joint.joint_type in ["revolute", "continuous", "prismatic"]:
2936                DOF += 1
2937            elif joint.joint_type in ["fixed"]:
2938                pass
2939            else:
2940                raise NotImplementedError(
2941                    "Joint type '" + joint.joint_type+"' not implemented yet!")
2942
2943        ji = 0  # joint index of used joints
2944        jia = 0  # joint index of all joints (fixed included)
2945        joint_origins = []
2946        joint_origins_dict = {}
2947        for joint in robot.joints:
2948            name = joint.name
2949            
2950            # get SE3 pose from xyzrpy
2951            origin = xyz_rpy_to_matrix(joint.origin.xyz+joint.origin.rpy)
2952            if symbolic:
2953                xyz_rpy = Matrix(joint.origin.xyz+joint.origin.rpy)
2954                # substitute variables
2955                xyz_rpy_syms.append(
2956                    symbols(" ".join([name+"_%s" % s 
2957                                      for s in ["x", "y", "z", "roll", "pitch", "yar"]])))
2958                xyzrpylist = []
2959                if simplify_numbers:
2960                    # replace values like 3.142 with pi
2961                    for i in range(6):
2962                        if (self._nsimplify(xyz_rpy[i], 
2963                                           tolerance=tolerance, 
2964                                           max_denominator=max_denominator) 
2965                            in [0, -1, 1, pi, -pi, pi/2, -pi/2, 3*pi/2, -3*pi/2]
2966                            ):
2967                            xyzrpylist.append(
2968                                self._nsimplify(xyz_rpy[i], tolerance=tolerance,
2969                                                max_denominator=max_denominator))
2970                        else:
2971                            xyzrpylist.append(xyz_rpy_syms[jia][i])
2972                            self.assignment_dict[xyz_rpy_syms[jia]
2973                                                 [i]] = xyz_rpy[i]
2974                else:
2975                    # replace all values unequal 0, abs(1) with symbolic values
2976                    for i in range(6):
2977                        if xyz_rpy[i] == 0:
2978                            xyzrpylist.append(0)
2979                        elif xyz_rpy[i] == 1:
2980                            xyzrpylist.append(1)
2981                        elif xyz_rpy[i] == -1:
2982                            xyzrpylist.append(-1)
2983                        else:
2984                            xyzrpylist.append(xyz_rpy_syms[jia][i])
2985                            self.assignment_dict[xyz_rpy_syms[jia]
2986                                                 [i]] = xyz_rpy[i]
2987                # get new SE3 Pose from xyzrpy
2988                origin = xyz_rpy_to_matrix(xyzrpylist)
2989                if cse:
2990                    origin = self._cse_expression(origin)
2991            elif simplify_numbers:
2992                for i in range(4):
2993                    for j in range(4):
2994                        origin[i, j] = self._nsimplify(
2995                            origin[i, j], [pi], tolerance=tolerance,
2996                            max_denominator=max_denominator)
2997            # save SE3 pose in list
2998            joint_origins.append(origin)
2999            joint_origins_dict[name] = origin
3000            
3001            # add fixed parents to origin
3002            if joint.joint_type in ["revolute", "continuous", "prismatic"]:
3003                axis = Matrix(joint.axis)
3004                
3005                # calc fixed origin from parent origins:
3006                fixed_origin = Matrix(Identity(4))
3007                parent_joint = copy.copy(joint)
3008                while True :
3009                    try:
3010                        parent_joint = robot.joint_map[robot.parent_map[parent_joint.parent][0]]
3011                    except KeyError: # base_link has no parent
3012                        break
3013                    if parent_joint.type == "fixed":
3014                        fixed_origin = joint_origins_dict[parent_joint.name] * fixed_origin
3015                    else: # stop when last non fixed joint is reached
3016                        break
3017
3018                # transform
3019                origin = fixed_origin * origin 
3020                
3021                if simplify_numbers:
3022                    for i in range(3):
3023                        axis[i] = self._nsimplify(axis[i], [pi], tolerance=tolerance,
3024                                            max_denominator=max_denominator)
3025                
3026                self.B.append(Matrix(origin))
3027
3028                if joint.joint_type in ["revolute", "continuous"]:
3029                    self.X.append(Matrix(axis).col_join(Matrix([0, 0, 0])))
3030                else:
3031                    self.X.append(Matrix(Matrix([0, 0, 0])).col_join(axis))
3032                ji += 1
3033            elif joint.joint_type == "fixed":
3034                fixed_links.append((joint.parent, joint.child))
3035            jia += 1
3036
3037        self.Mb = []
3038        i = 0
3039        first_non_fixed = 1
3040        for link in robot.links:
3041            name = link.name
3042            # ignore base link
3043            if i < first_non_fixed:
3044                if name in [x[1] for x in fixed_links]:
3045                    first_non_fixed += 1
3046                i += 1
3047                continue
3048            inertia = Matrix(link.inertial.inertia.to_matrix())
3049            mass = link.inertial.mass
3050            inertiaorigin = xyz_rpy_to_matrix(link.inertial.origin.xyz+link.inertial.origin.rpy)
3051            if symbolic:
3052                I_syms = symbols("Ixx_%s Ixy_%s Ixz_%s Iyy_%s Iyz_%s Izz_%s" % (
3053                    name, name, name, name, name, name))
3054                c_syms = symbols("cx_%s cy_%s cz_%s" % (name, name, name))
3055                I = inertia_matrix(*I_syms)
3056                m = symbols("m_%s" % name)
3057                cg = Matrix([*c_syms])
3058            else:
3059                I = Matrix(inertia)
3060                m = mass
3061                cg = Matrix(inertiaorigin[0:3, 3])
3062            M = mass_matrix_mixed_data(m, I, cg)
3063            # if link is child of fixed joint
3064            if name in [x[1] for x in fixed_links]:
3065                parent_joint = robot.joint_map[robot.parent_map[name][0]]
3066                while True:
3067                    if parent_joint.type == 'fixed':
3068                        M = (SE3AdjInvMatrix(joint_origins_dict[parent_joint.name]).T 
3069                             * M * SE3AdjInvMatrix(joint_origins_dict[parent_joint.name]))
3070                    else:
3071                        break
3072                    try:
3073                        parent_joint = robot.joint_map[robot.parent_map[parent_joint.parent][0]]
3074                    except KeyError:
3075                        break      
3076                # j = i
3077                # # transform Mass matrix
3078                # while robot.links[j].name in [x[1] for x in fixed_links]:
3079                #     M = (SE3AdjInvMatrix(joint_origins[j-1]).T 
3080                #          * M * SE3AdjInvMatrix(joint_origins[j-1]))
3081                #     j -= 1
3082                try:
3083                    self.Mb[-1] += M
3084                except IndexError: # Base dynamics not important
3085                    pass
3086                i += 1
3087                continue
3088            self.Mb.append(M)
3089            i += 1
3090        if simplify_numbers and not symbolic:
3091            for M in self.Mb:
3092                for i in range(6):
3093                    for j in range(6):
3094                        M[i, j] = self._nsimplify(
3095                            M[i, j], [pi], tolerance=tolerance,
3096                            max_denominator=max_denominator)
3097        if self.ee is None:
3098            self.ee = [transformation_matrix()]
3099        if self.gravity_vector is None:
3100            self.gravity_vector = Matrix([0,0,-9.81])
3101        if self.ee_parent is None:
3102            self.ee_parent = DOF
3103        return

3123    def dh_to_screw_coord(self, DH_param_table: MutableDenseMatrix) -> None:
3124        """Build screw coordinate paramters (joint axis frames and 
3125        body reference frames) from a given modified Denavit-Hartenberg 
3126        (DH) parameter table.
3127        Joint screw coordinates and reference configurations of bodies 
3128        are directly applied to class.
3129
3130        Args:
3131            DH_param_table (array_like): 
3132                Table with modified DH parameters (n,5) 
3133                -> (gamma,alpha,d,theta,r)
3134        """
3135        number_of_frames = DH_param_table.shape[0]
3136        self.B = []
3137        self.X = []
3138        for i in range(number_of_frames):
3139            # Reference configurations of bodies (i.e. of body-fixed 
3140            # reference frames) w.r.t their previous bodies
3141            # gamma, alpha, d, theta,r
3142            frame = DH_param_table[i, :]
3143            gamma = frame[0]
3144            alpha = frame[1]
3145            d = frame[2]
3146            theta = frame[3]
3147            r = frame[4]
3148            self.B.append(SO3Exp(Matrix([1, 0, 0]), alpha)
3149                          .row_join(Matrix([d, 0, 0]))
3150                          .col_join(Matrix([0, 0, 0, 1]).T)
3151                          * SO3Exp(Matrix([0, 0, 1]), theta)
3152                          .row_join(Matrix([0, 0, r]))
3153                          .col_join(Matrix([0, 0, 0, 1]).T)
3154                          )
3155
3156            #  Joint screw coordinates in body-fixed representation
3157            if gamma == 0:
3158                self.X.append(Matrix([0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0]))
3159            else:
3160                self.X.append(Matrix([0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1]))

3162    def _set_value_as_process(self, name: str, target: Callable) -> None:
3163        """Set return value of target as value to queue in 
3164        self.queue_dict with identifier name.
3165
3166        Args:
3167            name (str): Identifier.
3168            target (function): function, which returns value. 
3169        """
3170        if name not in self.queue_dict:
3171            self.queue_dict[name] = Queue()
3172        if name in self.process_dict:
3173            print("already there")
3174        self.process_dict[name] = Process(
3175            target=lambda: self._set_value(name, target()), args=(), name=name)
3176        self.process_dict[name].start()

3179        """Set value to queue in self.queue_dict.
3180
3181        Args:
3182            name (str): Identifier.
3183            var (any): Value to save.
3184        """
3185        if name not in self.queue_dict:
3186            self.queue_dict[name] = Queue()
3187        self.queue_dict[name].put(var)

3189    def _start_simplification_process(
3190        self, name: str, cse: bool=False, simplify: bool=True) -> None:
3191        """Start Process, which simplifies and overwrites value in 
3192        queue from self.queue_dict.
3193
3194        Args:
3195            name (str): Identifier
3196            cse (bool, optional): 
3197                Use common subexpression elimination. Defaults to False.
3198            simplify (bool, optional): 
3199                deactivate simplification by setting simplify to False. 
3200                Defaults to True.
3201        """
3202        if not simplify: 
3203            if not cse:
3204                return
3205            else:
3206                self._start_cse_process(name)
3207                return
3208        if name not in self.queue_dict:
3209            self.queue_dict[name] = Queue()
3210        self.process_dict[name+"_simplify"] = Process(
3211            target=self._simplify_parallel, 
3212            args=(name, cse,), 
3213            name=name+"_simplify")
3214        self.process_dict[name+"_simplify"].start()
3215        return
3216
3217    def _start_cse_process(self, name: str) -> None:
3218        """Start Process, which generates cse expression and overwrites value in 
3219        queue from self.queue_dict.
3220
3221        Args:
3222            name (str): Identifier
3223        """
3224        if name not in self.queue_dict:
3225            self.queue_dict[name] = Queue()
3226        self.process_dict[name+"_cse"] = Process(
3227            target=self._cse_parallel, 
3228            args=(name,), 
3229            name=name+"_cse")
3230        self.process_dict[name+"_cse"].start()

3232    def _get_value(self, name: str) -> Any:
3233        """Get value from queue in self.queue_dict and put it in again.
3234
3235        Args:
3236            name (str): Identifier.
3237
3238        Returns:
3239            any: Value
3240        """
3241        value = self.queue_dict[name].get()
3242        self.queue_dict[name].put(value)
3243        return value

3245    def _simplify_parallel(self, name: str, cse: bool=False) -> None:
3246        """Take value from self.queue_dict, simplify it and put it in 
3247        again.
3248
3249        Args:
3250            name (str): Identifier
3251            cse (bool, optional): 
3252                Use common subexpression elimination. Defaults to False.
3253        """
3254        value = self.simplify(self.queue_dict[name].get(), cse)
3255        self.queue_dict[name].put(value)

3257    def _cse_parallel(self, name: str) -> None:
3258        """Take value from self.queue_dict, generate cse_expressions and 
3259        put it in again.
3260
3261        Args:
3262            name (str): Identifier
3263        """
3264        value = self._cse_expression(self.queue_dict[name].get())
3265        self.queue_dict[name].put(value)

3267    def _flush_queue(self, q: Queue) -> None:
3268        """Flush all items in queue
3269
3270        Args:
3271            q (Queue): Queue to flush
3272        """
3273        try:
3274            while True:
3275                q.get(block=False)
3276        except queue.Empty:
3277            pass

3279    def _individual_numbered_symbols(
3280        self, exclude: list=[], i: list[int]=[0]) -> Generator[sympy.Symbol, None, None]:
3281        """create individual symbol names for subexpressions using 
3282        multiprocessing.
3283
3284        Args:
3285            exclude (list, optional): 
3286                List of names, which should not be used. Defaults to [].
3287            i (list, optional): 
3288                List with starting value -1 as first value. Is used as 
3289                counter and should not be set. Defaults to [0].
3290
3291        Returns:
3292            sympy.numbered_symbols:  Symbols
3293        """
3294        i[0] += 1
3295        prefix="sub%s_%s_" % (
3296            "_".join([str(j) for j in multiprocessing.current_process()._identity]), 
3297            i[0]
3298            )
3299        prefix = prefix.replace("sub_","sub0_")
3300        return numbered_symbols(
3301            prefix=prefix, 
3302            exclude=exclude)
3303
3304    def _cse_expression(self, exp: sympy.Expr) -> sympy.Expr:
3305        """Use common subexpression elimination to shorten expression.
3306        The used subexpressions are saved to the class internal 
3307        subex_dict.
3308
3309        Args:
3310            exp (Sympy expression): Expression to shorten using cse.
3311
3312        Returns:
3313            Sympy expression: Shortened expression.
3314        """
3315        # cse expression
3316        r, e = sympy.cse([exp, exp], self._individual_numbered_symbols(
3317            exclude=self.all_symbols), order="canonical", ignore=self.var_syms)
3318        # add subexpressions to dict
3319        for (sym, val) in r:
3320            self.subex_dict[sym] = val
3321            # for multiprocessing save in queue
3322            try:
3323                self.queue_dict["subex_dict"].put(self.subex_dict)
3324            except:
3325                pass
3326            # update used symbols
3327            self.all_symbols.update({sym})
3328        return e[0]
3329
3330    def _get_expressions(self) -> list[sympy.Expr]:
3331        """Get list of all generated expressions.
3332
3333        Returns:
3334            list: generated expressions.
3335        """
3336        expression_dict = self.get_expressions_dict()
3337        expressions = [expression_dict[i] for i in expression_dict]
3338        return expressions

3340    def _calc_A_matrix(
3341        self, q: MutableDenseMatrix
3342        ) -> tuple[list[MutableDenseMatrix], MutableDenseMatrix]:
3343        """Calculate forward kinematics and the block diagonal matrix 
3344        A (6n x 6n) of the Adjoint of body frame for serial robots.
3345
3346        Args:
3347            q (sympy.MutableDenseMatrix): 
3348                Generalized position vector.
3349
3350        Raises:
3351            ValueError: 
3352                Joint screw coordinates or body reference configuration 
3353                not found.
3354
3355        Returns:
3356            tuple[list[MutableDenseMatrix], MutableDenseMatrix]: (FK, A)
3357        """
3358        # calc Forward kinematics
3359        if self._FK_C is not None:
3360            FK_C = self._FK_C
3361        elif self.A:
3362            # print("Using absolute configuration (A) of the body frames")
3363            FK_f = [SE3Exp(self.Y[0], q[0])]
3364            FK_C = [FK_f[0]*self.A[0]]
3365            for i in range(1, self.n):
3366                FK_f.append(FK_f[i-1]*SE3Exp(self.Y[i], q[i]))
3367                FK_C.append(FK_f[i]*self.A[i])
3368            self._FK_C = FK_C
3369            if not self.X:
3370                # Joint screw coordinates in body-fixed representation 
3371                # computed from screw coordinates in IFR
3372                self.X = [SE3AdjInvMatrix(
3373                    self.A[i])*self.Y[i] for i in range(self.n)]
3374
3375        elif self.B:
3376            # print('Using relative configuration (B) of the body frames')
3377            FK_C = [self.B[0]*SE3Exp(self.X[0], q[0])]
3378            for i in range(1, self.n):
3379                FK_C.append(FK_C[i-1]*self.B[i]*SE3Exp(self.X[i], q[i]))
3380            self._FK_C = FK_C
3381        else:
3382            # 'Absolute (A) or Relative (B) configuration of the bodies should be provided in class!'
3383            raise ValueError("Joint screw coordinates and/or reference configuration of bodies not set.")
3384
3385        # Block diagonal matrix A (6n x 6n) of the Adjoint of body frame
3386        if self._A is not None:
3387            A = self._A
3388        else:
3389            A = Matrix(Identity(6*self.n))
3390            for i in range(self.n):
3391                for j in range(i):
3392                    Crel = SE3Inv(FK_C[i])*FK_C[j]
3393                    AdCrel = SE3AdjMatrix(Crel)
3394                    r = 6*(i)
3395                    c = 6*(j)
3396                    A[r:r+6, c:c+6] = AdCrel
3397            self._A = A
3398        return FK_C, A
3399
3400    def _calc_A_matrix_tree(
3401        self, q: MutableDenseMatrix
3402        ) -> tuple[list[MutableDenseMatrix], MutableDenseMatrix]:
3403        """Calculate forward kinematics and the block diagonal matrix 
3404        A (6n x 6n) of the Adjoint of body frame for tree like robot 
3405        structures.
3406
3407        Args:
3408            q (sympy.MutableDenseMatrix): 
3409                Generalized position vector.
3410
3411        Raises:
3412            ValueError: 
3413                Joint screw coordinates or body reference configuration 
3414                not found.
3415
3416        Returns:
3417            tuple[list[MutableDenseMatrix], MutableDenseMatrix]: (FK, A)
3418        """
3419        if self._FK_C is not None:
3420            FK_C = self._FK_C
3421        elif self.A:
3422            # print("Using absolute configuration (A) of the body frames")
3423            FK_f = []
3424            FK_C = []
3425            for i in range(self.n):
3426                if self.parent[i] == 0: # bodies with no predecessor
3427                    # Initialization for the first body
3428                    FK_f.append(SE3Exp(self.Y[i], q[i]))
3429                    FK_C.append(FK_f[i]*self.A[i])
3430                else:
3431                    FK_f.append(FK_f[self.parent[i]-1]*SE3Exp(self.Y[i], q[i]))
3432                    FK_C.append(FK_f[i]*self.A[i])      
3433            self._FK_C = FK_C
3434            if not self.X:
3435                # Joint screw coordinates in body-fixed representation 
3436                # computed from screw coordinates in IFR
3437                self.X = [SE3AdjInvMatrix(
3438                    self.A[i])*self.Y[i] for i in range(self.n)]
3439
3440        elif self.B:
3441            # print('Using relative configuration (B) of the body frames')
3442            FK_C = []
3443            for i in range(self.n):
3444                if self.parent[i] == 0: # bodies with no predecessor
3445                    # Initialization for the first body
3446                    FK_C.append(self.B[i]*SE3Exp(self.X[i], q[i]))
3447                else:
3448                    FK_C.append(FK_C[self.parent[i]-1]*self.B[i]*SE3Exp(self.X[i], q[i]))
3449        else:
3450            # 'Absolute (A) or Relative (B) configuration of the bodies should be provided in class!'
3451            raise ValueError("Joint screw coordinates and/or reference configuration of bodies not set.")
3452
3453        # Block diagonal matrix A (6n x 6n) of the Adjoint of body frame
3454        if self._A is not None:
3455            A = self._A
3456        else:
3457            A = Matrix(Identity(6*self.n))
3458            for i in range(self.n):        
3459                if True:
3460                # if self.parent[i] != 0:
3461                    for k in self.support[i]:
3462                        j = k-1
3463                        Crel = SE3Inv(FK_C[i])*FK_C[j]
3464                        AdCrel = SE3AdjMatrix(Crel)
3465                        r = 6*(i)
3466                        c = 6*(j)
3467                        A[r:r+6, c:c+6] = AdCrel
3468            self._A = A
3469        return FK_C, A
3470    
3471    def _find_start_index(self) -> int:
3472        """Guess if 0 or 1 is the first index in the robot by analysing 
3473        used variable names.
3474
3475        Returns:
3476            int: index.
3477        """
3478        # search all symbols
3479        syms = set()
3480        for i in self.Mb:
3481            syms.update(i.free_symbols)
3482        for i in self.body_ref_config:
3483            syms.update(i.free_symbols)
3484        for i in self.joint_screw_coord:
3485            syms.update(i.free_symbols)
3486        # search all indices in symbols
3487        indices = []
3488        for i in syms:
3489            indices.extend(regex.findall("\d+",str(i)))
3490        #find smalles used index
3491        if indices:
3492            if min([int(i) for i in indices]) == 0:
3493                return 0
3494            if max([int(i) for i in indices]) == self.n -1:
3495                return 0
3496        return 1

3498    def _save_vectors(self, q: MutableDenseMatrix, qd: MutableDenseMatrix, 
3499                      q2d: MutableDenseMatrix, q3d: MutableDenseMatrix, 
3500                      q4d: MutableDenseMatrix, WEE: MutableDenseMatrix, 
3501                      WDEE: MutableDenseMatrix, W2DEE: MutableDenseMatrix) -> None:
3502        """Save generalized vectors als class parameter.
3503
3504        Args:
3505            q (sympy.Matrix): 
3506                (n,1) Generalized position vector.
3507            qd (sympy.Matrix): 
3508                (n,1) Generalized velocity vector.
3509            q2d (sympy.Matrix): 
3510                (n,1) Generalized acceleration vector.
3511            q3d (sympy.Matrix): 
3512                (n,1) Generalized jerk vector.
3513            q4d (sympy.Matrix): 
3514                (n,1) Generalized jounce vector.
3515            WEE (sympy.Matrix): 
3516                (6,1) WEE (t) = [Mx,My,Mz,Fx,Fy,Fz] is the time varying 
3517                wrench on the EE link. 
3518            WDEE (sympy.Matrix): 
3519                (6,1) WDEE (t) = [dMx,dMy,dMz,dFx,dFy,dFz] is the derivative 
3520                of the time varying wrench on the EE link. 
3521            W2DEE (sympy.Matrix): 
3522                (6,1) W2DEE (t) = [ddMx,ddMy,ddMz,ddFx,ddFy,ddFz] is the 
3523                2nd derivative of the time varying wrench on the EE link. 
3524        """
3525        if not self.q: self.q = q 
3526        if not self.qd: self.qd = qd 
3527        if not self.q2d: self.q2d = q2d 
3528        if not self.q3d: self.q3d = q3d 
3529        if not self.q4d: self.q4d = q4d
3530        if self.WEE == zeros(6,1) and WEE is not Ellipsis: self.WEE = WEE
3531        if self.WDEE == zeros(6,1) and WDEE is not Ellipsis: self.WDEE = WDEE
3532        if self.W2DEE == zeros(6,1) and W2DEE is not Ellipsis: self.W2DEE = W2DEE
3533        
3534    def _time_derivative(self, expression: sympy.Expr, level: int=1) -> sympy.Expr:
3535        """Generate time derivative of expression by substituting 
3536        generalized vectors with time dependent functions,
3537        let sympy calculate the time derivative, and resubstitute the 
3538        generalized vectors.
3539
3540        Used for unit testing.
3541        
3542        Warning: This does not support external wrenches yet.
3543
3544        Args:
3545            expression (sympy.Expr): 
3546                expression dependent on generalized vectors.
3547            level (int, optional): 
3548                Order of derivative to evaluate. Defaults to 1.
3549
3550        Returns:
3551            sympy.Expr: Derived expression.
3552        """
3553        # generate dynamic symbols as substitutes
3554        startindex = 1
3555        if self.n > 1:
3556            subq = Matrix(sympy.physics.mechanics.dynamicsymbols(
3557                " ".join(f"subq{i}" for i in range(startindex,startindex+self.n))))
3558            subqd =  subq.diff()
3559            subq2d = subqd.diff() 
3560            subq3d = subq2d.diff() 
3561            subq4d = subq3d.diff() 
3562        else:
3563            subq = Matrix([sympy.physics.mechanics.dynamicsymbols(
3564                " ".join(f"subq{i}" for i in range(startindex,startindex+self.n)))])
3565            subqd =  subq.diff()
3566            subq2d = subqd.diff() 
3567            subq3d = subq2d.diff() 
3568            subq4d = subq3d.diff()
3569        # substitute
3570        expression = (expression.subs(zip(self.q,subq))
3571                                .subs(zip(self.qd,subqd))
3572                                .subs(zip(self.q2d,subq2d))
3573                                .subs(zip(self.q3d,subq3d))
3574                                .subs(zip(self.q4d,subq4d)))
3575        # derivative
3576        for _ in range(level):
3577            expression = expression.diff("t")
3578        # resubstitute
3579        expression = (expression.subs(zip(subq4d,self.q4d))
3580                                .subs(zip(subq3d,self.q3d))
3581                                .subs(zip(subq2d,self.q2d))
3582                                .subs(zip(subqd,self.qd))
3583                                .subs(zip(subq,self.q))
3584                                )
3585        return expression
3586

SymbolicKinDyn Symbolic tool to compute equations of motion of serial chain robots and autogenerate code from the calculated equations. This tool supports generation of python, C and Matlab code.

Arguments:
  • gravity_vector (sympy.Matrix, optional): Vector of gravity. Defaults to None.
  • ee (sympy.Matrix | list of sympy.Matrix, optional): End-effector configuration with reference to last link body fixed frame in the chain. This link can be selected manually using the parameter ee_parent. If there is more than one end-effector use a list of transforms instead. Defaults to None.
  • body_ref_config (list of sympy.Matrix, optional): List of reference configurations of bodies in body-fixed or spatial representation, dependent on selected config_representation. Leave empty for dH Parameter usage (dhToScrewCoord(...)). Defaults to [].
  • joint_screw_coord (list of sympy.Matrix, optional): List of joint screw coordinates in body-fixed or spatial representation, dependent on selected config_representation. Leave empty for dH Parameter usage (dhToScrewCoord(...)). Defaults to [].
  • config_representation (str, optional): Use body fixed or spatial representation for reference configuration of bodies and joint screw coordinates. Has to be "body_fixed" or "spatial". Defaults to "spatial".
  • Mb (list of sympy.Matrix, optional): List of Mass Inertia matrices for all links. Only necessary for inverse dynamics. Defaults to [].
  • parent (list, optional): list of parent link indices for any joint. Use 0 for world. Only necessary for tree-like robot structures. Defaults to [].
  • support (list, optional): list of lists with one list per link which includes all support links beginning with the first link in the chain and including the current link. Only necessary for tree-like robot structures. Defaults to [].
  • child (list, optional): list of lists with one list per link which includes all child links. Use empty list if no child link is present. Only necessary for tree-like robot structures. Defaults to [].
  • ee_parent (int | list, optional): parent link of the end effector frame. If there is more than one end-effector, use a list of indices instead. Defaults to None (= last link).
  • q (sympy.Matrix, optional): (n,1) Generalized position vector. Defaults to None.
  • qd (sympy.Matrix, optional): (n,1) Generalized velocity vector. Defaults to None.
  • q2d (sympy.Matrix, optional): (n,1) Generalized acceleration vector. Defaults to None.
  • q3d (sympy.Matrix, optional): (n,1) Generalized jerk vector. Defaults to None.
  • q4d (sympy.Matrix, optional): (n,1) Generalized jounce vector. Defaults to None.
  • WEE (sympy.Matrix | list, optional): (6,1) WEE (t) = [Mx,My,Mz,Fx,Fy,Fz] is the time varying wrench on the EE link. If there is more than one end-effector, you can use a list containing all wrenches instead. Defaults to zeros(6, 1).
  • WDEE (sympy.Matrix | list, optional): (6,1) WDEE (t) = [dMx,dMy,dMz,dFx,dFy,dFz] is the derivative of the time varying wrench on the EE link. If there is more than one end-effector, you can use a list containing all wrenches instead. Defaults to zeros(6, 1).
  • W2DEE (sympy.Matrix | list, optional): (6,1) W2DEE (t) = [ddMx,ddMy,ddMz,ddFx,ddFy,ddFz] is the 2nd derivative of the time varying wrench on the EE link. If there is more than one end-effector, you can use a list containing all wrenches instead. Defaults to zeros(6, 1).

Inverse dynamics using body fixed representation of the twists in closed form.

The following expressions are saved in the class and can be code generated afterwards: coriolis_centrifugal_matrix generalized_mass_inertia_matrix gravity_vector inverse_dynamics

Arguments:
  • q (sympy.Matrix, optional): (n,1) Generalized position vector. Defaults to None.
  • qd (sympy.Matrix, optional): (n,1) Generalized velocity vector. Defaults to None.
  • q2d (sympy.Matrix, optional): (n,1) Generalized acceleration vector. Defaults to None.
  • q3d (sympy.Matrix, optional): (n,1) Generalized jerk vector. Defaults to None.
  • q4d (sympy.Matrix, optional): (n,1) Generalized jounce vector. Defaults to None.
  • WEE (list | sympy.Matrix, optional): (6,1) WEE (t) = [Mx,My,Mz,Fx,Fy,Fz] is the time varying wrench on the EE link. If there is more than one end-effector, you can use a list containing all wrenches instead. Defaults to zeros(6, 1).
  • WDEE (list | sympy.Matrix, optional): (6,1) WDEE (t) = [dMx,dMy,dMz,dFx,dFy,dFz] is the derivative of the time varying wrench on the EE link. If there is more than one end-effector, you can use a list containing all wrenches instead. Defaults to zeros(6, 1).
  • W2DEE (list | sympy.Matrix, optional): (6,1) W2DEE (t) = [ddMx,ddMy,ddMz,ddFx,ddFy,ddFz] is the 2nd derivative of the time varying wrench on the EE link. If there is more than one end-effector, you can use a list containing all wrenches instead. Defaults to zeros(6, 1).
  • simplify (bool, optional): Use simplify command on saved expressions. Defaults to True.
  • cse (bool, optional): Use common subexpression elimination. Defaults to False.
  • parallel (bool, optional): Use parallel computation via multiprocessing. Defaults to True.
Raises:
  • ValueError: Joint screw coordinates and/or reference configuration of bodies not set.
Returns:

sympy.Matrix: Generalized forces

def partial_factor(self, exp: sympy.core.expr.Expr) -> sympy.core.expr.Expr: 
2663    def partial_factor(self, exp: sympy.Expr) -> sympy.Expr:
2664        """Partial factor simplification for sympy expression.
2665
2666        Args:
2667            exp (sympy.Expr): sympy expression.
2668
2669        Returns:
2670            sympy.Expr: modified sympy expression.
2671        """
2672        # split up matrices
2673        if (type(exp) == sympy.matrices.immutable.ImmutableDenseMatrix
2674            or type(exp) == sympy.matrices.dense.MutableDenseMatrix):
2675            new_expr = zeros(*exp.shape)
2676            for i in range(exp.shape[0]):
2677                for j in range(exp.shape[1]):
2678                    new_expr[i,j] = self.partial_factor(exp[i,j])
2679            return new_expr
2680            
2681        # seach for factors
2682        factor_map = defaultdict(set)
2683        const, additive_terms = exp.as_coeff_add()
2684        for term1, term2 in combinations(additive_terms, 2):
2685            common_terms = (
2686                set(term1.as_coeff_mul()[-1])
2687                & set(term2.as_coeff_mul()[-1])
2688            )
2689            if common_terms:
2690                common_factor = sympy.Mul(*common_terms)
2691                factor_map[common_factor] |= {term1, term2}
2692        
2693        # sort by number of operations represented by the terms
2694        factor_list = sorted(
2695            factor_map.items(),
2696            key = lambda i: (i[0].count_ops() + 1) * len(i[1])
2697        )[::-1]
2698
2699        # rebuild expression
2700        used = set()
2701        new_expr = nsimplify(0)
2702        for item in factor_list:
2703            factor = item[0]
2704            appearances = item[-1]
2705            terms = 0
2706            for instance in appearances:
2707                if instance not in used:
2708                    terms += instance.as_coefficient(factor)
2709                    used.add(instance)
2710            new_expr += factor * terms
2711        for term in set(additive_terms) - used:
2712            new_expr += term
2713        return new_expr + const

Partial factor simplification for sympy expression.

Arguments:
  • exp (sympy.Expr): sympy expression.
Returns:

sympy.Expr: modified sympy expression.

def collect_and_subs(self, ex: sympy.core.expr.Expr, terms: dict) -> sympy.core.expr.Expr: 
2715    def collect_and_subs(self, ex: sympy.Expr, terms: dict) -> sympy.Expr:
2716        for key in terms:
2717            if key.is_Atom:
2718                ex = ex.subs(key,terms[key])
2719            else:
2720                ex = ex.expand().collect(key).subs(key,terms[key])
2721        return ex
def simplify( self, exp: sympy.core.expr.Expr, cse: bool = False, simplify: bool = True) -> sympy.core.expr.Expr: 
2723    def simplify(self, exp: sympy.Expr, cse: bool=False, simplify: bool=True) -> sympy.Expr:
2724        """Faster simplify implementation for sympy expressions.
2725        Expressions can be different simplified as with sympy.simplify.
2726
2727        Args:
2728            exp (sympy expression): 
2729                Expression to simplify.
2730            cse (bool, optional): 
2731                Use common subexpression elimination. Defaults to False.
2732            simplify (bool, optional): 
2733                deactivate simplification by setting simplify to False. 
2734                Defaults to True.
2735
2736        Returns:
2737            sympy expression: Simplified expression.
2738        """
2739        if cse:
2740            exp = self._cse_expression(exp)
2741        if simplify:
2742            if (type(exp) == sympy.matrices.immutable.ImmutableDenseMatrix
2743                    or type(exp) == sympy.matrices.dense.MutableDenseMatrix):
2744                # fasten simplification of symmetric matrices
2745                if exp.is_square:
2746                    # test if matrix is symmetric
2747                    # numeric test is faster than is_symmetric method  for 
2748                    # long expressions
2749                    
2750                    # create matrix with randon values
2751                    num = lambdify(list(exp.free_symbols), exp, "numpy")(
2752                        *(random.random() for i in exp.free_symbols))
2753                    # if (random) matrix is symmetric, we have to simplify 
2754                    # less values
2755                    if numpy.allclose(num, num.T):
2756                        shape = exp.shape
2757                        m_exp = exp.as_mutable()
2758                        # simplify values only once in symmetric matrices
2759                        for i in range(shape[0]):
2760                            for j in range(i):
2761                                m_exp[i, j] = self.simplify(exp[i, j])
2762                                if i != j:
2763                                    m_exp[j, i] = exp[j, i]
2764                        return Matrix(m_exp)
2765            if type(exp) == sympy.matrices.dense.MutableDenseMatrix:
2766                exp = exp.as_immutable()
2767            exp = fu(exp)  # fast function to simplify sin and cos expressions
2768            exp = cancel(exp)
2769            exp = factor(exp)
2770            exp = powsimp(exp)
2771            exp = self.partial_factor(exp)
2772            exp = exp.doit()
2773        return exp

  • cse (bool, optional): Use common subexpression elimination. Defaults to False.
  • simplify (bool, optional): deactivate simplification by setting simplify to False. Defaults to True.
Returns:

sympy expression: Simplified expression.

2897        """Load robot from urdf.
2898
2899        Args:
2900            path (str): path to URDF.
2901            symbolic (bool, optional): 
2902                generate symbols for numeric values. 
2903                Defaults to False.
2904            cse (bool, optional): 
2905                use common subexpression elimination. Defaults to False.
2906            simplify_numbers (bool, optional): 
2907                Use eg. pi/2 instead of 1.5708. Defaults to True.
2908            tolerance (float, optional): 
2909                tolerance for simplify_numbers. Defaults to 0.0001.
2910            max_denominator (int, optional): 
2911                Maximum denominator to use for simplify numbers to avoid
2912                values like 13/153. Use 0 to deactivate. Defaults to 9.
2913
2914        Raises:
2915            NotImplementedError: supports only the joint types 
2916                "revolute", "continuous" and "prismatic".
2917        """        
2918        # load URDF
2919        robot = URDF.from_xml_file(path)
2920        
2921        self.config_representation = self.BODY_FIXED
2922        self.B = []
2923        self.X = []
2924        
2925        # get parent, child and support array
2926        self._create_topology_lists(robot)
2927        # init some variables for later
2928        fixed_origin = None
2929        fixed_links = []
2930        DOF = 0
2931        xyz_rpy_syms = []
2932        
2933        # count DOF
2934        for joint in robot.joints:
2935            if joint.joint_type in ["revolute", "continuous", "prismatic"]:
2936                DOF += 1
2937            elif joint.joint_type in ["fixed"]:
2938                pass
2939            else:
2940                raise NotImplementedError(
2941                    "Joint type '" + joint.joint_type+"' not implemented yet!")
2942
2943        ji = 0  # joint index of used joints
2944        jia = 0  # joint index of all joints (fixed included)
2945        joint_origins = []
2946        joint_origins_dict = {}
2947        for joint in robot.joints:
2948            name = joint.name
2949            
2950            # get SE3 pose from xyzrpy
2951            origin = xyz_rpy_to_matrix(joint.origin.xyz+joint.origin.rpy)
2952            if symbolic:
2953                xyz_rpy = Matrix(joint.origin.xyz+joint.origin.rpy)
2954                # substitute variables
2955                xyz_rpy_syms.append(
2956                    symbols(" ".join([name+"_%s" % s 
2957                                      for s in ["x", "y", "z", "roll", "pitch", "yar"]])))
2958                xyzrpylist = []
2959                if simplify_numbers:
2960                    # replace values like 3.142 with pi
2961                    for i in range(6):
2962                        if (self._nsimplify(xyz_rpy[i], 
2963                                           tolerance=tolerance, 
2964                                           max_denominator=max_denominator) 
2965                            in [0, -1, 1, pi, -pi, pi/2, -pi/2, 3*pi/2, -3*pi/2]
2966                            ):
2967                            xyzrpylist.append(
2968                                self._nsimplify(xyz_rpy[i], tolerance=tolerance,
2969                                                max_denominator=max_denominator))
2970                        else:
2971                            xyzrpylist.append(xyz_rpy_syms[jia][i])
2972                            self.assignment_dict[xyz_rpy_syms[jia]
2973                                                 [i]] = xyz_rpy[i]
2974                else:
2975                    # replace all values unequal 0, abs(1) with symbolic values
2976                    for i in range(6):
2977                        if xyz_rpy[i] == 0:
2978                            xyzrpylist.append(0)
2979                        elif xyz_rpy[i] == 1:
2980                            xyzrpylist.append(1)
2981                        elif xyz_rpy[i] == -1:
2982                            xyzrpylist.append(-1)
2983                        else:
2984                            xyzrpylist.append(xyz_rpy_syms[jia][i])
2985                            self.assignment_dict[xyz_rpy_syms[jia]
2986                                                 [i]] = xyz_rpy[i]
2987                # get new SE3 Pose from xyzrpy
2988                origin = xyz_rpy_to_matrix(xyzrpylist)
2989                if cse:
2990                    origin = self._cse_expression(origin)
2991            elif simplify_numbers:
2992                for i in range(4):
2993                    for j in range(4):
2994                        origin[i, j] = self._nsimplify(
2995                            origin[i, j], [pi], tolerance=tolerance,
2996                            max_denominator=max_denominator)
2997            # save SE3 pose in list
2998            joint_origins.append(origin)
2999            joint_origins_dict[name] = origin
3000            
3001            # add fixed parents to origin
3002            if joint.joint_type in ["revolute", "continuous", "prismatic"]:
3003                axis = Matrix(joint.axis)
3004                
3005                # calc fixed origin from parent origins:
3006                fixed_origin = Matrix(Identity(4))
3007                parent_joint = copy.copy(joint)
3008                while True :
3009                    try:
3010                        parent_joint = robot.joint_map[robot.parent_map[parent_joint.parent][0]]
3011                    except KeyError: # base_link has no parent
3012                        break
3013                    if parent_joint.type == "fixed":
3014                        fixed_origin = joint_origins_dict[parent_joint.name] * fixed_origin
3015                    else: # stop when last non fixed joint is reached
3016                        break
3017
3018                # transform
3019                origin = fixed_origin * origin 
3020                
3021                if simplify_numbers:
3022                    for i in range(3):
3023                        axis[i] = self._nsimplify(axis[i], [pi], tolerance=tolerance,
3024                                            max_denominator=max_denominator)
3025                
3026                self.B.append(Matrix(origin))
3027
3028                if joint.joint_type in ["revolute", "continuous"]:
3029                    self.X.append(Matrix(axis).col_join(Matrix([0, 0, 0])))
3030                else:
3031                    self.X.append(Matrix(Matrix([0, 0, 0])).col_join(axis))
3032                ji += 1
3033            elif joint.joint_type == "fixed":
3034                fixed_links.append((joint.parent, joint.child))
3035            jia += 1
3036
3037        self.Mb = []
3038        i = 0
3039        first_non_fixed = 1
3040        for link in robot.links:
3041            name = link.name
3042            # ignore base link
3043            if i < first_non_fixed:
3044                if name in [x[1] for x in fixed_links]:
3045                    first_non_fixed += 1
3046                i += 1
3047                continue
3048            inertia = Matrix(link.inertial.inertia.to_matrix())
3049            mass = link.inertial.mass
3050            inertiaorigin = xyz_rpy_to_matrix(link.inertial.origin.xyz+link.inertial.origin.rpy)
3051            if symbolic:
3052                I_syms = symbols("Ixx_%s Ixy_%s Ixz_%s Iyy_%s Iyz_%s Izz_%s" % (
3053                    name, name, name, name, name, name))
3054                c_syms = symbols("cx_%s cy_%s cz_%s" % (name, name, name))
3055                I = inertia_matrix(*I_syms)
3056                m = symbols("m_%s" % name)
3057                cg = Matrix([*c_syms])
3058            else:
3059                I = Matrix(inertia)
3060                m = mass
3061                cg = Matrix(inertiaorigin[0:3, 3])
3062            M = mass_matrix_mixed_data(m, I, cg)
3063            # if link is child of fixed joint
3064            if name in [x[1] for x in fixed_links]:
3065                parent_joint = robot.joint_map[robot.parent_map[name][0]]
3066                while True:
3067                    if parent_joint.type == 'fixed':
3068                        M = (SE3AdjInvMatrix(joint_origins_dict[parent_joint.name]).T 
3069                             * M * SE3AdjInvMatrix(joint_origins_dict[parent_joint.name]))
3070                    else:
3071                        break
3072                    try:
3073                        parent_joint = robot.joint_map[robot.parent_map[parent_joint.parent][0]]
3074                    except KeyError:
3075                        break

3081                #     j -= 1

3083                    self.Mb[-1] += M
3084                except IndexError: # Base dynamics not important
3085                    pass

3087                continue
3088            self.Mb.append(M)
3089            i += 1
3090        if simplify_numbers and not symbolic:

3093                    for j in range(6):
3094                        M[i, j] = self._nsimplify(
3095                            M[i, j], [pi], tolerance=tolerance,
3096                            max_denominator=max_denominator)
3097        if self.ee is None:

3099        if self.gravity_vector is None:
3100            self.gravity_vector = Matrix([0,0,-9.81])

def dh_to_screw_coord(self, DH_param_table: sympy.matrices.dense.MutableDenseMatrix) -> None: 
3123    def dh_to_screw_coord(self, DH_param_table: MutableDenseMatrix) -> None:
3124        """Build screw coordinate paramters (joint axis frames and 
3125        body reference frames) from a given modified Denavit-Hartenberg 
3126        (DH) parameter table.
3127        Joint screw coordinates and reference configurations of bodies 
3128        are directly applied to class.
3129
3130        Args:
3131            DH_param_table (array_like): 
3132                Table with modified DH parameters (n,5) 
3133                -> (gamma,alpha,d,theta,r)
3134        """
3135        number_of_frames = DH_param_table.shape[0]
3136        self.B = []
3137        self.X = []
3138        for i in range(number_of_frames):
3139            # Reference configurations of bodies (i.e. of body-fixed 
3140            # reference frames) w.r.t their previous bodies
3141            # gamma, alpha, d, theta,r
3142            frame = DH_param_table[i, :]
3143            gamma = frame[0]
3144            alpha = frame[1]
3145            d = frame[2]
3146            theta = frame[3]
3147            r = frame[4]
3148            self.B.append(SO3Exp(Matrix([1, 0, 0]), alpha)
3149                          .row_join(Matrix([d, 0, 0]))
3150                          .col_join(Matrix([0, 0, 0, 1]).T)
3151                          * SO3Exp(Matrix([0, 0, 1]), theta)
3152                          .row_join(Matrix([0, 0, r]))
3153                          .col_join(Matrix([0, 0, 0, 1]).T)
3154                          )
3155
3156            #  Joint screw coordinates in body-fixed representation
3157            if gamma == 0:
3158                self.X.append(Matrix([0, 0, 1, 0, 0, 0]))
3159            else:
3160                self.X.append(Matrix([0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1]))
